WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.425 --> 00:00:03.883
- [Narrator] The history of our story began long ago.

00:00:03.883 --> 00:00:06.633
(dramatic music)

00:00:08.758 --> 00:00:12.550
At one point in time, around 3 billion years ago,

00:00:12.550 --> 00:00:13.841
we were floating around

00:00:13.841 --> 00:00:17.883
as little tiny atoms in the little Petri dish of the world.

00:00:18.966 --> 00:00:22.091
Fast forward to around 6 million years ago,

00:00:22.091 --> 00:00:25.091
and we see the emergence of the first hominids,

00:00:25.091 --> 00:00:28.133
the family of primates that include humans.

00:00:28.133 --> 00:00:33.008
1.9 million years ago, homoerectus was the first species

00:00:33.008 --> 00:00:36.591
to leave Africa and colonize other parts of the world.

00:00:36.591 --> 00:00:40.383
They had larger brains than their primate ancestors.

00:00:40.383 --> 00:00:42.758
Around 400,000 years ago,

00:00:42.758 --> 00:00:45.550
the first evidence of the Neanderthals,

00:00:45.550 --> 00:00:48.300
their bodies were adapted to the cold environments

00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:50.091
of Europe and Western Asia.

00:00:50.091 --> 00:00:52.508
Their distinctive facial features were some

00:00:52.508 --> 00:00:55.091
of the most human-like ever seen.

00:00:56.050 --> 00:01:01.050
Then came us, the only surviving species of the homo genus.

00:01:01.300 --> 00:01:05.508
But how did homo sapiens rise into a global dominance

00:01:05.508 --> 00:01:07.716
through the mechanism of civilization?

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:12.050
(dramatic music)

00:01:16.591 --> 00:01:18.841
We begin our story in the fertile lands

00:01:18.841 --> 00:01:22.508
of Mesopotamia in 4,000 BCE,

00:01:22.508 --> 00:01:26.008
nestled between the great Tigris and Euphrates rivers

00:01:26.008 --> 00:01:28.216
and the Sumerian city of Uruk.

00:01:28.216 --> 00:01:30.008
Instead of relying on hunting

00:01:30.008 --> 00:01:33.008
and gathering like our ancestors of the past,

00:01:33.008 --> 00:01:35.841
the citizens of Uruk were able to develop a way

00:01:35.841 --> 00:01:39.258
to harvest cereal grains like wheat and barley.

00:01:39.258 --> 00:01:41.341
However, turning cereal grains

00:01:41.341 --> 00:01:44.258
into edible foods took a lot of work.

00:01:44.258 --> 00:01:45.466
In the beginning, they had

00:01:45.466 --> 00:01:47.675
to use an invention called a hand mill,

00:01:47.675 --> 00:01:49.925
which consisted of two stones.

00:01:49.925 --> 00:01:53.008
As the grains were crushed between the two stones,

00:01:53.008 --> 00:01:55.175
the flour was collected in a container

00:01:55.175 --> 00:01:57.175
and stored for future use.

00:01:57.175 --> 00:02:00.008
This was the start of something great.

00:02:00.008 --> 00:02:02.341
This complex strenuous process

00:02:02.341 --> 00:02:06.300
was our modern world's first example of agriculture.

00:02:06.300 --> 00:02:09.050
We no longer depended on hunting animals

00:02:09.050 --> 00:02:11.550
or picking berries for our food.

00:02:11.550 --> 00:02:13.925
Rather than using human ingenuity,

00:02:13.925 --> 00:02:16.800
we can create our own food source.

00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:19.758
This allowed Uruk to prosper into a place

00:02:19.758 --> 00:02:22.716
with over 50,000 residents.

00:02:22.716 --> 00:02:26.841
However, this change did have a change on the human body.

00:02:26.841 --> 00:02:29.133
The average height of men drastically shrunk

00:02:29.133 --> 00:02:31.925
from five foot nine to five foot three,

00:02:31.925 --> 00:02:33.800
and for women, they shrunk on average

00:02:33.800 --> 00:02:36.175
from five foot, three to five feet.

00:02:36.175 --> 00:02:39.800
Instead of being the super athletes we were of the past,

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:43.008
we were smaller, less noticeable farmers.

00:02:43.008 --> 00:02:45.300
People also became landlocked,

00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:49.633
changing the very essence of what it means to be human.

00:02:49.633 --> 00:02:52.300
In the early 3000 BCE,

00:02:52.300 --> 00:02:55.383
according to legend, King Gilgamesh began his rule

00:02:55.383 --> 00:02:57.591
as a Sumerian king of his region.

00:02:57.591 --> 00:03:00.633
However, by the end of 3000, BCE,

00:03:00.633 --> 00:03:03.633
the Acadians ousted the Sumerians.

00:03:03.633 --> 00:03:07.466
Sargon the Great took power and conquered all of Sumeria.

00:03:12.841 --> 00:03:16.091
While in the Indus Valley in modern day Pakistan,

00:03:16.091 --> 00:03:18.300
a new civilization was growing.

00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.341
The Indus Valley civilization,

00:03:20.341 --> 00:03:24.633
3300 to 1300 BCE was most notable

00:03:24.633 --> 00:03:27.300
for its highly advanced toilet system.

00:03:27.300 --> 00:03:28.925
The toilets were built with a seat

00:03:28.925 --> 00:03:32.008
and a chute that led to the underground drainage system.

00:03:32.008 --> 00:03:34.383
The sewage was then carried away from the homes

00:03:34.383 --> 00:03:36.216
through a network of covered drains,

00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:38.091
preventing disease spread.

00:03:38.091 --> 00:03:39.175
The waste was treated

00:03:39.175 --> 00:03:41.425
and disposed outside of city limits,

00:03:41.425 --> 00:03:44.091
helping to keep the cities clean and hygienic.

00:03:49.133 --> 00:03:51.508
While in Egypt, they were more consumed

00:03:51.508 --> 00:03:54.716
with building pyramids than basic human plumbing.

00:03:54.716 --> 00:03:57.925
This was because in ancient Egyptian religion,

00:03:57.925 --> 00:03:59.716
it was believed that when a Pharaoh was

00:03:59.716 --> 00:04:03.008
to die in the physical world, his spirit would continue

00:04:03.008 --> 00:04:06.091
to live on in the afterlife in which they would continue

00:04:06.091 --> 00:04:07.883
to rule in perpetuity

00:04:07.883 --> 00:04:10.675
and where they would be worshiped by the living.

00:04:10.675 --> 00:04:12.175
Inside these pyramids,

00:04:12.175 --> 00:04:15.133
the Pharaoh's body was carefully mummified.

00:04:15.133 --> 00:04:18.508
A process believed to preserve his physical form

00:04:18.508 --> 00:04:21.633
and help ensure his spirit's journey to the afterlife.

00:04:21.633 --> 00:04:24.050
The pyramid was also filled with offerings

00:04:24.050 --> 00:04:26.758
and treasures intended to provide the Pharaoh

00:04:26.758 --> 00:04:29.591
with the resources he would need in the afterlife.

00:04:29.591 --> 00:04:32.716
Every Pharaoh wanted to make sure they were immortal.

00:04:32.716 --> 00:04:35.091
They wanted to succeed in the afterlife.

00:04:35.091 --> 00:04:37.383
They wanted to be worshiped forever.

00:04:37.383 --> 00:04:41.216
That's why it was an utmost priority for Egyptian Pharaohs

00:04:41.216 --> 00:04:44.716
to build pyramids for themselves when laid to rest.

00:04:44.716 --> 00:04:49.175
It started when Pharaoh Djoser, 2667 to 2648, BCE,

00:04:50.550 --> 00:04:52.800
built the Step Pyramid at Saqqara,

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:57.800
followed by Sneferu, 2613 to 2589 BCE,

00:04:58.050 --> 00:04:59.800
who built several pyramids

00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:02.550
such as the Bent Pyramid and the Red Pyramid.

00:05:02.550 --> 00:05:05.966
Then came the Pharaoh Khufu, 2589 to 2566 BCE,

00:05:08.258 --> 00:05:11.050
who built the famous Great Pyramid of Giza

00:05:11.050 --> 00:05:14.675
in a labor intensive 20 year process,

00:05:14.675 --> 00:05:17.758
one that the world still marvels at today.

00:05:17.758 --> 00:05:20.633
Khufu was then followed by Pharaohs Khafre

00:05:20.633 --> 00:05:23.758
and Mekaure who built these slightly smaller second

00:05:23.758 --> 00:05:26.425
and third pyramids of Giza respectively.

00:05:31.216 --> 00:05:35.341
While over in China in the year 2100 BCE,

00:05:35.341 --> 00:05:38.175
the first Chinese dynasty was upon us.

00:05:38.175 --> 00:05:40.050
Like the people of Mesopotamia,

00:05:40.050 --> 00:05:43.383
the Chinese were ever reliant on agriculture,

00:05:43.383 --> 00:05:47.050
producing rice, wheat, and barley among other crops.

00:05:47.050 --> 00:05:50.633
However, as legend has it, the Yellow River flooded.

00:05:50.633 --> 00:05:53.966
These massive floods would destroy all the crops

00:05:53.966 --> 00:05:56.550
leading to massive famine and suffering.

00:05:56.550 --> 00:05:58.925
However, not all was to be lost

00:05:58.925 --> 00:06:01.758
because Yu The Great was on his way.

00:06:01.758 --> 00:06:04.258
Yu was so distraught by this problem

00:06:04.258 --> 00:06:06.466
that he would spend his days traveling up

00:06:06.466 --> 00:06:08.341
and down the Yellow River.

00:06:08.341 --> 00:06:11.133
He found ways to divert the rivers by building levies

00:06:11.133 --> 00:06:14.550
and dikes so that he could regulate the waterways.

00:06:14.550 --> 00:06:17.675
Then after 13 years of hard work,

00:06:17.675 --> 00:06:20.841
the floods could no longer wreak havoc on the land.

00:06:20.841 --> 00:06:25.050
The people were overjoyed and Yu was hailed as a savior.

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:28.591
That was the start of the first Chinese dynasty,

00:06:28.591 --> 00:06:30.175
the Xia Dynasty.

00:06:30.175 --> 00:06:33.091
Though the accuracy of this tale is questioned

00:06:33.091 --> 00:06:36.716
by historians, it does establish an important precedent.

00:06:36.716 --> 00:06:39.966
The idea is that power ought to follow one's merit.

00:06:39.966 --> 00:06:42.591
An individual who deserves absolute power

00:06:42.591 --> 00:06:44.716
shall have absolute power.

00:06:44.716 --> 00:06:48.508
This idea would shape the world for years to come

00:06:48.508 --> 00:06:51.841
and cause the people of ancient China to follow him

00:06:51.841 --> 00:06:55.591
to create the first ever Chinese dynasty.

00:07:01.050 --> 00:07:04.591
While back over in Mesopotamia around 1772, BCE,

00:07:06.216 --> 00:07:10.550
a Babylonian king named King Hammurabi created the basis

00:07:10.550 --> 00:07:13.675
of the legal system as we know it today,

00:07:13.675 --> 00:07:16.966
Hammurabi ordered the creation of a seven foot tall,

00:07:16.966 --> 00:07:19.258
two foot wide stone slab.

00:07:19.258 --> 00:07:24.091
Written on it was a system of 282 laws that each citizen

00:07:24.091 --> 00:07:26.216
of his kingdom was to follow.

00:07:26.216 --> 00:07:30.300
Such laws included various laws such as law one,

00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:33.383
if a man brings an accusation against another man,

00:07:33.383 --> 00:07:36.258
charging him with murder, but cannot prove it,

00:07:36.258 --> 00:07:38.966
the accuser shall be put to death.

00:07:38.966 --> 00:07:43.341
Law 196, if a man destroys the eye of another man,

00:07:43.341 --> 00:07:45.550
they shall destroy his eye.

00:07:45.550 --> 00:07:49.300
Law 197 says, if he breaks another man's bone,

00:07:49.300 --> 00:07:50.591
they shall break it.

00:07:50.591 --> 00:07:54.591
Law 199, if he destroys the eye of a man's slave

00:07:54.591 --> 00:07:56.966
or breaks the bone of a man's slave,

00:07:56.966 --> 00:07:59.591
he shall pay one half his price.

00:07:59.591 --> 00:08:02.550
However, what King Hammurabi did was create

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:05.091
a society based on laws.

00:08:05.091 --> 00:08:06.591
He laid out strict laws,

00:08:06.591 --> 00:08:10.008
placing people into certain casts of life and value.

00:08:10.008 --> 00:08:12.008
Everyone was worth a different amount

00:08:12.008 --> 00:08:14.425
based on what class they were in society.

00:08:14.425 --> 00:08:17.883
There was no illusion of equality in ancient Babylon.

00:08:17.883 --> 00:08:19.925
Instead, it was pretty clear the value

00:08:19.925 --> 00:08:23.133
of a noble's bone was worth more than a plebeian's

00:08:23.133 --> 00:08:26.175
which in turn was worth more than a slave's.

00:08:26.175 --> 00:08:29.675
An idea we continue to see throughout history.

00:08:35.216 --> 00:08:37.050
While in modern day Turkey,

00:08:37.050 --> 00:08:39.925
a lesser known civilization came to power,

00:08:39.925 --> 00:08:43.008
the Hittites' Empire under the charismatic rule

00:08:43.008 --> 00:08:47.841
of the leader, Labarnas, 1680 to 1650 BCE,

00:08:47.841 --> 00:08:51.300
he was a skilled ruler with a single vision in mind.

00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:54.966
Uniting the Hittite city states under a single rule.

00:08:54.966 --> 00:08:57.591
Labarnas led his army from city to city,

00:08:57.591 --> 00:08:59.591
conquering neighboring city states

00:08:59.591 --> 00:09:02.341
and making alliances with their leaders.

00:09:02.341 --> 00:09:04.425
He was a shrewd diplomat

00:09:04.425 --> 00:09:07.341
and he used his diplomatic skills to win over the hearts

00:09:07.341 --> 00:09:08.966
and minds of the people.

00:09:08.966 --> 00:09:11.216
Eventually, Labarnas became the ruler

00:09:11.216 --> 00:09:15.091
of all the Hittite city states and established the empire.

00:09:15.091 --> 00:09:19.091
He was a just and fair ruler and was loved by his people.

00:09:19.091 --> 00:09:21.508
Under his rule, the Hittites prospered

00:09:21.508 --> 00:09:24.591
and their territory expanded, leaving them right next

00:09:24.591 --> 00:09:26.591
to their neighbors in Egypt.

00:09:32.008 --> 00:09:34.341
While in modern day Greece, a collection

00:09:34.341 --> 00:09:37.466
of city states emerged on the European continent,

00:09:37.466 --> 00:09:42.133
Mycenean Greece, 1600 BCE to 1100 BCE

00:09:42.133 --> 00:09:45.591
was dominated by an elite warrior society

00:09:45.591 --> 00:09:49.175
and consisted of a network of palace centered states

00:09:49.175 --> 00:09:53.050
that developed rigid, hierarchical political, social,

00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:54.925
and economic systems.

00:09:54.925 --> 00:09:57.550
At the head of this society was the king.

00:09:57.550 --> 00:10:00.300
However, unlike a unified civilization,

00:10:00.300 --> 00:10:02.425
each city was on its own.

00:10:02.425 --> 00:10:04.175
A city state is a city that

00:10:04.175 --> 00:10:08.466
with its surrounding territory forms an independent state.

00:10:08.466 --> 00:10:10.216
The development of city states such as Troy,

00:10:10.216 --> 00:10:12.758
Mycenae, and Pylos start to grow.

00:10:12.758 --> 00:10:16.133
The first remnants of the Greek written language known

00:10:16.133 --> 00:10:19.591
as Linear B, also started to emerge.

00:10:19.591 --> 00:10:20.466
The first record

00:10:20.466 --> 00:10:24.633
of any Indo-European Greek record we have today.

00:10:30.591 --> 00:10:34.133
While back in Egypt, they started to create a social pyramid

00:10:34.133 --> 00:10:38.008
of another type, the Egyptian social pyramid.

00:10:38.008 --> 00:10:39.841
Like the Great Pyramid of Giza,

00:10:39.841 --> 00:10:41.675
it is more prominent at the bottom

00:10:41.675 --> 00:10:43.425
and tinier at the top.

00:10:43.425 --> 00:10:46.300
At the bottom lays the peasants and the slaves,

00:10:46.300 --> 00:10:49.591
they were responsible for doing all the manual labor.

00:10:49.591 --> 00:10:51.091
They worked on the lands.

00:10:51.091 --> 00:10:54.008
They would spend the day in and day out farming,

00:10:54.008 --> 00:10:56.425
producing food for all of Egypt.

00:10:56.425 --> 00:10:59.550
Then when the season to farm was over for the year,

00:10:59.550 --> 00:11:03.091
they would work on the Pharaoh's massive building projects.

00:11:03.091 --> 00:11:05.966
Literally building the pyramids.

00:11:07.133 --> 00:11:10.133
Slightly above the slaves came the artisans.

00:11:10.133 --> 00:11:12.466
They were the stone masons, the plasters,

00:11:12.466 --> 00:11:15.550
and the sculptors who created the exuberant art

00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:19.550
the wealthy desired, and for Egypt is most known for today.

00:11:19.550 --> 00:11:21.300
Then came the merchants

00:11:21.300 --> 00:11:24.633
who spent their days in navigating the Nile, trading gold,

00:11:24.633 --> 00:11:27.841
papyrus and linen to anyone who could afford it.

00:11:27.841 --> 00:11:29.133
They were well respected

00:11:29.133 --> 00:11:31.716
and able to make a healthy profit by selling.

00:11:31.716 --> 00:11:33.591
Then came the scribes.

00:11:33.591 --> 00:11:35.425
These masters of the word would go

00:11:35.425 --> 00:11:39.841
to specialized scribe schools just to master the language

00:11:39.841 --> 00:11:42.508
of ancient Egyptian hieroglyphics.

00:11:42.508 --> 00:11:43.883
In practical use,

00:11:43.883 --> 00:11:46.508
these scribes took account of the stores of food,

00:11:46.508 --> 00:11:48.300
various tax documents,

00:11:48.300 --> 00:11:51.258
and even the daily lives of the Pharaoh.

00:11:51.258 --> 00:11:54.258
After the scribes came the soldiers,

00:11:54.258 --> 00:11:55.341
the soldiers were tasked

00:11:55.341 --> 00:11:57.675
with protecting the Egyptian empire.

00:11:57.675 --> 00:11:59.841
They dedicated their lives to defend

00:11:59.841 --> 00:12:02.716
or make preemptive strikes against their enemy.

00:12:02.716 --> 00:12:04.633
Generally, they were well fed.

00:12:04.633 --> 00:12:07.591
Then near the top came the bureaucrats.

00:12:07.591 --> 00:12:11.216
These high ranking government officials did essential tasks

00:12:11.216 --> 00:12:14.050
at the top of society, like the viziers

00:12:14.050 --> 00:12:16.508
who ran the logistical tasks necessary

00:12:16.508 --> 00:12:18.341
to run a civilization.

00:12:18.341 --> 00:12:21.300
The priests oversaw taking care of the temples

00:12:21.300 --> 00:12:23.716
to ensure the gods were well cared for.

00:12:23.716 --> 00:12:27.091
The nobles oversaw specific regions of the empire

00:12:27.091 --> 00:12:29.341
and kept order in said regions.

00:12:29.341 --> 00:12:30.383
At the top,

00:12:30.383 --> 00:12:34.133
the purpose of everyone below was the pharaoh, the king,

00:12:34.133 --> 00:12:38.425
and the mediator between the gods and the world of men.

00:12:38.425 --> 00:12:41.216
The Pharaohs will be known to be supreme

00:12:41.216 --> 00:12:43.216
and all must succumb to it.

00:12:43.216 --> 00:12:44.633
When the Pharaoh dies,

00:12:44.633 --> 00:12:46.133
he will be buried in a pyramid

00:12:46.133 --> 00:12:48.383
in which he will help eternally rule

00:12:48.383 --> 00:12:50.425
over the Egyptian empire.

00:12:50.425 --> 00:12:54.216
Egyptian society was created to serve the Pharaoh.

00:12:54.216 --> 00:12:57.591
Taxes were taken from the farmers for the Pharaoh,

00:12:57.591 --> 00:13:00.466
and artisans made unique crafts for it.

00:13:00.466 --> 00:13:03.175
The merchants ensured the Pharaoh was well supplied

00:13:03.175 --> 00:13:04.550
with the needed goods.

00:13:04.550 --> 00:13:06.383
The scribes would follow the Pharaoh

00:13:06.383 --> 00:13:07.675
and record his thoughts.

00:13:07.675 --> 00:13:10.716
The soldiers made sure his empire was protected.

00:13:10.716 --> 00:13:14.383
The bureaucrats did the jobs the Pharaoh couldn't do.

00:13:14.383 --> 00:13:16.300
While the Pharaoh sat at the top

00:13:16.300 --> 00:13:18.800
and communicated with the gods.

00:13:18.800 --> 00:13:23.800
Pharaoh Ramesses II, 1279 to 1213 BCE,

00:13:24.008 --> 00:13:26.466
accomplished many extraordinary things

00:13:26.466 --> 00:13:28.300
by living in this social system.

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:30.716
He orchestrated the construction of the temple

00:13:30.716 --> 00:13:35.133
of Abu Simbel, the Ramesseum and the Temple of Karnak.

00:13:35.133 --> 00:13:38.133
He was also able to grow the Egyptian empire

00:13:38.133 --> 00:13:41.841
and re-conquer lands lost by other Pharaohs.

00:13:41.841 --> 00:13:46.008
Except for the land claimed by the Hittite empire.

00:13:53.466 --> 00:13:56.550
The Hittite king of the time, Mutwalli II,

00:13:56.550 --> 00:14:01.550
1295 to 1272 BCE was notorious for ordering his troops

00:14:02.091 --> 00:14:04.383
to attack his Egyptian neighbors.

00:14:04.383 --> 00:14:06.800
Following the example of Labarnas,

00:14:06.800 --> 00:14:10.050
Mutwalli wanted to unify the world under Hittite rule.

00:14:10.050 --> 00:14:12.341
However, Ramesses had enough.

00:14:12.341 --> 00:14:15.841
Other Pharaohs in the past have tried to stop the Hittites,

00:14:15.841 --> 00:14:19.133
but he knew if his empire was to ever succeed,

00:14:19.133 --> 00:14:21.008
he needed to attack back.

00:14:21.008 --> 00:14:23.758
His target is the city of Kadesh.

00:14:23.758 --> 00:14:27.383
Ramesses rode in on his chariot with four divisions

00:14:27.383 --> 00:14:32.008
of 20,000 men ready to dominate and kill Mutwalli.

00:14:32.008 --> 00:14:34.133
However, the Hittites already knew

00:14:34.133 --> 00:14:38.008
of the incoming Egyptian invasion through espionage.

00:14:38.008 --> 00:14:39.508
They fortified their city

00:14:39.508 --> 00:14:44.216
with 40,000 of his own men, a war was about to commence.

00:14:44.216 --> 00:14:46.675
Ramesses decided to split up his divisions

00:14:46.675 --> 00:14:50.591
to force Mutwalli out, but yet Mutwalli never did,

00:14:50.591 --> 00:14:52.466
a gruesome mistake.

00:14:52.466 --> 00:14:55.175
Splitting up his forces left him exposed,

00:14:55.175 --> 00:14:58.675
unable to get an advantage, allowing Mutwalli and the people

00:14:58.675 --> 00:15:01.133
of Kadesh a chance for victory.

00:15:01.133 --> 00:15:02.258
Historians believe

00:15:02.258 --> 00:15:04.925
that all they did was come out from the fortification

00:15:04.925 --> 00:15:08.258
of Kadesh and trap Ramesses II's forces

00:15:08.258 --> 00:15:10.341
in his army by the river.

00:15:10.341 --> 00:15:14.258
But yet for some unknown reason, they never did.

00:15:14.258 --> 00:15:17.758
Leaving the battle of Kadesh to end in a draw.

00:15:17.758 --> 00:15:21.050
After the battle though, both sides decided it would be best

00:15:21.050 --> 00:15:24.508
to stop attacking each other, that they should live in peace

00:15:24.508 --> 00:15:26.425
and unity in this world.

00:15:26.425 --> 00:15:28.550
Then after the death of Mutwalli

00:15:28.550 --> 00:15:31.425
the new king, Hattusili III, took the throne

00:15:31.425 --> 00:15:33.050
of the Hittite empire.

00:15:33.050 --> 00:15:34.800
Through the means of messengers,

00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:38.758
in the year 1258, BCE, both Ramesses

00:15:38.758 --> 00:15:43.508
and Hattusili signed the first peace treaty to ever exist.

00:15:43.508 --> 00:15:44.550
Reading in part,

00:15:44.550 --> 00:15:47.758
"Ramesses the Great King, the king of the country

00:15:47.758 --> 00:15:50.966
of Egypt shall never attack the country of Hatti

00:15:50.966 --> 00:15:53.758
to take possession of a part of this country.

00:15:53.758 --> 00:15:56.966
And Hattusili, the great king of the country of Hatti,

00:15:56.966 --> 00:16:00.633
shall never attack the country of Egypt to take possession

00:16:00.633 --> 00:16:02.550
of a part of that country."

00:16:02.550 --> 00:16:05.966
Then a period of friendship occurred between these two,

00:16:05.966 --> 00:16:10.466
once warring nations, the Hittites were skilled in metalwork

00:16:10.466 --> 00:16:14.466
and taught the Egyptians to make superior weapons and tools.

00:16:14.466 --> 00:16:16.466
At the same time, the Egyptians,

00:16:16.466 --> 00:16:19.258
master of agriculture shared their knowledge

00:16:19.258 --> 00:16:20.300
with the Hittites.

00:16:20.300 --> 00:16:23.550
Trade for the benefit of both civilizations,

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:27.008
both civilizations prospered because of this,

00:16:27.008 --> 00:16:29.300
peace can lead to prosperity.

00:16:29.300 --> 00:16:33.675
The agreement was kept in place until around 1200 BCE,

00:16:33.675 --> 00:16:36.341
because that's when the Hittite empire fell

00:16:36.341 --> 00:16:38.800
because of the constant attacks they faced

00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:40.425
from the sea people.

00:16:40.425 --> 00:16:41.841
Leaving the Hittite empire

00:16:41.841 --> 00:16:44.508
to be lost in the state of history.

00:16:50.300 --> 00:16:52.341
While on a continent far away,

00:16:52.341 --> 00:16:55.591
the first civilization in the Americas was taking foot

00:16:55.591 --> 00:16:57.383
in modern day Mexico.

00:16:57.383 --> 00:17:00.758
The Olmec civilization, 1200 BCE

00:17:00.758 --> 00:17:05.300
to 400 BCE is often considered the mother civilization

00:17:05.300 --> 00:17:07.966
of Native American civilizations.

00:17:07.966 --> 00:17:11.425
However, sadly though not much is known about them.

00:17:11.425 --> 00:17:12.633
Mainly due to their writing

00:17:12.633 --> 00:17:16.425
in a hieroglyph historians still can't decipher.

00:17:16.425 --> 00:17:17.758
One of the few remains

00:17:17.758 --> 00:17:22.216
we have are these 17 colossal stone heads.

00:17:22.216 --> 00:17:25.008
In Meso American culture, there is this belief

00:17:25.008 --> 00:17:26.591
that the head alone could contain

00:17:26.591 --> 00:17:30.383
an individual's emotion, experience, and soul.

00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:32.216
We may not know their leaders' names like

00:17:32.216 --> 00:17:35.758
of other civilizations like Ramesses and Hammurabi.

00:17:35.758 --> 00:17:38.175
When looking through the eyes of a stone head,

00:17:38.175 --> 00:17:40.633
we can still feel their presence,

00:17:40.633 --> 00:17:43.258
and in some ways, they remain immortal,

00:17:43.258 --> 00:17:45.091
enshrined in history.

00:17:45.091 --> 00:17:47.508
For one day, we may learn who they are.

00:17:51.966 --> 00:17:54.508
While in the East, the Zhou Dynasty,

00:17:54.508 --> 00:17:59.508
1046 to 256 BCE in China was taking its stride.

00:18:00.050 --> 00:18:01.841
The Zhou Dynasty gained power

00:18:01.841 --> 00:18:05.425
because of the failures of the less critical Shang dynasty,

00:18:05.425 --> 00:18:08.591
they believed in the idea of a mandate from heaven.

00:18:08.591 --> 00:18:10.341
This resulted in four principles

00:18:10.341 --> 00:18:12.508
in the Chinese dynastical structure

00:18:12.508 --> 00:18:14.758
that would be repeated repeatedly.

00:18:14.758 --> 00:18:18.175
One, heaven grants the emperor the right to rule.

00:18:18.175 --> 00:18:20.466
Two, since there is only one heaven,

00:18:20.466 --> 00:18:23.675
there can only be one emperor at any given time.

00:18:23.675 --> 00:18:27.300
Three, the emperor's virtue determines his right to rule,

00:18:27.300 --> 00:18:32.050
and four, no one dynasty has a permanent right to rule.

00:18:32.050 --> 00:18:35.508
A ruler in dynasty could lose the mandate from heaven,

00:18:35.508 --> 00:18:38.716
and the heavens weren't always on the side of the rulers.

00:18:38.716 --> 00:18:41.925
Over time, it will fade into another dynasty.

00:18:41.925 --> 00:18:45.591
The heavens would send signs of droughts, famines, floods,

00:18:45.591 --> 00:18:47.800
and earthquakes across the land,

00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:51.091
signaling they'd lost the blessing from above.

00:18:51.091 --> 00:18:53.425
This is how the Shang dynasty fell,

00:18:53.425 --> 00:18:56.341
and the Zhou Dynasty grew to prominence.

00:18:56.341 --> 00:18:59.425
The Zhou Dynasty brought another style of government

00:18:59.425 --> 00:19:01.675
and the creation of feudalism.

00:19:01.675 --> 00:19:03.675
The system was straightforward,

00:19:03.675 --> 00:19:05.966
leading to another social pyramid.

00:19:05.966 --> 00:19:09.341
At the bottom lay the peasants who were tied to the land

00:19:09.341 --> 00:19:12.341
and whose job was to produce crops for the empire.

00:19:12.341 --> 00:19:14.675
Then came the soldiers whose job was

00:19:14.675 --> 00:19:17.175
to protect the lands from foreign invaders.

00:19:17.175 --> 00:19:19.883
Then the lords who owned the land

00:19:19.883 --> 00:19:22.633
and taxed the peasants a portion of their crops,

00:19:22.633 --> 00:19:26.341
who in turn, the lord gave some of their crops to the king.

00:19:26.341 --> 00:19:28.675
The person in charge of the whole empire,

00:19:28.675 --> 00:19:31.091
the king would then receive more crops

00:19:31.091 --> 00:19:33.050
and become very wealthy.

00:19:33.050 --> 00:19:37.758
All profits go to the king and all work goes to the masses.

00:19:37.758 --> 00:19:39.591
Why would anyone just settle for a life

00:19:39.591 --> 00:19:41.591
of farming day in and day out?

00:19:41.591 --> 00:19:43.883
There are two reasons for this phenomenon.

00:19:43.883 --> 00:19:46.466
The first reason was due to necessity.

00:19:46.466 --> 00:19:48.800
It took many more people to feed an empire

00:19:48.800 --> 00:19:50.425
and a family back then,

00:19:50.425 --> 00:19:53.341
and the second reason being philosophy.

00:19:53.341 --> 00:19:55.341
Towards the end of the Zhou Dynasty,

00:19:55.341 --> 00:19:58.550
the beginning of Eastern philosophy was created.

00:19:58.550 --> 00:20:01.341
Confucius created a philosophy system

00:20:01.341 --> 00:20:03.466
justly named Confucianism,

00:20:03.466 --> 00:20:06.008
which is focused on the importance of respect,

00:20:06.008 --> 00:20:10.425
loyalty, and responsibility in all relationships in life.

00:20:10.425 --> 00:20:14.300
A central concept of Confucianism is called Li,

00:20:14.300 --> 00:20:18.841
which can be translated as rituals, customs, or manners.

00:20:18.841 --> 00:20:20.550
Li refers to the formal

00:20:20.550 --> 00:20:22.550
and informal social conventions

00:20:22.550 --> 00:20:24.716
that guide societal behavior.

00:20:24.716 --> 00:20:26.466
It is seen as maintaining order

00:20:26.466 --> 00:20:28.966
and harmony in social relationships.

00:20:28.966 --> 00:20:32.758
While Lao Tzi created another philosophy called Taoism.

00:20:32.758 --> 00:20:36.300
The word Tao means the way or the path,

00:20:36.300 --> 00:20:39.383
and Taoism teaches that individuals should seek

00:20:39.383 --> 00:20:42.091
to align themselves with the natural flow

00:20:42.091 --> 00:20:45.091
of the universe rather than fighting against it.

00:20:45.091 --> 00:20:48.633
Live your life as peacefully with yourself as possible,

00:20:48.633 --> 00:20:52.216
and don't worry about external things outside your control.

00:20:52.216 --> 00:20:54.300
Just focus on your farming.

00:20:54.300 --> 00:20:57.341
One of the most famous contemporaries from Taoism is

00:20:57.341 --> 00:21:01.508
the idea of yin and yang, representing complimentary

00:21:01.508 --> 00:21:03.883
and interdependent forces in nature,

00:21:03.883 --> 00:21:05.716
such as light and dark,

00:21:05.716 --> 00:21:09.300
hot and cold, or masculine and feminine.

00:21:09.300 --> 00:21:12.925
Taoism teaches that by balancing these opposing forces,

00:21:12.925 --> 00:21:16.383
individuals can achieve harmony and fulfillment.

00:21:16.383 --> 00:21:20.300
Confucianism and Taoism made life bearable

00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:22.675
for ancient Chinese farmers.

00:21:26.633 --> 00:21:29.133
But as time progressed, the city states

00:21:29.133 --> 00:21:32.008
that occupied ancient Greece grew.

00:21:32.008 --> 00:21:35.841
Around 800 BCE, the Greek city started to realize

00:21:35.841 --> 00:21:39.383
that the land they occupied was practically infertile.

00:21:39.383 --> 00:21:42.175
So to produce an essential staple of grain,

00:21:42.175 --> 00:21:43.841
they had to import it.

00:21:43.841 --> 00:21:45.466
Hence why the Greek states had

00:21:45.466 --> 00:21:47.841
to colonize the world around them.

00:21:47.841 --> 00:21:49.341
The city state Miletus,

00:21:49.341 --> 00:21:52.800
at its height, had over 90 colonies throughout Europe,

00:21:52.800 --> 00:21:54.758
producing food for the Greeks.

00:21:54.758 --> 00:21:56.883
At its height, the Greek had set up colonies

00:21:56.883 --> 00:21:58.925
from modern day Marseille in France

00:21:58.925 --> 00:22:00.883
to Rostov-on-Don in Russia.

00:22:04.633 --> 00:22:07.925
One of these new emerging city states was Rome.

00:22:07.925 --> 00:22:09.175
As legend has it,

00:22:09.175 --> 00:22:11.716
Romulus and Remus were twin brothers,

00:22:11.716 --> 00:22:15.175
abandoned by their parents and placed into the river Tibet.

00:22:15.175 --> 00:22:17.675
As the basket floated across the river,

00:22:17.675 --> 00:22:20.258
a female wolf discovered the two orphans

00:22:20.258 --> 00:22:22.133
and nursed them back to health.

00:22:22.133 --> 00:22:25.091
When Romulus and Remus became adults, they decided

00:22:25.091 --> 00:22:27.675
to find the city where the wolf rescued them.

00:22:27.675 --> 00:22:29.758
However, this created turmoil

00:22:29.758 --> 00:22:31.883
as both brothers wanted the site to be named

00:22:31.883 --> 00:22:33.508
after themselves.

00:22:33.508 --> 00:22:36.591
As Romulus and Remus fought relentlessly,

00:22:36.591 --> 00:22:39.383
eventually, Romulus came up with the final blow

00:22:39.383 --> 00:22:43.300
and killed Remus, creating Rome in 753 BC.

00:22:48.675 --> 00:22:51.550
While the Greek city states might have been colonizing,

00:22:51.550 --> 00:22:54.966
Cyrus the Great was about to take over an empire.

00:22:54.966 --> 00:22:57.508
At the time, the Persians were subjugated

00:22:57.508 --> 00:22:59.883
to the rule of the Medes empire.

00:22:59.883 --> 00:23:01.050
According to legend,

00:23:01.050 --> 00:23:03.675
after his grandson, Cyrus was born,

00:23:03.675 --> 00:23:06.841
King Astyages of Medes had a vivid dream

00:23:06.841 --> 00:23:09.258
that his little grandson would one day stage

00:23:09.258 --> 00:23:10.841
a revolt against him.

00:23:10.841 --> 00:23:13.133
King Astyages knew what to do

00:23:13.133 --> 00:23:16.341
and ordered his chief advisor to kill the baby,

00:23:16.341 --> 00:23:18.508
but the chief advisor gave the baby off

00:23:18.508 --> 00:23:21.008
to a shepherd to be raised instead.

00:23:21.008 --> 00:23:23.550
However, troubles weren't over for Cyrus.

00:23:23.550 --> 00:23:27.216
When he was 10, King Astyages found Cyrus.

00:23:27.216 --> 00:23:29.425
King Astyages wanted to kill him

00:23:29.425 --> 00:23:31.800
because the dream was very clear.

00:23:31.800 --> 00:23:34.258
This man will revolt against you.

00:23:34.258 --> 00:23:36.508
Yet against his better senses,

00:23:36.508 --> 00:23:38.508
Cyrus was allowed to live.

00:23:38.508 --> 00:23:41.258
King Astyages' biggest mistake.

00:23:41.258 --> 00:23:44.050
When Cyrus was a man, he gathered his army

00:23:44.050 --> 00:23:47.925
and revolted against his maternal grandfather, the two,

00:23:47.925 --> 00:23:52.091
but as prophecy had it, Astyages surrendered in 550 BCE.

00:23:53.258 --> 00:23:55.716
However, Cyrus wasn't done conquering.

00:23:55.716 --> 00:23:57.050
He conquered Babylon

00:23:57.050 --> 00:24:00.383
and became the supreme ruler of Mesopotamia

00:24:00.383 --> 00:24:03.550
and even the Indus Valley civilization.

00:24:03.550 --> 00:24:06.341
The world was in Cyrus's hand.

00:24:06.341 --> 00:24:08.425
Cyrus then took over the Greek colony

00:24:08.425 --> 00:24:13.383
of Ionia in Asia Minor, leading a great Persian empire,

00:24:13.383 --> 00:24:16.258
and then he died, leaving it all in the air

00:24:16.258 --> 00:24:20.008
for the next great Persian king, Darius The Great.

00:24:24.216 --> 00:24:27.216
While back in Greece, various city states started

00:24:27.216 --> 00:24:30.966
to gain power, but two were at the forefront,

00:24:30.966 --> 00:24:33.383
Sparta and Athens.

00:24:33.383 --> 00:24:36.841
Sparta was a military powerhouse.

00:24:36.841 --> 00:24:39.966
The famous Spartans believed everything should focus

00:24:39.966 --> 00:24:42.383
on physical strength and war.

00:24:42.383 --> 00:24:44.675
When a new young Spartan was born,

00:24:44.675 --> 00:24:47.550
it would be slaughtered if it didn't look healthy.

00:24:47.550 --> 00:24:50.508
Boys were taken from their families at a young age

00:24:50.508 --> 00:24:52.841
and were trained to become soldiers.

00:24:52.841 --> 00:24:55.675
The brutal training included physical conditioning,

00:24:55.675 --> 00:24:59.133
weapons training, and harsh living conditions.

00:24:59.133 --> 00:25:02.550
The entire life of a Spartan was to win a war.

00:25:02.550 --> 00:25:06.008
Their society reflected with three main groups.

00:25:06.008 --> 00:25:08.675
The ruling class consisted of aristocrats

00:25:08.675 --> 00:25:12.383
who held political power, the free non-citizens

00:25:12.383 --> 00:25:14.591
who were not allowed to participate in government,

00:25:14.591 --> 00:25:17.466
but were still expected to serve in the military.

00:25:17.466 --> 00:25:20.300
And the helots, a group of enslaved people

00:25:20.300 --> 00:25:22.841
that provided labor for the Spartan state.

00:25:22.841 --> 00:25:27.091
Life in Sparta was harsh, brutal, and militaristic.

00:25:30.675 --> 00:25:32.841
While their neighbors up north were experimenting

00:25:32.841 --> 00:25:34.966
with this idea of democracy,

00:25:34.966 --> 00:25:39.008
Athenian democracy was a highly complicated mess.

00:25:39.008 --> 00:25:40.216
There were two branches,

00:25:40.216 --> 00:25:43.008
the Council of Five Hundred and the Assembly.

00:25:43.008 --> 00:25:45.508
The Council of Five Hundred was selected randomly

00:25:45.508 --> 00:25:47.966
by a process known as sortition.

00:25:47.966 --> 00:25:51.383
Athens itself was made up of 10 different tribes.

00:25:51.383 --> 00:25:54.883
Each tribe was responsible for providing 50 citizens

00:25:54.883 --> 00:25:56.425
to serve for one year

00:25:56.425 --> 00:25:59.841
in the Council of Five Hundred via random selection.

00:25:59.841 --> 00:26:03.508
Each eligible citizen would be given a personalized token.

00:26:03.508 --> 00:26:05.091
Those tokens were inserted

00:26:05.091 --> 00:26:08.425
into a particular machine called the Kleroterion.

00:26:08.425 --> 00:26:12.383
This long lost technology included tubes and balls,

00:26:12.383 --> 00:26:16.341
which somehow selected 50 residents of each tribe

00:26:16.341 --> 00:26:19.341
to join the illustrious Council of Five Hundred.

00:26:19.341 --> 00:26:23.008
While in the assembly, there was a system in place that said

00:26:23.008 --> 00:26:25.591
that every single citizen had a vote.

00:26:25.591 --> 00:26:28.175
Of course, to be a citizen, you had to be a male

00:26:28.175 --> 00:26:31.008
and not a slave, and either born in Athens

00:26:31.008 --> 00:26:32.966
or to Athenian parents.

00:26:32.966 --> 00:26:35.466
The Council of Five Hundred would create the agenda

00:26:35.466 --> 00:26:37.300
for the main assembly to vote on

00:26:37.300 --> 00:26:40.050
because over 30,000 people could have a vote

00:26:40.050 --> 00:26:41.675
at any given time.

00:26:41.675 --> 00:26:43.675
It was total chaos.

00:26:43.675 --> 00:26:45.091
So to quell this,

00:26:45.091 --> 00:26:48.300
the council would nominate nine presidents the morning

00:26:48.300 --> 00:26:51.925
of the meeting, and it was their job to ensure all the rules

00:26:51.925 --> 00:26:53.966
and procedures were being followed.

00:26:53.966 --> 00:26:57.133
Since they were appointed right before the assembly met,

00:26:57.133 --> 00:26:59.633
they were almost impossible to bribe.

00:26:59.633 --> 00:27:02.258
Somehow the assembly would loudly vote

00:27:02.258 --> 00:27:04.175
on whether a bill would pass.

00:27:04.175 --> 00:27:06.841
They would vote on matters like appointing generals,

00:27:06.841 --> 00:27:09.758
various laws, and other government bureaucracy.

00:27:09.758 --> 00:27:13.133
However, not everyone liked this Athenian democracy.

00:27:13.133 --> 00:27:15.716
The famous Greek philosopher Plato thought

00:27:15.716 --> 00:27:17.550
the idea was barbaric.

00:27:17.550 --> 00:27:20.341
In book six of his seminal book, "The Republic,"

00:27:20.341 --> 00:27:24.175
Plato writes, "the true navigator must study the seasons

00:27:24.175 --> 00:27:27.383
of the year, the sky, the stars, the winds,

00:27:27.383 --> 00:27:30.716
and all the other subjects appropriate to his profession,

00:27:30.716 --> 00:27:33.508
if he is really fit to control the ship."

00:27:33.508 --> 00:27:35.091
Think that it's quite impossible

00:27:35.091 --> 00:27:38.966
to acquire the professional skill needed for such control,

00:27:38.966 --> 00:27:42.591
and that there's no such thing as the art of navigation.

00:27:42.591 --> 00:27:45.258
How much could a randomly selected member

00:27:45.258 --> 00:27:48.258
of the Council of Five Hundred really know?

00:27:48.258 --> 00:27:51.258
How much could he fully contribute to society?

00:27:51.258 --> 00:27:53.883
Should we allow a random member of society

00:27:53.883 --> 00:27:55.466
to have any power?

00:27:55.466 --> 00:27:58.258
Instead, Plato would advocate for the idea

00:27:58.258 --> 00:28:00.133
of a philosopher king,

00:28:00.133 --> 00:28:03.591
a man who studies wisdom, logic, and reasoning.

00:28:03.591 --> 00:28:05.925
A man who dedicates his life to understanding

00:28:05.925 --> 00:28:07.341
how to be just,

00:28:07.341 --> 00:28:10.508
a man who will become the navigator of wisdom.

00:28:10.508 --> 00:28:12.050
Plato would rather say,

00:28:12.050 --> 00:28:15.841
"the society we have described can never grow into a reality

00:28:15.841 --> 00:28:17.550
or see the light of day,

00:28:17.550 --> 00:28:20.550
and there will be no end to the troubles of the states

00:28:20.550 --> 00:28:24.716
or indeed, my dear Glaucon, of humanity itself,

00:28:24.716 --> 00:28:27.841
till philosophers become rulers in this world

00:28:27.841 --> 00:28:30.925
or till those we now call kings and rulers really

00:28:30.925 --> 00:28:34.675
and truly become philosophers and political power

00:28:34.675 --> 00:28:38.216
and philosophy thus come into the same hands."

00:28:38.216 --> 00:28:40.508
There's just one issue with Plato's quote.

00:28:40.508 --> 00:28:43.133
Every leader thinks they're a philosopher king.

00:28:43.133 --> 00:28:45.633
Everyone thinks their thoughts are the best.

00:28:45.633 --> 00:28:48.925
Everyone thinks their ideas are the wisest.

00:28:48.925 --> 00:28:50.550
From Yu the great in China,

00:28:50.550 --> 00:28:52.675
to Labarnas of the Hittite Empire,

00:28:52.675 --> 00:28:57.091
to Siddhartha Gautama, of the kingdom of Magadha in India.

00:29:01.883 --> 00:29:05.716
While not so far away in the Indian Kingdom of Magadha,

00:29:05.716 --> 00:29:08.216
a spoiled prince named Siddhartha Gautama,

00:29:08.216 --> 00:29:12.508
500 BCE, lived in luxury inside a palace.

00:29:12.508 --> 00:29:13.841
Inside this palace,

00:29:13.841 --> 00:29:16.675
Siddhartha could have anything he wanted,

00:29:16.675 --> 00:29:18.883
all the jewels, all the wealth,

00:29:18.883 --> 00:29:21.716
all the finest goods thrust upon him.

00:29:21.716 --> 00:29:25.716
His world inside of the palace was a utopia on Earth.

00:29:25.716 --> 00:29:29.633
There was no want, need or desire, and it was perfect.

00:29:29.633 --> 00:29:32.341
Until he went outside his palace compound,

00:29:32.341 --> 00:29:33.925
the only place he ever knew.

00:29:33.925 --> 00:29:36.925
As he took his first steps outside of his palace,

00:29:36.925 --> 00:29:39.008
what he saw struck a chord.

00:29:39.008 --> 00:29:42.758
He saw an old man dying right on the street, in front,

00:29:42.758 --> 00:29:45.716
he realized that the human experience wasn't something

00:29:45.716 --> 00:29:47.591
that was perfect and sublime.

00:29:47.591 --> 00:29:49.675
Instead, it was death.

00:29:49.675 --> 00:29:52.841
As Gilgamesh realized many years ago,

00:29:52.841 --> 00:29:56.383
this was an inevitable part of the human experience.

00:29:56.383 --> 00:29:58.966
Siddhartha left his life of luxury behind

00:29:58.966 --> 00:30:01.966
and began a quest for knowledge and enlightenment.

00:30:01.966 --> 00:30:04.050
He studied with spiritual teachers

00:30:04.050 --> 00:30:06.091
and meditated for many years,

00:30:06.091 --> 00:30:09.216
searching for answers to life's big questions.

00:30:09.216 --> 00:30:11.925
Finally, after six years of seeking,

00:30:11.925 --> 00:30:13.716
he sat down under a fig tree

00:30:13.716 --> 00:30:17.008
and meditated until he achieved enlightenment.

00:30:17.008 --> 00:30:18.466
Enlightenment is a state

00:30:18.466 --> 00:30:22.258
of inner peace in which one has transcended the limitations

00:30:22.258 --> 00:30:24.175
of the ego and is in touch

00:30:24.175 --> 00:30:28.466
with a universal consciousness or divine essence.

00:30:28.466 --> 00:30:30.508
It isn't a fixed and permanent thing,

00:30:30.508 --> 00:30:34.383
but rather an ongoing process of growth and development.

00:30:34.383 --> 00:30:37.341
But under that fig tree, Siddhartha became known

00:30:37.341 --> 00:30:40.675
as The Buddha or The Awakened One.

00:30:40.675 --> 00:30:41.758
He would spend the rest

00:30:41.758 --> 00:30:44.341
of his life traveling the countryside,

00:30:44.341 --> 00:30:46.466
becoming close to the enlightenment.

00:30:50.300 --> 00:30:53.966
Darius was determined to follow in his father's footsteps

00:30:53.966 --> 00:30:55.591
and take over the world.

00:30:55.591 --> 00:30:59.216
After finalizing their rule over the city state of Ionia,

00:30:59.216 --> 00:31:02.383
the Persians were on a quest to take over Greece.

00:31:02.383 --> 00:31:05.550
Darius and his 20,000 men came to the city

00:31:05.550 --> 00:31:09.050
of Marathon in the year 490 BCE,

00:31:09.050 --> 00:31:13.258
a city 26.2 miles away from Athens.

00:31:13.258 --> 00:31:17.675
The Athenians were vastly outnumbered, with only 10,000 men.

00:31:17.675 --> 00:31:19.966
As the Persians were trying to regroup,

00:31:19.966 --> 00:31:22.258
the powerful Greek hoplites crushed

00:31:22.258 --> 00:31:24.383
the weaker Persian foot soldiers,

00:31:24.383 --> 00:31:25.758
by routing the wings

00:31:25.758 --> 00:31:29.050
before turning towards the center of the Persian line.

00:31:29.050 --> 00:31:31.216
The remnants of the Persian army fled

00:31:31.216 --> 00:31:33.050
to their ships and left the battle.

00:31:33.050 --> 00:31:34.383
Early historians believe

00:31:34.383 --> 00:31:38.550
the battlefield littered 6,400 Persian bodies,

00:31:38.550 --> 00:31:42.050
while the Athenians lost only 192.

00:31:42.050 --> 00:31:43.883
So the Persians retreated

00:31:43.883 --> 00:31:46.716
and an Athenian messenger named Pheidippides ran

00:31:46.716 --> 00:31:51.175
the 26.2 miles from Marathon to Athens.

00:31:52.800 --> 00:31:55.300
Exclaiming with joy, how the Athenians

00:31:55.300 --> 00:31:58.675
just beat the mighty Persian empire.

00:31:58.675 --> 00:32:02.966
All of Athens went crazy with this fantastic news,

00:32:02.966 --> 00:32:05.758
hence leading to Pheidippides' historic trek

00:32:05.758 --> 00:32:10.758
to be sketched into history as the world's first marathon.

00:32:10.841 --> 00:32:12.966
However, the Persians weren't done.

00:32:12.966 --> 00:32:14.758
Even with Darius I dying

00:32:14.758 --> 00:32:16.966
of mysterious circumstances,

00:32:16.966 --> 00:32:20.175
his son Xerxes I took over the crown

00:32:20.175 --> 00:32:23.216
and wanted to complete his grandfather's legacy.

00:32:23.216 --> 00:32:27.550
In 480 BCE, Xerxes I wanted revenge,

00:32:27.550 --> 00:32:30.008
so he brought his enormous invasion force

00:32:30.008 --> 00:32:33.383
of over 100,000 soldiers

00:32:33.383 --> 00:32:36.508
and was dead set on conquering Greece.

00:32:36.508 --> 00:32:38.633
Then at a narrow pass at Thermopylae,

00:32:38.633 --> 00:32:41.383
the Spartan King Leonidas had his force

00:32:41.383 --> 00:32:45.341
of 7,000 Spartans maintain the defense.

00:32:45.341 --> 00:32:48.800
Leonidas knew of his disadvantage and developed a bold

00:32:48.800 --> 00:32:51.508
and daring plan to defeat the Persians.

00:32:51.508 --> 00:32:54.050
Rather than waiting for the Persians to attack,

00:32:54.050 --> 00:32:55.675
Leonidas ordered his soldiers

00:32:55.675 --> 00:32:58.591
to make a surprise attack on the Persian camp,

00:32:58.591 --> 00:33:00.300
catching the Persians off guard

00:33:00.300 --> 00:33:02.216
and disrupting their formation.

00:33:02.216 --> 00:33:03.758
Despite their success,

00:33:03.758 --> 00:33:07.841
the Greek army was ultimately overwhelmed by the Persians

00:33:07.841 --> 00:33:09.466
who attacked from all sides

00:33:09.466 --> 00:33:12.341
and eventually broke through the Greek defenses.

00:33:12.341 --> 00:33:14.883
Leonidas and his soldiers fought with courage

00:33:14.883 --> 00:33:16.258
and determination.

00:33:16.258 --> 00:33:19.050
Still, they were ultimately defeated.

00:33:19.050 --> 00:33:20.966
Then came the battle of Salamis

00:33:20.966 --> 00:33:22.966
where the Greeks could change the tilt

00:33:22.966 --> 00:33:25.300
of the war in a naval battle

00:33:25.300 --> 00:33:30.300
between the 500 Persian trireme and 300 Greek trireme,

00:33:30.383 --> 00:33:32.508
it didn't look good for the Greeks.

00:33:32.508 --> 00:33:36.091
Still the great Athenian general, Themistocles,

00:33:36.091 --> 00:33:38.550
employed his plan to move the Persian fleet

00:33:38.550 --> 00:33:41.008
into the narrow straits of Salamis,

00:33:41.008 --> 00:33:43.383
and hit the enemy fleet so hard

00:33:43.383 --> 00:33:45.091
that it had nowhere to retreat.

00:33:45.966 --> 00:33:47.216
After a massive sea battle,

00:33:47.216 --> 00:33:49.633
Themistocles won Greece the victory

00:33:49.633 --> 00:33:52.216
and changed the face of the war.

00:33:52.216 --> 00:33:54.258
The Persians still had their goal,

00:33:54.258 --> 00:33:56.550
conquer the Greek city states.

00:33:56.550 --> 00:33:58.466
Xerxes had returned to Persia,

00:33:58.466 --> 00:34:01.050
leaving Persian general Mardonius in charge

00:34:01.050 --> 00:34:02.550
of the Persian force,

00:34:02.550 --> 00:34:04.966
for most of the significant battle yet,

00:34:04.966 --> 00:34:07.133
after diplomatic talks ceased,

00:34:07.133 --> 00:34:09.300
Persia knew they had to attack.

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:12.050
As the Persians sent their troops to Platea,

00:34:12.050 --> 00:34:14.341
the Greeks knew they had to work together.

00:34:14.341 --> 00:34:17.966
With 30 various Greek city states working together,

00:34:17.966 --> 00:34:22.800
they were able to fill the massive 110,000 hoplite army

00:34:22.800 --> 00:34:26.091
with the primary purpose of defeating Persia.

00:34:26.091 --> 00:34:27.841
Though that was nothing compared

00:34:27.841 --> 00:34:32.425
to the estimated 150,000 man army of Persia,

00:34:32.425 --> 00:34:35.008
the battle was fierce and intense.

00:34:35.008 --> 00:34:37.300
With both sides fighting with ferocity

00:34:37.300 --> 00:34:40.008
and determination, the Greek hoplites continued

00:34:40.008 --> 00:34:42.341
to be effective against the Persian (indistinct)

00:34:42.341 --> 00:34:43.466
and archers.

00:34:43.466 --> 00:34:46.216
The Greeks also strategically used the terrain,

00:34:46.216 --> 00:34:47.966
fighting on a slope that helped offset

00:34:47.966 --> 00:34:50.175
the Persian numerical advantage.

00:34:50.175 --> 00:34:53.133
In the end, the Greeks defeated the Persian forces

00:34:53.133 --> 00:34:55.550
and secured a decisive victory.

00:34:55.550 --> 00:34:57.716
The Persians suffered heavy losses

00:34:57.716 --> 00:35:00.300
and Mardonius was killed in the fighting.

00:35:00.300 --> 00:35:02.633
The battle of Platea marked the end

00:35:02.633 --> 00:35:07.633
of the Greco Persian wars and the Persian threat to Greece.

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:16.258
After the Persian war,

00:35:16.258 --> 00:35:18.925
life in ancient Greece was spectacular.

00:35:18.925 --> 00:35:22.841
A golden age of culture was upon us, with no longer having

00:35:22.841 --> 00:35:25.341
to face the threat of war, Athens was able

00:35:25.341 --> 00:35:29.425
to create architectural wonders such as the Parthenon.

00:35:29.425 --> 00:35:32.550
The Parthenon sits upon the Athenian Acropolis,

00:35:32.550 --> 00:35:35.550
a prominent hill overlooking the city of Athens

00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:37.675
to show its wealth and culture.

00:35:37.675 --> 00:35:39.633
No matter where you'll go in Athens,

00:35:39.633 --> 00:35:43.383
you can still see the great Parthenon, even today.

00:35:43.383 --> 00:35:45.091
Then came the theater.

00:35:45.091 --> 00:35:46.966
Around this time, the state would sponsor

00:35:46.966 --> 00:35:48.508
the most significant poets

00:35:48.508 --> 00:35:51.466
to create stories in the Athenian Festival,

00:35:51.466 --> 00:35:53.716
called the City Dionysia.

00:35:53.716 --> 00:35:56.675
A festival designed to worship the Greek God of theater

00:35:56.675 --> 00:36:00.300
and fertility, Dionysus, creating playwrights

00:36:00.300 --> 00:36:04.050
such as Sophocles, Aeschylus and Aristophanes.

00:36:07.841 --> 00:36:10.300
States were hungry for power.

00:36:10.300 --> 00:36:13.008
Athens was recruiting city states

00:36:13.008 --> 00:36:14.966
into their Delian Alliance.

00:36:14.966 --> 00:36:17.300
While Sparta was recruiting city states

00:36:17.300 --> 00:36:19.633
into their Peloponnesian Alliance,

00:36:19.633 --> 00:36:22.800
both Sparta and Athens felt like they should control

00:36:22.800 --> 00:36:24.175
the City of Korkyra.

00:36:24.175 --> 00:36:27.341
Hence, why in 434 BCE

00:36:27.341 --> 00:36:29.841
war was upon the Greek peninsula.

00:36:29.841 --> 00:36:32.966
Resulting in naval battles, such as the Battle of Sybota,

00:36:32.966 --> 00:36:34.675
and the Battle of Pylos.

00:36:34.675 --> 00:36:39.258
By 421 BCE, a short peace was negotiated.

00:36:39.258 --> 00:36:41.800
However, this peace would not last,

00:36:41.800 --> 00:36:44.591
and Athens had their eyes on Sicily.

00:36:44.591 --> 00:36:47.133
Initially, the expedition was going well.

00:36:47.133 --> 00:36:49.341
The Athenians established alliances

00:36:49.341 --> 00:36:51.383
with several Sicilian cities

00:36:51.383 --> 00:36:53.716
and won several minor skirmishes

00:36:53.716 --> 00:36:55.883
against the Sicilian forces.

00:36:55.883 --> 00:36:58.050
But soon, Alcibiades,

00:36:58.050 --> 00:37:01.883
one of the greatest naval generals in history,

00:37:01.883 --> 00:37:05.841
was recalled to Athens to face charges of sacrilege.

00:37:05.841 --> 00:37:08.966
The Athenian fleet was left without his leadership.

00:37:12.008 --> 00:37:15.300
In his absence, the expedition began to unravel.

00:37:15.300 --> 00:37:18.341
The Athenians could not take the city of Syracuse,

00:37:18.341 --> 00:37:20.091
which had fortified its defenses

00:37:20.091 --> 00:37:22.591
and was well prepared for a siege.

00:37:22.591 --> 00:37:26.383
The Sicilians were aided by reinforcements from Sparta,

00:37:26.383 --> 00:37:27.675
which saw an opportunity

00:37:27.675 --> 00:37:32.050
to strike a crippling blow against its arch rival Athens.

00:37:32.050 --> 00:37:34.591
The Athenians suffered from a lack of supplies

00:37:34.591 --> 00:37:36.341
and were plagued by disease.

00:37:36.341 --> 00:37:39.300
At the same time, the Syracusans launched a series

00:37:39.300 --> 00:37:41.633
of surprise attacks and ambushes.

00:37:41.633 --> 00:37:44.675
Finally, after months of grueling fighting,

00:37:44.675 --> 00:37:48.050
the Athenian fleet was destroyed in a decisive battle.

00:37:48.050 --> 00:37:50.175
Thousands of Athenians were killed,

00:37:50.175 --> 00:37:53.008
and many more were captured and enslaved.

00:37:53.008 --> 00:37:56.883
A decade after that, Athens fell to the Spartans.

00:37:56.883 --> 00:38:00.841
The age of legendary Greece was now over.

00:38:00.841 --> 00:38:04.716
Both Athens and Sparta were significantly weaker,

00:38:04.716 --> 00:38:08.216
never to regain the same power they once had.

00:38:08.216 --> 00:38:12.175
Leaving the world ready for a philosopher king

00:38:12.175 --> 00:38:13.508
to conquer it all.

00:38:17.883 --> 00:38:20.008
Then in the East, the mandate

00:38:20.008 --> 00:38:21.425
of heaven was up.

00:38:21.425 --> 00:38:25.050
The Zhou Dynasty, after a long 800 year rule,

00:38:25.050 --> 00:38:26.966
it was deemed by the heavens

00:38:26.966 --> 00:38:29.966
that their empire was up, which led to a period known

00:38:29.966 --> 00:38:32.966
as the warring states, 474 to 221 BCE.

00:38:35.550 --> 00:38:37.716
This resulted in Han Feizi

00:38:37.716 --> 00:38:40.841
who created a new philosophy called legalism.

00:38:40.841 --> 00:38:42.675
Followers of legalism believe

00:38:42.675 --> 00:38:44.841
that people were inherently selfish

00:38:44.841 --> 00:38:47.925
and would only act in their own self-interest,

00:38:47.925 --> 00:38:50.133
and that the only way to keep them in line was

00:38:50.133 --> 00:38:52.716
through a system of rewards and punishments

00:38:52.716 --> 00:38:55.883
that was clear and consistently enforced.

00:38:55.883 --> 00:38:58.508
This resulted in Feizi claiming that the best way

00:38:58.508 --> 00:39:00.508
to achieve social order was

00:39:00.508 --> 00:39:03.841
by establishing a powerful ruler, responsible

00:39:03.841 --> 00:39:07.466
for enforcing the law and punishing wrongdoers.

00:39:07.466 --> 00:39:10.800
He also believed the ruler should have complete control

00:39:10.800 --> 00:39:14.383
over the military, the economy, and society.

00:39:18.258 --> 00:39:21.258
While in the heart of the Oaxaca region of Mexico,

00:39:21.258 --> 00:39:24.383
the Zapotec civilization started to flourish.

00:39:24.383 --> 00:39:27.258
The capital city of Monte Alban was being built

00:39:27.258 --> 00:39:31.050
on a mountaintop, overlooking the entire Oaxaca Valley.

00:39:31.050 --> 00:39:34.383
Perched on the mountaintop overlooking the valley of Oaxaca,

00:39:34.383 --> 00:39:36.925
the city was home to a ruling elite

00:39:36.925 --> 00:39:39.550
who oversaw a hierarchical social structure

00:39:39.550 --> 00:39:43.966
that included middle class artisans and lower class farmers.

00:39:43.966 --> 00:39:46.758
The people of the Zapotec civilization were known

00:39:46.758 --> 00:39:49.508
for their innovative agricultural practices,

00:39:49.508 --> 00:39:52.050
including the cultivation of maize

00:39:52.050 --> 00:39:55.466
and other crops, which sustained their communities in times

00:39:55.466 --> 00:39:58.216
of drought and other environmental pressures.

00:39:58.216 --> 00:40:00.883
They also developed an early writing system,

00:40:00.883 --> 00:40:02.758
which used a combination of symbols

00:40:02.758 --> 00:40:05.591
and glyphs to represent words and ideas.

00:40:05.591 --> 00:40:07.925
They developed an advanced calendar system

00:40:07.925 --> 00:40:12.925
based on 260 day and 365 day solar cycles.

00:40:17.425 --> 00:40:21.091
In Greece during the year 356 BCE

00:40:21.091 --> 00:40:24.050
in the City of Pella in the kingdom of Macedon,

00:40:24.050 --> 00:40:27.800
the greatest commander in history was born,

00:40:27.800 --> 00:40:31.425
Alexander the Great, grew up knowing he would be a leader

00:40:31.425 --> 00:40:35.300
and was the son of King Philip II and Queen Olympia.

00:40:35.300 --> 00:40:38.133
But the teacher was much more impressive.

00:40:38.133 --> 00:40:42.091
Since he was a kid, Alexander was tutored by Aristotle.

00:40:42.091 --> 00:40:46.425
Aristotle is the man who is known as the father of logic.

00:40:46.425 --> 00:40:48.716
He created the fields of biology

00:40:48.716 --> 00:40:50.925
and taxonomy by introducing a way

00:40:50.925 --> 00:40:53.675
to think called the scientific method,

00:40:53.675 --> 00:40:57.675
a method that is still taught in schools to this day.

00:40:57.675 --> 00:41:00.883
He also wrote extensively about philosophy, ethics,

00:41:00.883 --> 00:41:05.425
and art, changing the face of the world as we know it today.

00:41:05.425 --> 00:41:07.341
This is the man who was in charge

00:41:07.341 --> 00:41:09.758
of teaching Alexander the Great.

00:41:09.758 --> 00:41:13.133
Alexander was 20 when his father was assassinated,

00:41:13.133 --> 00:41:15.258
but his excellent education allowed him

00:41:15.258 --> 00:41:17.925
to take over the rest of the world.

00:41:17.925 --> 00:41:21.508
After his father died in 336 BCE,

00:41:21.508 --> 00:41:25.425
Alexander was hellbent on keeping his family's power.

00:41:25.425 --> 00:41:28.508
So when the Greek City of Thebes decided to revolt,

00:41:28.508 --> 00:41:33.508
Alexander and his army marched 240 miles in 14 days.

00:41:34.425 --> 00:41:36.675
When Thebes refused to surrender,

00:41:36.675 --> 00:41:39.841
he razed the entire city to the ground,

00:41:39.841 --> 00:41:44.425
and 6,000 were killed, and the rest were sold into slavery.

00:41:44.425 --> 00:41:47.633
The rest of the Greek city states recoiled in fear,

00:41:47.633 --> 00:41:50.383
allowing Alexander to do as he pleased,

00:41:50.383 --> 00:41:52.675
leaving for his new target to be Persia

00:41:52.675 --> 00:41:55.425
and the new Persian king, Darius III.

00:41:56.675 --> 00:41:58.341
In 333 BC,

00:41:58.341 --> 00:42:02.091
Alexander faced the Persian army at the Battle Of Issus.

00:42:02.091 --> 00:42:05.008
This significant engagement saw the Persian king,

00:42:05.008 --> 00:42:08.341
Darius III defeated and forced to flee.

00:42:08.341 --> 00:42:10.966
Alexander then captured several key cities,

00:42:10.966 --> 00:42:13.091
including the vital port of Tyre,

00:42:13.091 --> 00:42:15.591
which had resisted his initial siege.

00:42:15.591 --> 00:42:17.508
In 331 BC

00:42:17.508 --> 00:42:20.341
Alexander faced Darius III again

00:42:20.341 --> 00:42:22.050
at the Battle of Gaugamela,

00:42:22.050 --> 00:42:24.633
near the Tigris River in modern day Iraq.

00:42:24.633 --> 00:42:26.675
Despite being outnumbered,

00:42:26.675 --> 00:42:29.466
Alexander won a decisive victory

00:42:29.466 --> 00:42:32.175
using superior tactics and mobility.

00:42:32.175 --> 00:42:34.425
The Persian army was shattered,

00:42:34.425 --> 00:42:37.508
and Darius III fled once again.

00:42:37.508 --> 00:42:40.716
Alexander then proceeded to capture the Persian capital

00:42:40.716 --> 00:42:44.550
of Babylon and took control of much of Mesopotamia.

00:42:44.550 --> 00:42:47.758
He continued his campaign eastward, winning battles

00:42:47.758 --> 00:42:50.925
in what is now modern day Iran and Afghanistan.

00:42:50.925 --> 00:42:54.716
In 330 BC, he captured the Persian capital

00:42:54.716 --> 00:42:57.675
of Persepolis, a city of great wealth

00:42:57.675 --> 00:42:59.841
and cultural significance.

00:42:59.841 --> 00:43:02.216
But Alexander wasn't done.

00:43:02.216 --> 00:43:04.425
He wanted to expand eastward,

00:43:04.425 --> 00:43:08.258
eventually crossing the Hindu Kush mountains into India.

00:43:08.258 --> 00:43:11.258
However, his troops grew tired of the endless fighting

00:43:11.258 --> 00:43:13.258
and refused to go any further,

00:43:13.258 --> 00:43:16.966
and Alexander was forced to turn back.

00:43:16.966 --> 00:43:20.758
However, after Alexander failed in the Indian subcontinent,

00:43:20.758 --> 00:43:23.258
a powerhouse emerged in India

00:43:23.258 --> 00:43:25.091
called the Mauryan Empire.

00:43:25.091 --> 00:43:28.633
At its height, it spanned over much of India, Pakistan,

00:43:28.633 --> 00:43:30.925
Bangladesh, and Afghanistan.

00:43:30.925 --> 00:43:33.925
However, this conquering came at much of a cost

00:43:33.925 --> 00:43:35.675
for its leader, Ashoka the Great.

00:43:35.675 --> 00:43:38.050
In 261 BC,

00:43:38.050 --> 00:43:40.716
after the death of his parents, Ashoka decided

00:43:40.716 --> 00:43:43.133
that his empire needed to expand.

00:43:43.133 --> 00:43:45.716
In his sights, the kingdom of Kalinga.

00:43:45.716 --> 00:43:49.216
The war was bloody, the war was fierce.

00:43:49.216 --> 00:43:52.133
Over a hundred thousand people died.

00:43:52.133 --> 00:43:54.508
Ashoka couldn't sleep with himself.

00:43:54.508 --> 00:43:57.091
He didn't know how to deal with his actions that resulted

00:43:57.091 --> 00:43:59.008
in so much death,

00:43:59.008 --> 00:44:01.591
so he turned to the teaching of the Buddha.

00:44:01.591 --> 00:44:05.091
Under Ashoka's rule, the Mauryan Empire became known

00:44:05.091 --> 00:44:08.883
for supporting Buddhist teachings and promoting nonviolence.

00:44:08.883 --> 00:44:12.466
Ashoka issued a series of edicts inscribed on rocks

00:44:12.466 --> 00:44:14.425
and pillars throughout the empire

00:44:14.425 --> 00:44:17.508
that promoted principles such as kindness, respect

00:44:17.508 --> 00:44:21.383
for all religions and the abolition of slavery.

00:44:21.383 --> 00:44:25.675
Certain traits were not shared in the West by Alexander.

00:44:30.883 --> 00:44:34.675
In the West, it was deemed honorable to die in combat,

00:44:34.675 --> 00:44:37.425
and a hero's death would be remembered forever.

00:44:37.425 --> 00:44:39.633
A farmer will die in anonymity.

00:44:39.633 --> 00:44:41.758
Alexander died a few years later

00:44:41.758 --> 00:44:44.341
in Babylon at the age of 32.

00:44:44.341 --> 00:44:45.883
Throughout his expedition,

00:44:45.883 --> 00:44:48.508
Alexander was spreading Greek ideas founded

00:44:48.508 --> 00:44:51.758
by his once wise teacher, bringing the rise

00:44:51.758 --> 00:44:55.341
of Greek ideals across the land, starting the seeds

00:44:55.341 --> 00:44:57.716
of the Western cultures we see today.

00:44:57.716 --> 00:44:59.258
Once Alexander died,

00:44:59.258 --> 00:45:02.300
his empire just could not sustain itself.

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:05.050
His generals feuded as to who should be the leader

00:45:05.050 --> 00:45:06.925
of this great empire.

00:45:06.925 --> 00:45:08.675
Everyone wanted power,

00:45:08.675 --> 00:45:11.841
yet in fighting left to waste in oblivion.

00:45:11.841 --> 00:45:16.216
Eventually, in 323 BC after senseless wars,

00:45:16.216 --> 00:45:18.091
the Greek generals divided the world

00:45:18.091 --> 00:45:20.425
into three major empires.

00:45:20.425 --> 00:45:23.633
The Ptolemies in Egypt, the Seleucids in the east

00:45:23.633 --> 00:45:26.216
and the Antigonids in Greece.

00:45:28.300 --> 00:45:31.841
Ptolemy, one of Alexander's generals led Egypt

00:45:31.841 --> 00:45:33.925
into a period of prosperity.

00:45:33.925 --> 00:45:36.175
Inspiration by his former leader,

00:45:36.175 --> 00:45:39.550
Ptolemy built the library of Alexandria,

00:45:39.550 --> 00:45:42.633
a hub for an intellectual scholarship.

00:45:42.633 --> 00:45:45.383
Intellectuals from all over will come to the library

00:45:45.383 --> 00:45:46.758
to exchange ideas

00:45:46.758 --> 00:45:49.091
and thoughts throughout the world, leaving us

00:45:49.091 --> 00:45:51.383
to have great philosophers like Plato

00:45:51.383 --> 00:45:55.300
and Aristotle to be the backbone of our culture.

00:45:55.300 --> 00:45:58.591
While the general Seleucid was given the keys to the city

00:45:58.591 --> 00:46:02.425
of Babylon, Babylon at this time was a cultural hub,

00:46:02.425 --> 00:46:06.883
melting Greek, Persian, Indian and central Asian cultures.

00:46:06.883 --> 00:46:10.966
Seleucid though preferred Greek ideas and Greek language.

00:46:10.966 --> 00:46:12.925
The Seleucid Empire was at its height,

00:46:12.925 --> 00:46:16.133
during the reign of King Antiochus III

00:46:16.133 --> 00:46:18.925
223 BC to 187 BC.

00:46:18.925 --> 00:46:21.133
Under King Antiochus III,

00:46:21.133 --> 00:46:23.633
the Seleucids encompassed a vast territory

00:46:23.633 --> 00:46:27.300
from modern day Turkey to modern day Pakistan,

00:46:27.300 --> 00:46:30.300
one of the largest empires on record

00:46:30.300 --> 00:46:32.466
until the rise of the Romans.

00:46:33.591 --> 00:46:37.758
While the Antigonids did not have nearly as much success.

00:46:37.758 --> 00:46:40.383
By the time Antigonus I took power,

00:46:40.383 --> 00:46:43.341
the Greeks were just a shell of what they once were.

00:46:43.341 --> 00:46:45.925
The age of the Greeks was behind us,

00:46:45.925 --> 00:46:49.050
the Ptolemies, the Seleucids and the Antigonids

00:46:49.050 --> 00:46:52.300
went astray from the Roman Empire.

00:46:52.300 --> 00:46:54.716
However, for Rome to rise,

00:46:54.716 --> 00:46:58.341
it had to face a powerful foe, Carthage.

00:46:58.341 --> 00:47:02.508
Both Rome and Carthage had a desire for the same city state,

00:47:02.508 --> 00:47:05.300
Messina on the island of Sicily.

00:47:05.300 --> 00:47:08.258
This would give either civilization a foothold

00:47:08.258 --> 00:47:10.591
to grab power in the Mediterranean.

00:47:10.591 --> 00:47:13.841
The first Punic war was upon us, and

00:47:13.841 --> 00:47:18.841
after 20 years of fighting in the year 241, BCE,

00:47:18.841 --> 00:47:20.716
and the defeat of Carthage,

00:47:20.716 --> 00:47:23.466
the Treaty of Lutatius was signed.

00:47:23.466 --> 00:47:25.800
The peace though was shortlived.

00:47:25.800 --> 00:47:30.383
In 218, BCE, the second Punic Wars began

00:47:30.383 --> 00:47:33.716
when the Carthagian General Hannibal invaded Italy

00:47:33.716 --> 00:47:37.466
with his army, including elephants to conquer Rome.

00:47:37.466 --> 00:47:39.925
Hannibal won several early battles,

00:47:39.925 --> 00:47:43.591
including the Battle of Cannae in 216, BCE.

00:47:43.591 --> 00:47:46.300
Still, he was ultimately defeated

00:47:46.300 --> 00:47:49.258
by the Roman general Scipio Africanus,

00:47:49.258 --> 00:47:53.008
at the Battle of Zama in 202 BCE.

00:47:53.008 --> 00:47:57.091
The war resulted in the complete defeat of Carthage,

00:47:57.091 --> 00:48:00.133
which was forced to cede its territories to Rome

00:48:00.133 --> 00:48:02.883
and the end of the Carthaginian Empire.

00:48:02.883 --> 00:48:06.341
There was no doubt in the world anymore that it was time

00:48:06.341 --> 00:48:09.091
for the Romans to take charge in the West.

00:48:12.966 --> 00:48:14.841
While in the East, after the end

00:48:14.841 --> 00:48:16.883
of the warring states period.

00:48:16.883 --> 00:48:20.925
Qin Shi Huang and the Qin Dynasty were an absolute power.

00:48:20.925 --> 00:48:25.925
221 BCE to 206 BCE, Qin was determined

00:48:25.925 --> 00:48:30.425
to turn diverse China into a unified Chinese empire.

00:48:30.425 --> 00:48:34.633
He divided the lands into 36 command areas supervised

00:48:34.633 --> 00:48:39.050
by a governor, military commander, and imperial inspector.

00:48:39.050 --> 00:48:42.091
It was expected that you followed the will of Qin

00:48:42.091 --> 00:48:45.966
or else you would face harsh penalties, the basic ideas

00:48:45.966 --> 00:48:50.383
of legalism in action, strong government, harsh laws,

00:48:50.383 --> 00:48:51.591
and inheriting knowing

00:48:51.591 --> 00:48:54.591
that humans were necessarily selfish.

00:48:54.591 --> 00:48:58.341
However, their mandate from heaven ran quite quickly.

00:48:58.341 --> 00:49:02.008
After Qin Shi Huang's death, China was in turmoil

00:49:02.008 --> 00:49:04.050
with another dynasty on foot.

00:49:05.091 --> 00:49:09.508
Liu Bang, leader from 206 to 195 BCE,

00:49:09.508 --> 00:49:11.966
after leading a revolt against the Qin

00:49:11.966 --> 00:49:15.300
was declared emperor of the New Han dynasty.

00:49:15.300 --> 00:49:18.175
Instead of following the strict legalistic mindset

00:49:18.175 --> 00:49:21.175
of the Qin, Liu decided to set his empire

00:49:21.175 --> 00:49:23.633
as a Confucianist paradise.

00:49:23.633 --> 00:49:27.675
The ideals of moderation, virtue and piety as set

00:49:27.675 --> 00:49:31.341
through Confucianism were marched throughout the empire,

00:49:31.341 --> 00:49:34.591
weaving the cocoon of a powerful dynasty.

00:49:34.591 --> 00:49:36.466
During the Han Dynasty, the production

00:49:36.466 --> 00:49:38.675
of silk was ever increasing,

00:49:38.675 --> 00:49:42.175
and the idea of profits was in the minds of all.

00:49:42.175 --> 00:49:44.758
So in 138, BCE,

00:49:44.758 --> 00:49:48.925
Emperor Han Wu sent an imperial convoy to make contact

00:49:48.925 --> 00:49:52.425
with cultures of Central Asia and the Mediterranean.

00:49:52.425 --> 00:49:55.466
Then after the routes were established, Chinese merchants

00:49:55.466 --> 00:49:58.341
and traders would bring their silk across the Silk Road

00:49:58.341 --> 00:50:00.925
to the Middle East and eventually Europe,

00:50:00.925 --> 00:50:03.591
where it would be sold at high profits.

00:50:03.591 --> 00:50:06.716
Though in the beginning, the route was relatively short

00:50:06.716 --> 00:50:11.091
because in 97 BC Ambassador Gan Ying was

00:50:11.091 --> 00:50:14.341
sent to Rome with gifts of silk for their empire.

00:50:14.341 --> 00:50:17.466
However, Gan only got as far as Mesopotamia

00:50:17.466 --> 00:50:19.841
because he was told by the Parthians,

00:50:19.841 --> 00:50:22.341
the dominant empire in Iran at the time

00:50:22.341 --> 00:50:24.716
that the journey would take years.

00:50:24.716 --> 00:50:27.841
Little did Gan know that he was misinformed,

00:50:27.841 --> 00:50:30.758
that the journey would've been relatively shorter,

00:50:30.758 --> 00:50:31.925
but the Parthians wanted

00:50:31.925 --> 00:50:34.133
to keep their spot as the middlemen.

00:50:34.133 --> 00:50:35.508
They did not want China

00:50:35.508 --> 00:50:39.508
and Rome to have contact with one another, creating a system

00:50:39.508 --> 00:50:43.341
of three empires smooshed right up against each other,

00:50:43.341 --> 00:50:46.175
Rome in the west, Parthians in the center,

00:50:46.175 --> 00:50:48.133
and China in the east.

00:50:52.133 --> 00:50:56.508
Then in 86, BCE, Greece already being weakened

00:50:56.508 --> 00:51:00.175
by the conquest of Alexander The Great was now the target

00:51:00.175 --> 00:51:02.091
of the Roman Empire.

00:51:02.091 --> 00:51:05.216
General Lucius Cornelius Sulla led an army

00:51:05.216 --> 00:51:07.925
of legions to the forefront of Athens.

00:51:07.925 --> 00:51:10.925
He besieged Athens for several months,

00:51:10.925 --> 00:51:13.633
brutally torturing the citizens within.

00:51:13.633 --> 00:51:16.633
Eventually when Athens fell, he ordered his soldiers

00:51:16.633 --> 00:51:18.508
to loot and pillage the city,

00:51:18.508 --> 00:51:22.050
destroying many important cultural treasures.

00:51:22.050 --> 00:51:25.383
This takeover cemented Rome as a superpower.

00:51:25.383 --> 00:51:29.425
Athens no longer had the power, but rather it was in Rome.

00:51:30.300 --> 00:51:34.300
While in 63, BCE, General Pompey was tasked

00:51:34.300 --> 00:51:36.091
with capturing Jerusalem

00:51:36.091 --> 00:51:37.716
and the region of Galilee.

00:51:37.716 --> 00:51:40.466
The Romans quickly captured the cities,

00:51:40.466 --> 00:51:43.466
forcing Galilee to be placed under Roman rule,

00:51:43.466 --> 00:51:46.550
including a small village called Nazareth.

00:51:47.925 --> 00:51:51.508
The Romans desire to expand didn't end in Galilee though.

00:51:51.508 --> 00:51:55.758
In 58, BCE, Julius Caesar was appointed governor

00:51:55.758 --> 00:51:58.550
of the Roman provide of Cisalpine Gaul,

00:51:58.550 --> 00:52:01.008
Northern Italy, with the express assignment

00:52:01.008 --> 00:52:03.466
of conquering the rest of the Gauls.

00:52:03.466 --> 00:52:06.675
At the time, the Gauls were a group of Celtic peoples

00:52:06.675 --> 00:52:09.966
who lived in that area that is now France, Belgium,

00:52:09.966 --> 00:52:13.050
and parts of Switzerland, Germany, and Italy.

00:52:13.050 --> 00:52:15.133
However, it was Caesar's job

00:52:15.133 --> 00:52:18.341
to take over these Celtic tribes, while the Gauls

00:52:18.341 --> 00:52:21.300
who were insistent on their independence all had

00:52:21.300 --> 00:52:24.716
to work together under the leadership of Vercingetorix,

00:52:24.716 --> 00:52:27.591
in a last ditch attempt to stop the Romans.

00:52:27.591 --> 00:52:31.591
As Caesar brought his troops to Alesia in 52 BC,

00:52:31.591 --> 00:52:33.300
war was upon us.

00:52:33.300 --> 00:52:35.925
Alesia was surrounded by a double wall

00:52:35.925 --> 00:52:38.550
and a ditch with additional fortifications

00:52:38.550 --> 00:52:40.050
on the town's heels,

00:52:40.050 --> 00:52:42.716
Vercingetorix had gathered a large force

00:52:42.716 --> 00:52:45.216
of Gallic warriors inside the town.

00:52:45.216 --> 00:52:47.383
In contrast, Caesar had assembled

00:52:47.383 --> 00:52:50.800
a sizable Roman army outside the walls.

00:52:50.800 --> 00:52:53.216
Caesar realized that a direct assault

00:52:53.216 --> 00:52:55.133
on the town would be complex,

00:52:55.133 --> 00:52:57.133
so he surrounded the Gallic forces

00:52:57.133 --> 00:52:59.175
and starved them into submission.

00:52:59.175 --> 00:53:02.133
He ordered the construction of a series of fortifications

00:53:02.133 --> 00:53:06.091
around Alesia, including a circumvallation wall

00:53:06.091 --> 00:53:08.966
that encircled the town and a second wall,

00:53:08.966 --> 00:53:10.550
and ditch that faced outward

00:53:10.550 --> 00:53:13.258
to defend against any attempts to break out.

00:53:13.258 --> 00:53:14.633
Over several weeks,

00:53:14.633 --> 00:53:18.758
Caesar's forces engaged in a grueling Siege of Alesia

00:53:18.758 --> 00:53:21.591
with both sides suffering heavy losses.

00:53:21.591 --> 00:53:24.716
The Gallic warriors inside the town made several attempts

00:53:24.716 --> 00:53:28.258
to break out, but they were repelled by the Roman forces.

00:53:28.258 --> 00:53:31.341
The tide of the battle turned in favor of the Romans.

00:53:31.341 --> 00:53:33.216
When a second gallic army,

00:53:33.216 --> 00:53:36.175
led by Vercingetorix's ally Commius,

00:53:36.175 --> 00:53:38.425
attempted to relieve the siege.

00:53:38.425 --> 00:53:40.633
Caesar sent a detachment of his forces

00:53:40.633 --> 00:53:43.341
to intercept the gallic reinforcements.

00:53:43.341 --> 00:53:44.841
After a fierce battle,

00:53:44.841 --> 00:53:47.758
the Roman soldiers emerged victorious.

00:53:47.758 --> 00:53:50.883
With his forces surrounded and facing starvation,

00:53:50.883 --> 00:53:53.383
Vercingetorix was forced to surrender.

00:53:53.383 --> 00:53:54.883
He emerged from Alesia

00:53:54.883 --> 00:53:57.508
and offered himself as a prisoner to Caesar,

00:53:57.508 --> 00:54:01.425
effectively ending the Gallic resistance to Roman rule.

00:54:01.425 --> 00:54:03.008
Throughout the next two years,

00:54:03.008 --> 00:54:05.841
Caesar crossed the Gallic empire conquering

00:54:05.841 --> 00:54:07.925
and implementing it into Rome.

00:54:07.925 --> 00:54:10.258
The Gauls were implemented into Rome,

00:54:10.258 --> 00:54:13.466
even gaining citizenship within the empire.

00:54:17.883 --> 00:54:20.966
However, the Senate was not happy with Caesar.

00:54:20.966 --> 00:54:23.716
Even though he had great success against the Galls,

00:54:23.716 --> 00:54:26.008
the Roman Senate wanted him to stop.

00:54:26.008 --> 00:54:28.883
They did not like the popularity Caesar was gaining,

00:54:28.883 --> 00:54:30.966
nor the power he was controlling.

00:54:30.966 --> 00:54:34.508
So the Roman Senate called upon Caesar to resign his command

00:54:34.508 --> 00:54:36.050
and disband his army,

00:54:36.050 --> 00:54:39.216
or risk being declared an enemy of the state.

00:54:39.216 --> 00:54:42.425
This led Caesar to an essential choice to make.

00:54:42.425 --> 00:54:45.341
Will he either follow the wheel of the Roman Senate

00:54:45.341 --> 00:54:48.591
or ignore them and start a bloody civil war?

00:54:48.591 --> 00:54:51.633
Roman law at the time prohibited any general

00:54:51.633 --> 00:54:53.675
from crossing the Rubicon River

00:54:53.675 --> 00:54:56.425
and entering mainland Italy with a standing army,

00:54:56.425 --> 00:54:59.758
without the expressed permission of the Roman Senate.

00:54:59.758 --> 00:55:02.091
To do so would be treason,

00:55:02.091 --> 00:55:05.341
and this tiny stream would reveal Caesar's intentions

00:55:05.341 --> 00:55:07.466
and mark the point of no return.

00:55:07.466 --> 00:55:09.716
Civil war was imminent as Caesar

00:55:09.716 --> 00:55:12.008
and his army marched over the Rubicon.

00:55:12.008 --> 00:55:15.425
Battles in Corfinium and Pharsalus showed the Senate

00:55:15.425 --> 00:55:17.591
that Caesar was a worthy foe.

00:55:17.591 --> 00:55:22.050
So the Roman Senate appointed his son-in-law, Gnaeus Pompey,

00:55:22.050 --> 00:55:25.383
to lead the Roman forces against his father-in-law.

00:55:25.383 --> 00:55:27.841
Both parties knew the importance of Spain,

00:55:27.841 --> 00:55:29.216
due to it providing a link

00:55:29.216 --> 00:55:31.466
between Italy and the rest of Europe.

00:55:31.466 --> 00:55:33.383
The two armies clashed near the town

00:55:33.383 --> 00:55:35.758
of Ilerda in Northeastern Spain.

00:55:35.758 --> 00:55:38.966
Caesar's army was significantly outnumbered,

00:55:38.966 --> 00:55:42.466
but he could use his superior military tactics and training

00:55:42.466 --> 00:55:44.675
to gain the upper hand in the battle.

00:55:44.675 --> 00:55:47.466
After several days of intense fighting,

00:55:47.466 --> 00:55:49.800
Caesar emerged victorious,

00:55:49.800 --> 00:55:52.508
forcing Pompey's forces to retreat,

00:55:52.508 --> 00:55:55.925
declaring Caesar as the new leader of Rome.

00:55:55.925 --> 00:55:57.800
When Caesar made it back to Rome,

00:55:57.800 --> 00:56:01.341
the crowds were chanting hail Caesar, hail Caesar.

00:56:01.341 --> 00:56:02.716
The people then decided

00:56:02.716 --> 00:56:06.466
that he would be the dictator of Rome for life.

00:56:06.466 --> 00:56:09.508
Caesar immediately set to work, implementing a series

00:56:09.508 --> 00:56:11.550
of reforms and policies aimed

00:56:11.550 --> 00:56:14.091
at improving ordinary Roman's lives

00:56:14.091 --> 00:56:16.758
and strengthening the central government's power.

00:56:16.758 --> 00:56:17.841
He ordered the construction

00:56:17.841 --> 00:56:20.591
of new infrastructure such as roads, bridges,

00:56:20.591 --> 00:56:23.341
and aqueducts, which helped to connect different parts

00:56:23.341 --> 00:56:26.216
of the city and improve trade and commerce.

00:56:26.216 --> 00:56:28.800
Caesar also enacted a series of political

00:56:28.800 --> 00:56:32.633
and social reforms, including granting citizenship

00:56:32.633 --> 00:56:35.341
to many people living in the Roman Empire

00:56:35.341 --> 00:56:37.050
and creating new laws

00:56:37.050 --> 00:56:40.216
and customs that were based on Roman practices.

00:56:40.216 --> 00:56:42.758
He encouraged the spread of the Latin language

00:56:42.758 --> 00:56:44.758
and culture throughout the city

00:56:44.758 --> 00:56:47.300
and established the Julian calendar,

00:56:47.300 --> 00:56:50.758
which is the basis of the calendar we use today.

00:56:50.758 --> 00:56:53.425
However, Caesar's reign was short-lived

00:56:53.425 --> 00:56:57.966
because two years later in 44 BC, he was stabbed

00:56:57.966 --> 00:57:02.966
to death by two loyal senators, Cassius and Brutus.

00:57:03.091 --> 00:57:06.133
The assassination of Caesar led the Roman world

00:57:06.133 --> 00:57:07.341
into disarray.

00:57:07.341 --> 00:57:09.758
The world was filled with factions,

00:57:09.758 --> 00:57:13.133
vying for government control without a strong leader.

00:57:15.091 --> 00:57:18.383
Octavian, Caesar's son, who was 18 then,

00:57:18.383 --> 00:57:20.425
came to Rome to claim his inheritance

00:57:20.425 --> 00:57:22.883
and assert his place in the political landscape.

00:57:22.883 --> 00:57:24.341
He quickly aligned himself

00:57:24.341 --> 00:57:27.091
with Caesar's loyal Lieutenant Mark Antony.

00:57:27.091 --> 00:57:29.841
Together, they defeated Caesar's assassins

00:57:29.841 --> 00:57:33.383
at the Battle of Philippe in 42, BCE.

00:57:33.383 --> 00:57:36.508
However, tension soon arose between Octavian

00:57:36.508 --> 00:57:39.300
and Antony as both men vied for control

00:57:39.300 --> 00:57:40.675
of the Roman empire.

00:57:40.675 --> 00:57:43.800
In 31 BCE, their forces clashed

00:57:43.800 --> 00:57:45.758
in the naval battle of Actium,

00:57:45.758 --> 00:57:49.425
which resulted in Octavian emerging as the clear victor.

00:57:49.425 --> 00:57:52.675
Antony fled to Egypt with his lover Cleopatra

00:57:52.675 --> 00:57:55.508
and the two committed suicide the following year.

00:57:55.508 --> 00:57:57.008
With Antony's defeat,

00:57:57.008 --> 00:58:00.925
Octavian emerged as the undisputed ruler of Rome.

00:58:00.925 --> 00:58:04.800
In 27, BCE, he was appointed Augustus

00:58:04.800 --> 00:58:08.008
and became the first Roman emperor.

00:58:13.258 --> 00:58:15.300
During Augustus's reign, a man

00:58:15.300 --> 00:58:17.175
who would change the world was born

00:58:17.175 --> 00:58:21.300
in the Roman occupied city of Bethlehem, Jesus Christ.

00:58:21.300 --> 00:58:22.800
The gospel of Luke says,

00:58:22.800 --> 00:58:25.883
"in those days, a decree went out from Caesar Augustus

00:58:25.883 --> 00:58:28.341
that all the world should be registered.

00:58:28.341 --> 00:58:31.675
This was the first registration when Quirinius was governor

00:58:31.675 --> 00:58:34.508
of Syria and all went to be registered,

00:58:34.508 --> 00:58:36.175
each to his own town."

00:58:36.175 --> 00:58:38.091
Luke two, one through three.

00:58:38.091 --> 00:58:41.841
This census was an essential factor in Roman society

00:58:41.841 --> 00:58:44.216
because it established the population counts

00:58:44.216 --> 00:58:46.675
in these various communities making it possible

00:58:46.675 --> 00:58:48.925
to tax these various citizens.

00:58:48.925 --> 00:58:50.633
So the highly pregnant Mary

00:58:50.633 --> 00:58:53.091
and her betrothed husband, Joseph had

00:58:53.091 --> 00:58:57.925
to travel 90 miles on foot from Nazareth to Bethlehem

00:58:57.925 --> 00:59:01.425
to complete this legally required Roman census.

00:59:01.425 --> 00:59:03.133
When they arrived in Bethlehem,

00:59:03.133 --> 00:59:05.675
many other descendants of the king of David

00:59:05.675 --> 00:59:08.841
or members of the Jewish faith were also going

00:59:08.841 --> 00:59:10.800
to Bethlehem for the census.

00:59:10.800 --> 00:59:13.591
They found out that there was no room for them in the inn,

00:59:13.591 --> 00:59:16.008
so they were forced to take shelter in a stable

00:59:16.008 --> 00:59:18.383
where Mary gave birth to Jesus.

00:59:18.383 --> 00:59:21.341
Jesus was later named King of the Jews.

00:59:21.341 --> 00:59:24.841
After Jesus' birthday and the completion of the census,

00:59:24.841 --> 00:59:27.175
Mary and Joseph returned to Nazareth

00:59:27.175 --> 00:59:29.341
with their extraordinary son.

00:59:29.341 --> 00:59:33.425
As the years of Jesus went on, stories about him grew.

00:59:33.425 --> 00:59:35.258
More and more followers began

00:59:35.258 --> 00:59:37.800
to worship Jesus as their Messiah.

00:59:37.800 --> 00:59:40.716
They claim that he can catch an endless amount of fish.

00:59:40.716 --> 00:59:43.008
They claim that he can cure the blind,

00:59:43.008 --> 00:59:45.966
and they claim that he was the son of God.

00:59:45.966 --> 00:59:49.091
So these followers, specifically his disciples,

00:59:49.091 --> 00:59:51.925
started to write down his entire life journey.

00:59:51.925 --> 00:59:55.425
Four of his closest disciples, Matthew, Mark, Luke,

00:59:55.425 --> 00:59:57.925
and John, wrote down the main chunks

00:59:57.925 --> 01:00:01.133
of the book in these parts called gospels.

01:00:01.133 --> 01:00:04.800
Each of these gospels covered almost all of the same events,

01:00:04.800 --> 01:00:07.133
the narrative life of Jesus Christ.

01:00:07.133 --> 01:00:08.716
This narrative testimony

01:00:08.716 --> 01:00:13.175
of a child born in a stable changed the world forever.

01:00:15.300 --> 01:00:19.883
Even though many loved Jesus, some viewed him as a threat.

01:00:19.883 --> 01:00:22.258
Emperor Tiberius succeeded Augustus

01:00:22.258 --> 01:00:26.216
and reigned from 14 AD to 37 AD.

01:00:26.216 --> 01:00:29.675
Tiberius was notorious for his delators,

01:00:29.675 --> 01:00:32.341
a network of informants rewarded for spying

01:00:32.341 --> 01:00:35.675
and reporting on suspected traitors and criminals.

01:00:35.675 --> 01:00:38.091
Criminals reported on by the delators had

01:00:38.091 --> 01:00:42.508
to face a treason trial, often resulting in executions

01:00:42.508 --> 01:00:44.550
or forced suicides.

01:00:44.550 --> 01:00:46.883
His prefect of Judea at the time,

01:00:46.883 --> 01:00:49.300
Pontius Pilate was no stranger

01:00:49.300 --> 01:00:51.591
to the harsh punishment of traitors.

01:00:51.591 --> 01:00:53.758
As Jesus was influencing more

01:00:53.758 --> 01:00:57.091
and more people, he became more of a political threat.

01:00:57.091 --> 01:01:00.508
So following the guidelines of Emperor Tiberius,

01:01:00.508 --> 01:01:03.550
Pilate was given no practical political choice

01:01:03.550 --> 01:01:07.258
other than to execute Jesus on a cross.

01:01:07.258 --> 01:01:09.300
Roman law was evident then.

01:01:09.300 --> 01:01:11.550
One must follow the emperor's will,

01:01:11.550 --> 01:01:13.258
or else they will perish.

01:01:13.258 --> 01:01:16.050
As Jesus was crucified on the cross,

01:01:16.050 --> 01:01:20.133
a new religion was born, Christianity.

01:01:20.133 --> 01:01:22.466
In the beginning, Christianity was

01:01:22.466 --> 01:01:24.591
just a small sect of Judaism.

01:01:24.591 --> 01:01:28.383
Nevertheless, its growth would be unparalleled.

01:01:30.508 --> 01:01:32.216
Paul of Taurus would take the word

01:01:32.216 --> 01:01:36.091
of his chosen lord across the known world, from Greece

01:01:36.091 --> 01:01:39.925
to Turkey to Syria, the word of Jesus Christ spread.

01:01:39.925 --> 01:01:43.466
His missionary tales are now documented in the New Testament

01:01:43.466 --> 01:01:45.091
as the Book of Acts.

01:01:45.091 --> 01:01:47.383
The more Paul went to different places,

01:01:47.383 --> 01:01:49.341
the more followers he gained.

01:01:49.341 --> 01:01:52.341
On the same token, it created more enemies.

01:01:52.341 --> 01:01:54.425
The divide between monotheism

01:01:54.425 --> 01:01:57.050
and polytheism was on the rise.

01:01:57.050 --> 01:01:59.925
It was beginning to get a lot tougher for Romans

01:01:59.925 --> 01:02:02.091
to accept a religious population

01:02:02.091 --> 01:02:05.633
that didn't believe in gods like Mars and Jupiter.

01:02:05.633 --> 01:02:10.633
So when the great fire of Rome occurred in July of 64 AD

01:02:10.716 --> 01:02:14.133
Emperor Nero quickly blamed it on the Christians.

01:02:14.133 --> 01:02:15.633
The Great Fire was an event

01:02:15.633 --> 01:02:19.008
that destroyed two thirds of the city of Rome.

01:02:19.008 --> 01:02:21.841
So in order to pay for these massive repairs,

01:02:21.841 --> 01:02:25.341
Nero instituted heavy tributes across the empire

01:02:25.341 --> 01:02:28.050
to meet at least a proportion of the costs,

01:02:28.050 --> 01:02:31.258
Nero also started to print more Roman currency,

01:02:31.258 --> 01:02:33.383
creating an inflationary effect

01:02:33.383 --> 01:02:36.300
for the first time in the empire's history.

01:02:36.300 --> 01:02:39.550
However, the individuals who lived under Roman rule,

01:02:39.550 --> 01:02:43.800
which wasn't in Rome proper, were upset by this new policy.

01:02:43.800 --> 01:02:48.216
So in the holy city of Jerusalem in 66 AD,

01:02:48.216 --> 01:02:49.841
a revolt was on.

01:02:49.841 --> 01:02:52.841
At first, the first Jewish revolt succeeded,

01:02:52.841 --> 01:02:54.091
and the Jewish forces

01:02:54.091 --> 01:02:57.175
quickly expelled the unprepared Roman army.

01:02:57.175 --> 01:02:59.216
Then the rebels gained some traction

01:02:59.216 --> 01:03:01.675
in the neighboring villages in Galilee.

01:03:01.675 --> 01:03:04.550
In response, the Roman emperor Nero sent

01:03:04.550 --> 01:03:08.216
the general Vespasian to meet the Jewish forces,

01:03:08.216 --> 01:03:12.383
an endeavor that pushed most rebels into Jerusalem proper,

01:03:12.383 --> 01:03:17.383
by the time Vespasian was proclaimed emperor in 69 CD,

01:03:17.383 --> 01:03:20.508
then around Passover in 70 AD,

01:03:20.508 --> 01:03:24.216
Vespasian and his forces sieged the city depleting it

01:03:24.216 --> 01:03:25.425
of food and water,

01:03:25.425 --> 01:03:28.425
within the walls of Jerusalem, the Jews started

01:03:28.425 --> 01:03:32.216
to quarrel within, leaving them more vulnerable to attack.

01:03:32.216 --> 01:03:35.716
By August, the Romans breached the defenses,

01:03:35.716 --> 01:03:37.800
killed much of the population

01:03:37.800 --> 01:03:40.466
and destroyed many of their holy sites.

01:03:40.466 --> 01:03:42.508
With the Jews decimated,

01:03:42.508 --> 01:03:45.508
the strength of polytheism lived long.

01:03:47.341 --> 01:03:52.341
Then in 98 to 117 AD under Emperor Trajan,

01:03:52.675 --> 01:03:54.383
the Roman Empire was able

01:03:54.383 --> 01:03:57.716
to expand its greatest territorial extent,

01:03:57.716 --> 01:04:00.508
spanning all the way from modern day Britain

01:04:00.508 --> 01:04:02.258
to the Persian Gulf.

01:04:02.258 --> 01:04:05.216
Roman rule was everywhere.

01:04:05.216 --> 01:04:07.883
Well, except for in the Americas,

01:04:07.883 --> 01:04:11.008
because the Romans didn't even know they existed.

01:04:11.008 --> 01:04:13.050
In the Americas, we can see the growth

01:04:13.050 --> 01:04:14.633
of various civilizations

01:04:14.633 --> 01:04:18.466
across the Andes located in modern day Peru, in Chile,

01:04:18.466 --> 01:04:20.341
the Moche civilization was able

01:04:20.341 --> 01:04:23.300
to build monumental structures

01:04:23.300 --> 01:04:26.508
like the Huaca del Son and Huaca de la Luna,

01:04:26.508 --> 01:04:29.300
impressive pyramids that were the center

01:04:29.300 --> 01:04:30.716
of their religions.

01:04:30.716 --> 01:04:33.716
They also created advanced fertilization techniques

01:04:33.716 --> 01:04:36.508
that used bird droppings as fertilizer.

01:04:36.508 --> 01:04:38.383
Their highly centralized government

01:04:38.383 --> 01:04:41.341
made everyone know their place in society.

01:04:42.550 --> 01:04:44.133
While a little bit more south,

01:04:44.133 --> 01:04:48.591
the Nazca civilization is one enthralled in mystery,

01:04:48.591 --> 01:04:50.758
the people of Nazca created a series

01:04:50.758 --> 01:04:54.175
of large scale geoglyph consisting of hundreds

01:04:54.175 --> 01:04:57.925
of individual figures, including geometric shapes,

01:04:57.925 --> 01:05:00.091
animals, and human-like figures.

01:05:00.091 --> 01:05:01.258
By removing the dark,

01:05:01.258 --> 01:05:05.341
reddish brown iron oxide coated pebbles covering the surface

01:05:05.341 --> 01:05:06.800
of the Nazca desert.

01:05:06.800 --> 01:05:10.008
These lines are now called Nazca lines.

01:05:10.008 --> 01:05:13.341
The purpose of which is still unknown to this day,

01:05:13.341 --> 01:05:16.050
and subject to conspiracy theory today.

01:05:17.425 --> 01:05:18.841
Around 100 AD,

01:05:18.841 --> 01:05:23.091
the Zapotec started establishing Monte Alban, their capital.

01:05:23.091 --> 01:05:25.050
It was one of the first examples

01:05:25.050 --> 01:05:27.675
of urban planning in the Americas.

01:05:27.675 --> 01:05:31.050
The city was laid out in a grid pattern with main roads

01:05:31.050 --> 01:05:33.300
and smaller side streets leading to plazas

01:05:33.300 --> 01:05:34.800
and public buildings.

01:05:34.800 --> 01:05:37.883
The city was also divided into different districts,

01:05:37.883 --> 01:05:41.550
each with specialized functions such as residential,

01:05:41.550 --> 01:05:43.883
administrative, and religious,

01:05:43.883 --> 01:05:47.758
leaving it to be in use for a thousand years after that.

01:05:53.675 --> 01:05:55.341
While back in Rome,

01:05:55.341 --> 01:05:58.883
after the end of Trajan's reign in 117 AD,

01:05:58.883 --> 01:06:01.591
a new emperor with a purpose was in hand.

01:06:01.591 --> 01:06:05.091
Hadrian was a man tasked with a near impossible,

01:06:05.091 --> 01:06:08.758
keeping the massive Roman empire, under one rule,

01:06:08.758 --> 01:06:10.425
he first had to deal with a crisis

01:06:10.425 --> 01:06:13.175
with the newly colonized Roman Britain.

01:06:13.175 --> 01:06:14.300
Like their predecessors,

01:06:14.300 --> 01:06:18.008
in Judea, the Roman Brits did not like being Roman,

01:06:18.008 --> 01:06:20.091
so they started to cause unrest,

01:06:20.091 --> 01:06:21.841
and in the eyes of Hadrian,

01:06:21.841 --> 01:06:25.300
a real threat of revolution was on his mind.

01:06:25.300 --> 01:06:28.091
So Hadrian had ordered a massive wall

01:06:28.091 --> 01:06:30.091
aptly named Hadrian's Wall,

01:06:30.091 --> 01:06:32.800
which spanned almost coast to coast,

01:06:32.800 --> 01:06:35.216
keeping it sunk in the conquered people's minds

01:06:35.216 --> 01:06:36.883
that the Romans were here,

01:06:36.883 --> 01:06:39.591
staving off revolution in one region.

01:06:39.591 --> 01:06:43.050
However, in Galilee, things weren't as peaceful.

01:06:43.050 --> 01:06:46.841
Simon bar Kokhba led a rebellion of the Jewish people

01:06:46.841 --> 01:06:49.341
to free themselves from Roman rule.

01:06:49.341 --> 01:06:51.216
As you see, Rome was developing

01:06:51.216 --> 01:06:54.383
a new city called Aelia Capitolina

01:06:54.383 --> 01:06:56.341
over the ruins of Jerusalem.

01:06:56.341 --> 01:06:58.758
From the last revolt with temples dedicated

01:06:58.758 --> 01:07:01.258
to polytheistic gods like Jupiter.

01:07:01.258 --> 01:07:05.258
By 132, bar Kokhba took the (indistinct) of Nasi,

01:07:05.258 --> 01:07:06.383
head of state.

01:07:06.383 --> 01:07:08.925
Many Jews regarded him as the Messiah,

01:07:08.925 --> 01:07:10.591
who would save the Jewish people

01:07:10.591 --> 01:07:12.675
and restore their independence.

01:07:12.675 --> 01:07:15.716
Kokhba's troops would storm Aelia Capitolina,

01:07:15.716 --> 01:07:17.550
almost knocking out entirely

01:07:17.550 --> 01:07:20.050
the Roman garrison controlling the city.

01:07:20.050 --> 01:07:22.591
Hadrian, though would not have it.

01:07:22.591 --> 01:07:27.591
So he sent a force of 120,000 men to the lands of Judea

01:07:27.716 --> 01:07:31.466
to conquer and force the Jewish people into submission.

01:07:31.466 --> 01:07:34.591
As Cassius Dio says, in the History of Rome,

01:07:34.591 --> 01:07:37.341
"50 of their most important outposts

01:07:37.341 --> 01:07:41.925
and 985 of their most famous villages were razed.

01:07:41.925 --> 01:07:46.925
580,000 men were slain in the various raids and battles

01:07:47.758 --> 01:07:50.425
and the number of those that perished by famine,

01:07:50.425 --> 01:07:53.550
disease, and fire was past finding out.

01:07:53.550 --> 01:07:57.591
Thus, nearly the whole of Judea was made desolate."

01:07:57.591 --> 01:08:01.758
History of Rome 69.14, one to two.

01:08:01.758 --> 01:08:05.633
Rome made it clear that it was not to be taken lightly.

01:08:07.716 --> 01:08:11.008
While in China, the message was quite different.

01:08:11.008 --> 01:08:13.341
The ideas of Buddhism were spreading,

01:08:13.341 --> 01:08:16.383
along with the Chinese philosophies of Confucianism

01:08:16.383 --> 01:08:18.966
and Taoism and built a dynasty.

01:08:18.966 --> 01:08:21.091
These three philosophies work together

01:08:21.091 --> 01:08:23.050
to make the Han Dynasty stronger

01:08:23.050 --> 01:08:25.175
and more united in many ways.

01:08:26.383 --> 01:08:29.050
While in America, the Mayan architects went

01:08:29.050 --> 01:08:32.466
across Northern Peten and designed a series of short,

01:08:32.466 --> 01:08:35.091
broad temples with wide staircases,

01:08:35.091 --> 01:08:37.800
flanked by enormous stucco masks.

01:08:37.800 --> 01:08:40.550
These stucco masks were made of plaster

01:08:40.550 --> 01:08:43.133
and some burned and powdered limestone.

01:08:43.133 --> 01:08:45.508
The Mayans built these stone armatures

01:08:45.508 --> 01:08:50.508
into elaborate deity faces to capture the soul of the gods

01:08:50.633 --> 01:08:52.258
and bring it to the people.

01:08:52.258 --> 01:08:55.133
A temple like the E seven sub.

01:08:55.133 --> 01:08:57.258
Yes, historians named Mayan temples

01:08:57.258 --> 01:09:02.258
like military submarines, is a pyramid with 16 stucco masks.

01:09:02.925 --> 01:09:05.341
Each allows us to go deeper into the souls

01:09:05.341 --> 01:09:07.466
of these deities of the past.

01:09:08.716 --> 01:09:11.341
In the Middle East, a new empire was emerging

01:09:11.341 --> 01:09:14.883
with roots in the past, a man named Ardashir claimed

01:09:14.883 --> 01:09:17.383
to have a royal blood that traced all the way back

01:09:17.383 --> 01:09:18.716
to Cyrus the Great.

01:09:18.716 --> 01:09:21.841
Ardashir claimed that he should be the true ruler

01:09:21.841 --> 01:09:23.341
of the Persian Empire,

01:09:23.341 --> 01:09:25.841
not those frauds of the Parthians.

01:09:25.841 --> 01:09:29.466
Ardashir was able to unite the various tribes of Persia.

01:09:29.466 --> 01:09:33.591
In 224 AD Ardashir I led his forces

01:09:33.591 --> 01:09:36.675
against the Parthian King, Artabatus V,

01:09:36.675 --> 01:09:41.008
in a significant battle at Hormozgan, the Sasanian forces

01:09:41.008 --> 01:09:44.091
known for their cavalry defeated the Parthians

01:09:44.091 --> 01:09:46.341
and captured Artabatus V.

01:09:46.341 --> 01:09:50.800
With this victory Ardashir I declared himself king

01:09:50.800 --> 01:09:53.341
and established the Sasanian empire.

01:09:53.341 --> 01:09:55.550
Ardashir I quickly established

01:09:55.550 --> 01:09:57.300
a centralized government

01:09:57.300 --> 01:10:01.300
and built a new capital at Ctesiphon on the Tigris River,

01:10:01.300 --> 01:10:04.258
he reestablished the Zoroastrian religion,

01:10:04.258 --> 01:10:06.466
which had been suppressed by the Parthians

01:10:06.466 --> 01:10:09.008
as the empire's official religion.

01:10:09.008 --> 01:10:12.008
He also built a powerful military machine

01:10:12.008 --> 01:10:14.633
with skilled cavalry and archers.

01:10:14.633 --> 01:10:16.925
He began to expand his territory

01:10:16.925 --> 01:10:19.550
by conquering neighboring regions.

01:10:21.591 --> 01:10:24.133
As the Parthians were on their way out,

01:10:24.133 --> 01:10:25.550
so were the Han.

01:10:25.550 --> 01:10:28.091
The Han Dynasty's downfall was marked

01:10:28.091 --> 01:10:31.258
by political instability, economic problems,

01:10:31.258 --> 01:10:36.091
external threats, internal rebellions and power struggles.

01:10:36.091 --> 01:10:39.633
The weakening of central authority allowed regional warlords

01:10:39.633 --> 01:10:42.258
to seize power, and the government's attempts

01:10:42.258 --> 01:10:45.550
to address economic issues were unsuccessful.

01:10:45.550 --> 01:10:46.466
External threats

01:10:46.466 --> 01:10:50.091
and rebellions weakened the dynasty even further.

01:10:50.091 --> 01:10:53.758
A warlord named Cao Pi declared himself emperor

01:10:53.758 --> 01:10:55.883
and established the Wei Dynasty,

01:10:55.883 --> 01:10:58.883
officially ending the Han Dynasty.

01:11:03.841 --> 01:11:05.216
While back in Rome,

01:11:05.216 --> 01:11:10.216
Emperor Diocletian, 284 to 305 faced a problem.

01:11:10.300 --> 01:11:14.300
Rome was becoming too large and impossible to manage.

01:11:14.300 --> 01:11:16.758
So Diocletian created the tetrarchy

01:11:16.758 --> 01:11:18.633
and divided the region into four,

01:11:18.633 --> 01:11:21.591
where each region was governed by a separate emperor.

01:11:21.591 --> 01:11:24.925
Within the tetrarchy, there were two types of emperors,

01:11:24.925 --> 01:11:27.258
Augustus and Caesars.

01:11:27.258 --> 01:11:29.550
Dian chose Maximilian

01:11:29.550 --> 01:11:31.883
to be his equal to Augustus.

01:11:31.883 --> 01:11:35.466
In contrast, Galerius and Constantius were appointed

01:11:35.466 --> 01:11:36.966
to be Caesars.

01:11:36.966 --> 01:11:41.758
However, this system created uncontrolled chaos and anarchy.

01:11:41.758 --> 01:11:45.091
Each emperor had desires for power and ambition,

01:11:45.091 --> 01:11:49.341
and it all came to a head in 305 when power shifted,

01:11:49.341 --> 01:11:52.383
both Diocletian and Maximian retired,

01:11:52.383 --> 01:11:55.758
and in 306, Constantius died.

01:11:55.758 --> 01:11:59.383
Three out of the four original leaders were left out

01:11:59.383 --> 01:12:02.925
of the system leading to a power vacuum to come.

01:12:02.925 --> 01:12:05.300
Emperor Constantine the Great was appointed

01:12:05.300 --> 01:12:08.966
by his father's army unilaterally as an Augustus

01:12:08.966 --> 01:12:12.925
and a Caesar at the same time to replace his father.

01:12:12.925 --> 01:12:16.133
At the same time, Maximian's son Maxentius felt

01:12:16.133 --> 01:12:18.591
as though he should have been appointed Caesar

01:12:18.591 --> 01:12:20.800
instead of Valerius Severus.

01:12:20.800 --> 01:12:24.633
So in 307, Maxentius sent his army

01:12:24.633 --> 01:12:27.966
and forced Valerius Severus to surrender.

01:12:27.966 --> 01:12:32.508
Come 308, Galerius appointed Licinius to replace him.

01:12:32.508 --> 01:12:36.550
So on the west side of Rome, two emperors wanted to rule.

01:12:36.550 --> 01:12:39.341
Constantine ruled over Gaul in Britain

01:12:39.341 --> 01:12:42.633
and Maxentius ruled Italy and North Africa.

01:12:42.633 --> 01:12:46.633
Maxentius had a difficult time consolidating his power,

01:12:46.633 --> 01:12:50.216
and he faced increasing resistance from the people of Rome.

01:12:50.216 --> 01:12:52.883
To try and secure his hold on power,

01:12:52.883 --> 01:12:54.925
Maxentius ordered the construction

01:12:54.925 --> 01:12:58.841
of a new bridge across the Tiber River near Rome,

01:12:58.841 --> 01:13:01.133
known as the Milvian Bridge.

01:13:01.133 --> 01:13:04.925
Constantine saw Maxentius as a threat to his power,

01:13:04.925 --> 01:13:08.008
so he decided to march on Rome to confront him.

01:13:08.008 --> 01:13:09.591
As the two armies approached

01:13:09.591 --> 01:13:11.758
each other near the Milvian Bridge,

01:13:11.758 --> 01:13:14.925
Constantine had a vision of a cross in the sky

01:13:14.925 --> 01:13:18.175
with the words in this sign conquer.

01:13:18.175 --> 01:13:21.091
Some accounts suggest that this vision may have been a dream

01:13:21.091 --> 01:13:22.716
or a hallucination.

01:13:22.716 --> 01:13:25.800
While others suggest that it may have been a sign from God.

01:13:25.800 --> 01:13:29.008
Regardless of the nature of the vision, Constantine took it

01:13:29.008 --> 01:13:31.550
as a sign that he would be victorious in battle

01:13:31.550 --> 01:13:34.675
if he fought under the sign of the Christian Cross.

01:13:34.675 --> 01:13:37.175
He had his soldiers paint this symbol on their shields

01:13:37.175 --> 01:13:39.050
and banners, and he went into battle

01:13:39.050 --> 01:13:41.508
with renewed vigor and confidence.

01:13:41.508 --> 01:13:42.883
The battle was fierce

01:13:42.883 --> 01:13:46.550
and brutal with both sides suffering heavy losses.

01:13:46.550 --> 01:13:48.550
Maxentius had a larger army,

01:13:48.550 --> 01:13:51.341
but his troops were spread out and disorganized.

01:13:51.341 --> 01:13:53.966
Constantine was able to take advantage of this

01:13:53.966 --> 01:13:57.133
and he was able to push Maxentius' forces back

01:13:57.133 --> 01:13:58.675
towards the Tiber River.

01:13:58.675 --> 01:14:00.258
In the chaos of the retreat,

01:14:00.258 --> 01:14:03.091
Maxentius was forced off the Milvian bridge

01:14:03.091 --> 01:14:05.466
and into the water where he drowned.

01:14:05.466 --> 01:14:07.133
Shortly after his victory,

01:14:07.133 --> 01:14:11.216
Constantine met Licinius at Mediolanum, modern Milan,

01:14:11.216 --> 01:14:12.925
to confirm several political

01:14:12.925 --> 01:14:16.800
and dynastic arrangements to produce the Edict of Milan.

01:14:16.800 --> 01:14:20.550
This edict gave power for Eastern Rome to Licinius

01:14:20.550 --> 01:14:23.716
and Constantine sole power of the west.

01:14:23.716 --> 01:14:24.966
More importantly though,

01:14:24.966 --> 01:14:28.883
this document extended religious tolerance for Christians

01:14:28.883 --> 01:14:32.008
and restored any properties confiscated from them,

01:14:32.008 --> 01:14:33.675
during the persecution,

01:14:33.675 --> 01:14:35.883
however, the peaceful coexistence

01:14:35.883 --> 01:14:38.300
of both rulers was short-lived.

01:14:38.300 --> 01:14:41.466
Though the edict allowed for the safety of Christians,

01:14:41.466 --> 01:14:44.633
Licinius was still very much a paganist.

01:14:44.633 --> 01:14:46.591
Their differences started to grow.

01:14:46.591 --> 01:14:51.383
All came near the city of Chrysopolis in 324 AD

01:14:51.383 --> 01:14:53.383
where both armies went and fought.

01:14:53.383 --> 01:14:56.633
Constantine's military might was on display.

01:14:56.633 --> 01:15:00.591
He was able to force the Eastern Roman army towards the sea,

01:15:00.591 --> 01:15:03.008
leaving many to be killed or captured.

01:15:03.008 --> 01:15:06.050
Constantine was declared the sole leader of Rome

01:15:06.050 --> 01:15:09.716
and Licinius was declared dead by hanging.

01:15:09.716 --> 01:15:12.966
He renamed the Eastern Roman capital from Byzantium

01:15:12.966 --> 01:15:16.258
to Constantinople to celebrate his victory.

01:15:16.258 --> 01:15:18.508
Then in 325 AD,

01:15:18.508 --> 01:15:21.758
Constantine presided over the First Council of Nicea

01:15:21.758 --> 01:15:23.883
when the 300 bishops established

01:15:23.883 --> 01:15:26.133
the now famous Nicene Creed

01:15:26.133 --> 01:15:30.175
which declared that Jesus Christ was begotten, not made,

01:15:30.175 --> 01:15:33.133
and of one substance with the Father.

01:15:33.133 --> 01:15:35.425
Constantine was finally baptized

01:15:35.425 --> 01:15:39.550
as a Christian on his death bed, in 337 AD.

01:15:47.050 --> 01:15:50.800
Come 370 AD, a new player was on the scenes.

01:15:50.800 --> 01:15:54.591
The Huns were a barbaric nomadic civilization

01:15:54.591 --> 01:15:57.216
who were masters of warfare.

01:15:57.216 --> 01:16:00.508
According to legends, they were taught horsemanship as early

01:16:00.508 --> 01:16:02.091
as the age of three.

01:16:02.091 --> 01:16:03.633
Also, they would attack their own

01:16:03.633 --> 01:16:06.466
with a sword to teach them how to endure pain.

01:16:06.466 --> 01:16:09.133
These people weren't to be messed lightly with.

01:16:09.133 --> 01:16:11.883
When they crossed the Volga River in 370

01:16:11.883 --> 01:16:14.425
on their horses and lusted for blood,

01:16:14.425 --> 01:16:18.050
the Alans civilization didn't stand much chance.

01:16:18.050 --> 01:16:20.841
Two years later, they attacked the Ostrogoths,

01:16:20.841 --> 01:16:23.133
an eastern tribe of Germanic Goths,

01:16:23.133 --> 01:16:24.758
who harassed the Roman empire

01:16:24.758 --> 01:16:27.550
by frequently attacking their territories.

01:16:27.550 --> 01:16:31.466
By 376, the Huns had attacked the Visigoths,

01:16:31.466 --> 01:16:33.425
the Western tribe of Goths

01:16:33.425 --> 01:16:37.425
and forced them to seek sanctuary within the Roman Empire.

01:16:37.425 --> 01:16:39.383
As the Huns dominated Goth

01:16:39.383 --> 01:16:42.466
and Visigoth lands, they earned a new reputation

01:16:42.466 --> 01:16:47.216
as the new barbarians in town and seemed unstoppable.

01:16:47.216 --> 01:16:51.925
By 395 AD they began invading Roman domains,

01:16:51.925 --> 01:16:54.966
and some Roman Christians believed they were devils

01:16:54.966 --> 01:16:57.300
who arrived straight from hell.

01:16:58.841 --> 01:17:01.258
The reason they started invading Rome was

01:17:01.258 --> 01:17:03.925
because of the death of Theodosius the Great,

01:17:03.925 --> 01:17:05.300
his shining achievement

01:17:05.300 --> 01:17:08.925
as emperor was keeping the Goths and the Huns at bay,

01:17:08.925 --> 01:17:13.050
but on death, he decided to follow the ideas of Diocletian

01:17:13.050 --> 01:17:15.258
and split the empire up again.

01:17:15.258 --> 01:17:18.133
Splitting up control between his two sons,

01:17:18.133 --> 01:17:19.591
Arcadius in the east

01:17:19.591 --> 01:17:24.591
and Honorius in the west, making Theodosius the last leader

01:17:24.716 --> 01:17:26.050
of a united Rome.

01:17:27.716 --> 01:17:29.425
With Honorius in charge,

01:17:29.425 --> 01:17:32.008
the incapable general made Western Rome

01:17:32.008 --> 01:17:33.966
an easy target to be bullied.

01:17:33.966 --> 01:17:36.091
The Visigoths looking for a new place

01:17:36.091 --> 01:17:38.633
to live had their eyes set on Rome.

01:17:38.633 --> 01:17:41.175
So throughout the early 410s,

01:17:41.175 --> 01:17:44.841
the Visigoths ransacked various Roman cities.

01:17:44.841 --> 01:17:49.841
Then on August 24th, 410, the Visigoth sacked Rome,

01:17:50.008 --> 01:17:52.800
taking control of this historic city.

01:17:52.800 --> 01:17:56.216
It was the first time in nearly 800 years

01:17:56.216 --> 01:17:59.216
that a foreign army occupied the city of Rome.

01:17:59.216 --> 01:18:02.966
However, the Visigoths couldn't maintain control of Rome.

01:18:02.966 --> 01:18:06.716
Instead, they continued to ransack Roman territories

01:18:06.716 --> 01:18:09.800
until they established their kingdom in 418,

01:18:09.800 --> 01:18:11.466
in modern day Spain.

01:18:13.258 --> 01:18:16.383
While the prospects of existence weren't so much better

01:18:16.383 --> 01:18:17.800
in Eastern Rome,

01:18:17.800 --> 01:18:20.675
the notorious Attila the Hun was gaining power

01:18:20.675 --> 01:18:23.966
and his brutal tactics called him the Scourge of God.

01:18:23.966 --> 01:18:27.175
After a failed peace attempt in 441,

01:18:27.175 --> 01:18:28.966
Attila and his army stormed

01:18:28.966 --> 01:18:31.758
through the Balkans and the Danubian frontier.

01:18:31.758 --> 01:18:35.175
Another peace treaty was forged in 442,

01:18:35.175 --> 01:18:40.175
but Attila attacked again in 443, killing, ransacking

01:18:40.216 --> 01:18:43.341
and pillaging his way to the well fortified city

01:18:43.341 --> 01:18:44.883
of Constantinople.

01:18:44.883 --> 01:18:47.800
However, due to Constantinople's high walls,

01:18:47.800 --> 01:18:49.716
Attila couldn't conquer it.

01:18:49.716 --> 01:18:53.716
Instead, Attila was able to muster another peace agreement.

01:18:53.716 --> 01:18:55.800
He would leave Constantinople alone

01:18:55.800 --> 01:19:00.800
in exchange for an annual tribute of 2,100 pounds of gold,

01:19:01.008 --> 01:19:02.966
a staggering sum.

01:19:02.966 --> 01:19:06.716
Then in 451, the Huns invaded the Gauls,

01:19:06.716 --> 01:19:09.383
allowing the once enemies of the Visigoths

01:19:09.383 --> 01:19:11.050
and the Romans to wise up

01:19:11.050 --> 01:19:13.675
and work together to fight the Huns.

01:19:13.675 --> 01:19:14.883
According to legend,

01:19:14.883 --> 01:19:16.841
the night before the imminent battle,

01:19:16.841 --> 01:19:21.091
Attila consulted sacrificed bones and saw that thousands

01:19:21.091 --> 01:19:23.341
of his army would fall in the fight.

01:19:23.341 --> 01:19:26.591
The next day, his premonition came true.

01:19:26.591 --> 01:19:28.925
In the battle of the Catalaunian planes,

01:19:28.925 --> 01:19:32.675
after hours of ferocious fighting, tens of thousands

01:19:32.675 --> 01:19:35.841
of soldiers lay dead, giving Attila his first

01:19:35.841 --> 01:19:39.091
and only military defeat in history.

01:19:39.091 --> 01:19:43.300
However, even after the loss, Attila and his army marched on

01:19:43.300 --> 01:19:47.550
and returned to Italy, continuously ravaging the cities.

01:19:47.550 --> 01:19:51.300
In 452 with Rome in sight, he met Pope Leo I

01:19:52.216 --> 01:19:55.758
who acted as an emissary between Attila and Rome.

01:19:55.758 --> 01:19:58.216
There's no record of what they discussed.

01:19:58.216 --> 01:20:01.633
Still, according to legend, the apparitions of St. Paul

01:20:01.633 --> 01:20:04.008
and St. Peter appear to Attila.

01:20:04.008 --> 01:20:05.425
They threatened to kill him

01:20:05.425 --> 01:20:08.633
if he didn't negotiate with Pope Leo I.

01:20:08.633 --> 01:20:10.675
Attila decided to pull out of Italy

01:20:10.675 --> 01:20:13.591
and return to the great Hungarian plane,

01:20:13.591 --> 01:20:15.591
whether because of his fear of the Pope

01:20:15.591 --> 01:20:17.383
and his saintly allies

01:20:17.383 --> 01:20:20.341
or because of his troops were stretched too thin

01:20:20.341 --> 01:20:22.050
and weakened by malaria.

01:20:23.966 --> 01:20:27.383
However, the struggle for Western Rome wasn't over.

01:20:27.383 --> 01:20:32.050
In 476 AD, the young emperor Romulus Augustus

01:20:32.050 --> 01:20:34.591
had trouble keeping power for himself,

01:20:34.591 --> 01:20:37.216
as many Romans felt he was illegitimate.

01:20:37.216 --> 01:20:39.175
So the Eastern Roman empire sent

01:20:39.175 --> 01:20:41.466
the Germanic general Odoacer

01:20:41.466 --> 01:20:44.008
and his mercenaries to suppress a revolt

01:20:44.008 --> 01:20:46.216
by the Roman army in the region.

01:20:46.216 --> 01:20:49.841
However, instead of supporting the Eastern Roman empire,

01:20:49.841 --> 01:20:54.091
Odoacer saw an opportunity to seize power for himself.

01:20:54.091 --> 01:20:56.300
He turned against the Roman government

01:20:56.300 --> 01:20:59.175
and deposed the last Western Roman emperor,

01:20:59.175 --> 01:21:03.133
Romulus Augustus, effectively marking the end

01:21:03.133 --> 01:21:05.341
of the Western Roman empire.

01:21:05.341 --> 01:21:07.216
As the steps of his victory,

01:21:07.216 --> 01:21:10.175
Odoacer was declared the king of Italy.

01:21:10.175 --> 01:21:13.216
However, Odoacer's victory was short-lived

01:21:13.216 --> 01:21:17.550
because in 493, Theodoric the Great of the Ostrogoths

01:21:17.550 --> 01:21:21.050
with the support of Eastern Roman Emperor Zeno came in

01:21:21.050 --> 01:21:24.508
and created the Ostrogothic Kingdom of Italy,

01:21:24.508 --> 01:21:27.508
sending Odoacer to meet his fate.

01:21:30.716 --> 01:21:33.341
While Europe was in the crux of a dark age,

01:21:33.341 --> 01:21:35.925
India under the Gupta Empire was

01:21:35.925 --> 01:21:38.633
in a mathematical golden age.

01:21:38.633 --> 01:21:42.466
Great mathematicians like Brahmagupta started using zero

01:21:42.466 --> 01:21:45.383
as a placeholder and as various solutions

01:21:45.383 --> 01:21:47.383
for mathematical equations.

01:21:47.383 --> 01:21:49.591
The astronomer Aryabhata was able

01:21:49.591 --> 01:21:52.258
to calculate the circumference of the Earth.

01:21:52.258 --> 01:21:54.091
He proved the world was round

01:21:54.091 --> 01:21:56.925
long before it was globally accepted.

01:21:56.925 --> 01:21:59.508
Aryabhata was also able to develop methods

01:21:59.508 --> 01:22:02.341
for calculating pi and square roots.

01:22:02.341 --> 01:22:05.925
However, his crowning achievement was creating the concept

01:22:05.925 --> 01:22:10.258
of an asymptote, which is a line that approaches the curve

01:22:10.258 --> 01:22:11.633
but never touches it.

01:22:13.716 --> 01:22:15.841
The Franks under Clovis I

01:22:15.841 --> 01:22:18.091
had been an engaged with the Alamanni,

01:22:18.091 --> 01:22:19.883
another Germanic tribe

01:22:19.883 --> 01:22:23.216
and tensions between the two groups were running high.

01:22:23.216 --> 01:22:26.591
In 496 AD in the battle of Tolbiac,

01:22:26.591 --> 01:22:29.050
Clovis I led his forces into battle

01:22:29.050 --> 01:22:30.550
against the Alamanni,

01:22:30.550 --> 01:22:33.800
with both sides eager to gain the upper hand

01:22:33.800 --> 01:22:37.216
in the ongoing struggle for power and territory.

01:22:37.216 --> 01:22:40.591
As the Alamanni began to push the Franks to defeat,

01:22:40.591 --> 01:22:43.591
in a moment of desperation, Clovis called out

01:22:43.591 --> 01:22:46.216
to the Christian God for assistance,

01:22:46.216 --> 01:22:48.300
promising to convert to Christianity,

01:22:48.300 --> 01:22:50.425
if he emerged victorious.

01:22:50.425 --> 01:22:51.716
According to legend,

01:22:51.716 --> 01:22:55.675
a sudden thunderstorm appeared and the Franks could regroup

01:22:55.675 --> 01:22:59.591
and launch a successful counter attack against the Alamanni.

01:22:59.591 --> 01:23:03.091
The battle ended in a decisive victory for the Franks

01:23:03.091 --> 01:23:06.883
and Clovis kept his promise and converted to Christianity,

01:23:06.883 --> 01:23:10.508
officially cementing Christianity to the forefront

01:23:10.508 --> 01:23:12.800
and birthing the Frankish kingdom.

01:23:14.758 --> 01:23:17.425
While the western Roman empire might have fallen.

01:23:17.425 --> 01:23:20.550
In the East, the Roman Empire was changing.

01:23:20.550 --> 01:23:22.050
Many historians argue

01:23:22.050 --> 01:23:24.133
that the Eastern Roman empire based out

01:23:24.133 --> 01:23:27.716
of Constantinople should be considered a part of Rome.

01:23:27.716 --> 01:23:31.758
However, it is undeniable that under Justinian I

01:23:31.758 --> 01:23:33.675
would lead the Eastern half

01:23:33.675 --> 01:23:35.841
into its next chapter in life.

01:23:35.841 --> 01:23:39.508
The Byzantine Empire, whether it's a continuation

01:23:39.508 --> 01:23:42.300
of the Roman Empire before, is a debate

01:23:42.300 --> 01:23:43.841
for another (indistinct).

01:23:43.841 --> 01:23:46.133
Under the leadership of Justinian I,

01:23:46.133 --> 01:23:48.716
like many Roman emperors before him,

01:23:48.716 --> 01:23:50.966
he would expand the Byzantine Empire

01:23:50.966 --> 01:23:55.550
to reach places such as Italy, North Africa, and even Spain.

01:23:55.550 --> 01:23:58.341
He also commissioned a team of legal scholars

01:23:58.341 --> 01:24:01.716
to codify all the laws of the Roman Empire,

01:24:01.716 --> 01:24:05.966
known as the Corpus Juris Civilis which became the basis

01:24:05.966 --> 01:24:09.508
of the European laws we know today.

01:24:09.508 --> 01:24:12.716
He also commissioned the world-renowned Hagia Sophia

01:24:12.716 --> 01:24:16.466
in Constantinople, where this beautiful cathedral,

01:24:16.466 --> 01:24:18.716
adorned with intricate mosaics

01:24:18.716 --> 01:24:21.383
and marble decorations became the head

01:24:21.383 --> 01:24:23.966
of the Eastern Orthodox Church.

01:24:30.508 --> 01:24:33.883
However, Jesus wasn't the only prophet at the time.

01:24:33.883 --> 01:24:35.633
In the small town of Mecca,

01:24:35.633 --> 01:24:38.425
a nomadic tribe called the Quraysh gave birth

01:24:38.425 --> 01:24:40.050
to a man who would change

01:24:40.050 --> 01:24:43.341
the religious world, yet again, Muhammad.

01:24:43.341 --> 01:24:45.925
Muhammad was orphaned at an early age

01:24:45.925 --> 01:24:49.675
and was raised by his grandfather and later his uncle.

01:24:49.675 --> 01:24:52.133
As he grew up, he worked as a merchant,

01:24:52.133 --> 01:24:54.925
which earned him the nickname al-Amin,

01:24:54.925 --> 01:24:56.966
meaning the trustworthy.

01:24:56.966 --> 01:24:59.633
On one of his pilgrimages in 610,

01:24:59.633 --> 01:25:03.716
Muhammad meditated in a cave on Mount Jabal al-Nour,

01:25:03.716 --> 01:25:07.383
the angel Gabriel appeared and relayed the word of God.

01:25:07.383 --> 01:25:10.383
Recite in the name of your Lord who creates,

01:25:10.383 --> 01:25:12.341
creates a man from a clot.

01:25:12.341 --> 01:25:15.383
Recite for your Lord is most generous became

01:25:15.383 --> 01:25:20.175
the opening verses of Surah chapter 96 of the Quran.

01:25:20.175 --> 01:25:22.841
At first, Muhammad was reluctant,

01:25:22.841 --> 01:25:25.800
not knowing how to disclose this information.

01:25:25.800 --> 01:25:28.133
However, soon enough, Muhammad began

01:25:28.133 --> 01:25:30.175
to gather a small following,

01:25:30.175 --> 01:25:32.800
which was mocked by the pagans of Mecca.

01:25:32.800 --> 01:25:35.966
However, when Muhammad denounced idol worship,

01:25:35.966 --> 01:25:38.591
the leader of Mecca knew that he was through.

01:25:38.591 --> 01:25:41.383
So through the resistance from Mecca, Muhammad

01:25:41.383 --> 01:25:44.341
and his followers were eventually forced to immigrate

01:25:44.341 --> 01:25:48.341
to Medina, a city 260 miles away.

01:25:48.341 --> 01:25:52.841
There Muhammad was instrumental in ending various civil wars

01:25:52.841 --> 01:25:56.383
creating a prosperous Muslim community.

01:25:56.383 --> 01:25:59.425
Nevertheless, this prosperity would be challenged

01:25:59.425 --> 01:26:03.050
by the members of Muhammad's old tribe, the Quraysh

01:26:03.050 --> 01:26:05.633
and their allies who marched up to Medina

01:26:05.633 --> 01:26:08.550
with a large army to attack the Muslims.

01:26:08.550 --> 01:26:10.008
Muhammad devised a plan

01:26:10.008 --> 01:26:12.716
that they could defend the city if they dug a trench

01:26:12.716 --> 01:26:16.008
around its perimeter, making it near impossible

01:26:16.008 --> 01:26:18.175
for enemy forces to penetrate.

01:26:18.175 --> 01:26:20.758
For several weeks, the Quraysh tried to break

01:26:20.758 --> 01:26:24.300
through the trench, trying and trying yet again.

01:26:24.300 --> 01:26:25.883
Eventually, strong wind

01:26:25.883 --> 01:26:28.300
and heavy rain caused the Quraysh forces

01:26:28.300 --> 01:26:30.091
to abandon the siege,

01:26:30.091 --> 01:26:33.008
marking the Muslims as victorious.

01:26:33.008 --> 01:26:36.550
In 630, the Muslim army marched into Mecca,

01:26:36.550 --> 01:26:39.258
taking the city with minimum casualties.

01:26:39.258 --> 01:26:41.925
Muhammad gave amnesty to the enemy leaders

01:26:41.925 --> 01:26:43.925
who once supposed him, converting most

01:26:43.925 --> 01:26:46.925
of the Meccan population to Islam.

01:26:48.841 --> 01:26:50.716
At the time of Muhammad's death,

01:26:50.716 --> 01:26:54.591
the Muslims had successfully united the Arabian Peninsula

01:26:54.591 --> 01:26:56.383
under the banner of Islam.

01:26:56.383 --> 01:26:59.216
After Muhammad's death, a series of Caliphs

01:26:59.216 --> 01:27:03.091
or leaders took over the leadership of the Muslim community,

01:27:03.091 --> 01:27:07.175
beginning with Abu Bakr, a close companion of the prophet.

01:27:07.175 --> 01:27:09.008
Under the leadership of the Caliphs,

01:27:09.008 --> 01:27:12.591
the Muslim community continued to expand its territory,

01:27:12.591 --> 01:27:16.050
conquering new lands, and spreading the message of Islam.

01:27:16.050 --> 01:27:18.758
At first, Aku Bakr had his eyes set

01:27:18.758 --> 01:27:22.175
on the Byzantine Empire's provinces of Syria,

01:27:22.175 --> 01:27:26.550
taking over the crucial cities of Damascus and Jerusalem.

01:27:26.550 --> 01:27:28.258
Then in 636,

01:27:28.258 --> 01:27:31.341
the Arab forces invaded the Sasanian Empire,

01:27:31.341 --> 01:27:34.758
taking over their capital city in 637,

01:27:34.758 --> 01:27:37.300
marking the end of the Sasanian empire.

01:27:37.300 --> 01:27:39.216
Onward to Egypt, they went,

01:27:39.216 --> 01:27:41.508
where after years of fighting,

01:27:41.508 --> 01:27:44.008
they successfully defeated the Byzantine

01:27:44.008 --> 01:27:48.716
to take over the city of Alexandria in 642 AD,

01:27:48.716 --> 01:27:52.050
economically crippling the Byzantines.

01:27:52.050 --> 01:27:55.633
By 716, the Arab forces had conquered much

01:27:55.633 --> 01:27:57.716
of North Africa, Carthage,

01:27:57.716 --> 01:28:00.841
and Spain, so that by 716,

01:28:00.841 --> 01:28:05.133
the Arabs had an extensive empire from Lisbon to China.

01:28:07.050 --> 01:28:10.550
After consolidating their hold on the Iberian Peninsula,

01:28:10.550 --> 01:28:12.175
the Arabs launched raids

01:28:12.175 --> 01:28:15.383
into neighboring Francia, modern day France.

01:28:15.383 --> 01:28:19.216
In 732 AD they launched a significant invasion

01:28:19.216 --> 01:28:21.425
to expand their territory northward.

01:28:21.425 --> 01:28:25.883
The Arabs forces led by Emir Abdul Rahman Al Ghafiqi

01:28:25.883 --> 01:28:28.716
quickly conquered several cities in the region,

01:28:28.716 --> 01:28:30.841
including Bordeaux and Tours.

01:28:30.841 --> 01:28:34.591
However, Charles Martel, the military leader of the Franks,

01:28:34.591 --> 01:28:37.716
assembled a large army to meet the Arabs in battle,

01:28:37.716 --> 01:28:41.175
the battle of Christianity versus Islam.

01:28:41.175 --> 01:28:43.883
Both empires wanted to keep their own faith.

01:28:43.883 --> 01:28:47.633
The Arabs wanted to impose their religion onto the Franks.

01:28:47.633 --> 01:28:52.175
The two forces clashed near Tours on October 10th, 732 AD.

01:28:53.550 --> 01:28:56.550
The battle was fierce and lasted several days

01:28:56.550 --> 01:28:59.383
with both sides suffering heavy casualties.

01:28:59.383 --> 01:29:01.341
In the end, though, Charles Martel

01:29:01.341 --> 01:29:03.841
and the Franks emerged victorious

01:29:03.841 --> 01:29:07.800
and the Arab forces were forced to retreat back to Spain,

01:29:07.800 --> 01:29:11.925
ending the massive expansion of the Arabic empire.

01:29:18.883 --> 01:29:22.258
While in the West, the definition of God was war.

01:29:22.258 --> 01:29:24.300
In China, during the rule of the Tang,

01:29:24.300 --> 01:29:26.091
religions like Buddhism,

01:29:26.091 --> 01:29:29.966
Taoism, and Confucianism, all coexisted peacefully,

01:29:29.966 --> 01:29:33.508
a citizen was able to believe what they wanted to believe,

01:29:33.508 --> 01:29:34.841
leaving for many temples

01:29:34.841 --> 01:29:37.716
and pagodas to be built across the empire.

01:29:37.716 --> 01:29:39.258
Also, during the Tang,

01:29:40.216 --> 01:29:42.425
the height of Chinese poetry was upon us.

01:29:42.425 --> 01:29:43.716
Poets like Li Po

01:29:43.716 --> 01:29:47.758
and Du Fu created poems that later became the foundations

01:29:47.758 --> 01:29:49.466
of Chinese literature.

01:29:49.466 --> 01:29:51.883
Li Po wrote a poignant poem called

01:29:51.883 --> 01:29:54.550
Zazen on Ching-t'ing Mountain,

01:29:54.550 --> 01:29:56.341
translated by Sam Hamel,

01:29:56.341 --> 01:29:58.883
"the birds have vanished down the sky.

01:29:58.883 --> 01:30:01.133
Now the last cloud drains away.

01:30:01.133 --> 01:30:03.550
We sit together the mountain and me

01:30:03.550 --> 01:30:06.216
until only the mountain remains."

01:30:08.050 --> 01:30:11.258
Charlemagne, also known as Charles the Great

01:30:11.258 --> 01:30:14.591
became the king of the Franks in 768,

01:30:14.591 --> 01:30:17.300
Charlemagne was a skilled military leader

01:30:17.300 --> 01:30:19.341
who expanded the Frankish empire,

01:30:19.341 --> 01:30:21.383
through successful campaigns.

01:30:21.383 --> 01:30:23.550
He conquered much of Western Europe,

01:30:23.550 --> 01:30:27.675
including modern day France, Germany, Italy, and Spain.

01:30:27.675 --> 01:30:30.508
Charlemagne was also a devout Christian

01:30:30.508 --> 01:30:33.716
and worked to spread Christianity throughout his empire.

01:30:35.591 --> 01:30:39.008
In 785, Harun was declared Caliph,

01:30:39.008 --> 01:30:42.216
instead of focusing on conquering like his brethren,

01:30:42.216 --> 01:30:44.800
he instead focused on the scientific growth

01:30:44.800 --> 01:30:47.633
in the new capital city of Baghdad.

01:30:47.633 --> 01:30:51.508
Harun al-Rashid wanted to create the House of Wisdom,

01:30:51.508 --> 01:30:53.425
a library and research center

01:30:53.425 --> 01:30:56.050
that attracted scholars from around the world.

01:30:56.050 --> 01:30:58.383
These scholars would come to the House of Wisdom

01:30:58.383 --> 01:31:00.175
with the desire to learn.

01:31:00.175 --> 01:31:02.841
They've translated the works of the past as well

01:31:02.841 --> 01:31:07.425
as developing the science of algebra, chemistry, sociology,

01:31:07.425 --> 01:31:09.675
and the concept of infinity.

01:31:11.175 --> 01:31:15.175
While the Vikings had a different idea of progress,

01:31:15.175 --> 01:31:16.383
the Vikings were a group

01:31:16.383 --> 01:31:20.008
of uncivilized pagans from modern day Scandinavia

01:31:20.008 --> 01:31:22.216
who wanted to gain material wealth.

01:31:22.216 --> 01:31:25.800
So June 8th, 793 AD marked the beginning

01:31:25.800 --> 01:31:28.050
of the Viking Age in Europe.

01:31:28.050 --> 01:31:30.883
Lindisfarne was a small isolated island

01:31:30.883 --> 01:31:32.675
off the northeast coast of England

01:31:32.675 --> 01:31:35.216
that was home to a famous monastery

01:31:35.216 --> 01:31:38.008
and considered one of Europe's most important centers

01:31:38.008 --> 01:31:38.841
of learning.

01:31:38.841 --> 01:31:42.133
On the day of the raid, a group of Viking warriors,

01:31:42.133 --> 01:31:45.508
likely from Norway or Denmark, landed on the island

01:31:45.508 --> 01:31:47.508
and attacked the monastery.

01:31:47.508 --> 01:31:49.883
The Vikings pillaged the monastery,

01:31:49.883 --> 01:31:53.133
killing many monks and taking others as slaves.

01:31:53.133 --> 01:31:57.091
The raid was a brutal, an unexpected attack on a place

01:31:57.091 --> 01:32:00.091
of great religious and cultural significance,

01:32:00.091 --> 01:32:02.675
and it sent shock waves throughout Europe.

01:32:09.133 --> 01:32:13.841
In 799 in Rome, Pope Leo III was attacked by a faction

01:32:13.841 --> 01:32:17.133
of Rome who believed that the Pope was guilty of tyranny

01:32:17.133 --> 01:32:19.466
and serious personal misconduct.

01:32:19.466 --> 01:32:23.341
So Pope Leo III ran away to the Frankish kingdom.

01:32:23.341 --> 01:32:24.716
After this, Charlemagne

01:32:24.716 --> 01:32:28.341
and his Frank army provided an escort for the Pope

01:32:28.341 --> 01:32:30.841
and restored him to the papal office.

01:32:30.841 --> 01:32:34.591
But yet the power of the papacy was being questioned

01:32:34.591 --> 01:32:37.050
with many people wanting it to go away,

01:32:37.050 --> 01:32:40.341
which caused Charlamagne to go to Rome in late 800

01:32:40.341 --> 01:32:42.008
to fight for his Pope.

01:32:42.008 --> 01:32:45.300
For his loyalty, on Christmas day in the Basilica

01:32:45.300 --> 01:32:48.716
of St. Peter, Pope Leo III placed a crown

01:32:48.716 --> 01:32:50.258
on Charlamagne's head,

01:32:50.258 --> 01:32:53.966
declaring him the new Holy Roman emperor,

01:32:53.966 --> 01:32:58.800
creating a new Roman empire, the Holy Roman Empire,

01:32:58.800 --> 01:33:01.550
or at least the first rendition of it.

01:33:01.550 --> 01:33:03.800
Under Charlemagne, the foundations

01:33:03.800 --> 01:33:07.175
of a genuinely great empire were forming.

01:33:07.175 --> 01:33:10.258
But once Charlemagne died in 814,

01:33:10.258 --> 01:33:13.633
the new empire was bludgeoning with problems.

01:33:15.383 --> 01:33:19.300
His son, Louis the Pious, 788 to 840,

01:33:19.300 --> 01:33:22.675
inherited an empire filled with problems.

01:33:22.675 --> 01:33:26.050
Many of his own citizens viewed him as a strong Catholic

01:33:26.050 --> 01:33:29.300
who was well intentioned, but was incredibly weak

01:33:29.300 --> 01:33:31.258
and unable to do anything.

01:33:31.258 --> 01:33:34.550
As the Vikings continued their raids along the Rhine River

01:33:34.550 --> 01:33:36.925
attacking Holy Roman Empire cities

01:33:36.925 --> 01:33:39.716
such as Cologne, Trier And Mainz,

01:33:39.716 --> 01:33:42.383
raiding various Catholic monasteries

01:33:42.383 --> 01:33:45.383
and destroying religious artifacts caused fear

01:33:45.383 --> 01:33:47.800
and hatred among his citizens.

01:33:47.800 --> 01:33:49.466
Why would anyone trust a leader

01:33:49.466 --> 01:33:52.466
if they can't stop barbaric pagans?

01:33:52.466 --> 01:33:54.425
So various local leaders started

01:33:54.425 --> 01:33:56.633
to focus on defending their land

01:33:56.633 --> 01:33:59.800
rather than relying on the central government for defense.

01:33:59.800 --> 01:34:01.341
Hence beginning the process

01:34:01.341 --> 01:34:06.091
of independently recreating the Chinese system of feudalism.

01:34:06.091 --> 01:34:09.258
At this time, people would willingly farm on lands,

01:34:09.258 --> 01:34:11.800
giving up their freedom to these local leaders

01:34:11.800 --> 01:34:13.883
to protect them from the Vikings,

01:34:13.883 --> 01:34:17.258
creating the basis of a new system of feudalism.

01:34:18.341 --> 01:34:20.675
While the Holy Roman Empire might have been fighting

01:34:20.675 --> 01:34:21.633
with the Vikings

01:34:21.633 --> 01:34:24.175
and the Byzantines were fighting with the Arabs.

01:34:24.175 --> 01:34:25.883
In 820, a group

01:34:25.883 --> 01:34:29.008
of Arab raiders landed on the island of Crete.

01:34:29.008 --> 01:34:30.716
Over the next several years,

01:34:30.716 --> 01:34:34.175
Arab forces gradually gained control of the island,

01:34:34.175 --> 01:34:37.716
overcoming the resistance of the Byzantine defenders.

01:34:37.716 --> 01:34:40.591
The conquest was completed in 827,

01:34:40.591 --> 01:34:43.466
and Crete became part of the Arab Empire.

01:34:43.466 --> 01:34:44.925
The conquest of Sicily

01:34:44.925 --> 01:34:47.425
and Sardinia followed a similar pattern.

01:34:47.425 --> 01:34:51.550
In 827, a large Arab fleet landed on Sicily

01:34:51.550 --> 01:34:54.175
and Arab forces quickly gained control

01:34:54.175 --> 01:34:55.466
of much of the island.

01:34:55.466 --> 01:34:58.008
They then moved on to Sardinia, which fell

01:34:58.008 --> 01:35:01.050
to the Arab invaders in 828.

01:35:01.050 --> 01:35:02.966
In the Holy Roman empire,

01:35:02.966 --> 01:35:06.508
once Louis the Pious died in 840 AD,

01:35:06.508 --> 01:35:08.841
so did the Charlemagne Empire.

01:35:08.841 --> 01:35:11.591
The infighting between family members grew

01:35:11.591 --> 01:35:14.341
leading to the Holy Roman empire being divided

01:35:14.341 --> 01:35:16.383
between three family members,

01:35:16.383 --> 01:35:18.883
in the famous Treaty of Verdun.

01:35:18.883 --> 01:35:21.966
In the West, the formation of the West Frankish kingdom

01:35:21.966 --> 01:35:24.175
was given to Charlemagne's grandson,

01:35:24.175 --> 01:35:27.341
Charles the Bald in modern day France.

01:35:27.341 --> 01:35:30.383
In the East, the East Frankish kingdom was given

01:35:30.383 --> 01:35:33.341
to another grandson Louis the German,

01:35:33.341 --> 01:35:36.925
which was obviously settled in modern day Germany,

01:35:36.925 --> 01:35:38.758
while the Middle Kingdom was given

01:35:38.758 --> 01:35:41.466
to Charlemagne's eldest son, Lothair.

01:35:41.466 --> 01:35:44.133
However, being squeezed in between the west

01:35:44.133 --> 01:35:47.466
and East Frankish kingdoms gave the middle Kingdom

01:35:47.466 --> 01:35:51.383
a short lifespan and was practically irrelevant.

01:35:52.591 --> 01:35:55.883
The Vikings weren't just a problem for mainland Europe.

01:35:55.883 --> 01:35:59.133
They were pillaging everything in mainland England.

01:35:59.133 --> 01:36:03.425
So in 871, the new king of Wessex, Alfred the Great rose

01:36:03.425 --> 01:36:07.883
to power with one thing in mind, keeping everyone safe.

01:36:07.883 --> 01:36:11.425
Alfred built a network of fortifications known as burrows,

01:36:11.425 --> 01:36:14.633
designed to protect his people from Viking attacks.

01:36:14.633 --> 01:36:18.175
He also developed new military tactics and strategies

01:36:18.175 --> 01:36:23.175
and fostered alliances with other Anglo-Saxon kingdoms.

01:36:23.216 --> 01:36:25.008
Unlike in Great Britain, though,

01:36:25.008 --> 01:36:28.341
the Vikings were actually invited to Russia.

01:36:28.341 --> 01:36:31.758
According to Russian legend, the tribes in Russia were tired

01:36:31.758 --> 01:36:33.675
of dealing with political strife.

01:36:33.675 --> 01:36:37.133
So they invited the Varangians, a sect of Vikings

01:36:37.133 --> 01:36:40.050
to establish order and a government over there.

01:36:40.050 --> 01:36:42.925
Hence, Rurik came with his two brothers to the city

01:36:42.925 --> 01:36:46.883
of Novgorod, and using the Vikings' famous force,

01:36:46.883 --> 01:36:49.675
they were able to establish order in the city.

01:36:49.675 --> 01:36:52.050
Declaring Rurik as their new king,

01:36:52.050 --> 01:36:54.591
creating the Kievan Rus' dynasty.

01:36:54.591 --> 01:36:56.883
Under the military leadership of Oleg,

01:36:56.883 --> 01:36:58.758
one of the Rurik kingsmen,

01:36:58.758 --> 01:37:01.216
the Kievan Rus' started establishing Smolensk

01:37:01.216 --> 01:37:05.091
and Kiev in modern day Ukraine, creating the forefront

01:37:05.091 --> 01:37:06.425
of Russia today.

01:37:08.341 --> 01:37:09.716
While back in England,

01:37:09.716 --> 01:37:11.633
expanding upon his grandfather

01:37:11.633 --> 01:37:13.925
Alfred the Great's alliance network,

01:37:13.925 --> 01:37:17.216
Athelstan was declared king of Essex.

01:37:17.216 --> 01:37:20.716
Athelstan was able to get all the Anglo-Saxon kingdoms

01:37:20.716 --> 01:37:23.050
to work together to fend off the Vikings

01:37:23.050 --> 01:37:24.633
of the British Isles.

01:37:24.633 --> 01:37:27.716
He was declared to be the first king of England due

01:37:27.716 --> 01:37:32.133
to his ability to navigate alliances and keep everyone safe,

01:37:32.133 --> 01:37:36.175
beginning one of the longest monarchies in human history.

01:37:37.258 --> 01:37:39.466
While the East Frankish kingdom was facing

01:37:39.466 --> 01:37:40.883
a similar problem,

01:37:40.883 --> 01:37:44.216
the pagan Magyars were attacking everyone across

01:37:44.216 --> 01:37:47.466
the kingdom, leaving the kingdom to live in fear.

01:37:47.466 --> 01:37:51.675
However, King Otto of the East Frankish Empire was able

01:37:51.675 --> 01:37:53.633
to defeat the pesky Magyars

01:37:53.633 --> 01:37:56.966
at the Battle of Lechfeld in 955.

01:37:56.966 --> 01:38:01.550
Then in 961, he could fully conquer all of the kingdoms

01:38:01.550 --> 01:38:06.216
of Italy, restoring Christiandom to all the former pagans.

01:38:06.216 --> 01:38:09.883
So in 962, Otto I was coronated

01:38:09.883 --> 01:38:12.008
to Pope John the 12th in Rome

01:38:12.008 --> 01:38:15.383
to be the new Holy Roman emperor.

01:38:15.383 --> 01:38:19.383
In France, though, the West Frankish kingdom was struggling

01:38:19.383 --> 01:38:23.550
because in 987, King Louie the V, a direct descendant

01:38:23.550 --> 01:38:27.508
of Charlemagne died at age 20 without leaving an heir

01:38:27.508 --> 01:38:29.216
to take over their dynasty,

01:38:29.216 --> 01:38:31.758
leaving the French monarchy in peril.

01:38:31.758 --> 01:38:34.633
So the French aristocracy had an election

01:38:34.633 --> 01:38:36.091
between Hugh Capet,

01:38:36.091 --> 01:38:38.341
a noble with extensive lands in the region

01:38:38.341 --> 01:38:39.633
of Isle de France,

01:38:39.633 --> 01:38:42.175
and Charles Duke of Lower Lorraine.

01:38:42.175 --> 01:38:45.716
With the support of Adalberon, the Archbishop of Reims,

01:38:45.716 --> 01:38:49.258
Hugh Capet became the first king of France,

01:38:49.258 --> 01:38:51.841
starting the Capetian Dynasty.

01:38:56.216 --> 01:38:57.841
However, at this time,

01:38:57.841 --> 01:39:01.591
the typical person in Europe was always living in fear.

01:39:01.591 --> 01:39:04.675
Every civilization was on the verge of conquering.

01:39:04.675 --> 01:39:06.466
They've all become land hungry

01:39:06.466 --> 01:39:08.258
and were willing to fight for it.

01:39:08.258 --> 01:39:12.175
So across Europe at this time, every civilization started

01:39:12.175 --> 01:39:16.466
to entrench their society in the ideas of feudalism

01:39:16.466 --> 01:39:18.841
leading to another social pyramid.

01:39:18.841 --> 01:39:20.758
At the bottom, lay the serfs.

01:39:20.758 --> 01:39:24.258
Their job was to farm the land and ensure everyone was fed.

01:39:24.258 --> 01:39:27.716
Then came the knight who provided protection for the people.

01:39:27.716 --> 01:39:29.383
Then came the nobles

01:39:29.383 --> 01:39:33.091
who ruled over a specific territory owning the land.

01:39:33.091 --> 01:39:36.716
Then came the kings as previously mentioned, who gave lands

01:39:36.716 --> 01:39:40.675
to the nobles, but all the way at the top was the Pope

01:39:40.675 --> 01:39:43.675
because the Pope could speak directly to God

01:39:43.675 --> 01:39:47.633
and had God-given ownership of all the lands.

01:39:48.716 --> 01:39:52.800
In the early 11th century, Leif Erikson was sent on a voyage

01:39:52.800 --> 01:39:55.341
to discover lands west of Greenland.

01:39:55.341 --> 01:39:59.175
If you look at a map, west of Greenland is the Americas.

01:39:59.175 --> 01:40:01.258
So Leif and his crew ventured

01:40:01.258 --> 01:40:04.383
to this new mystical land called Vinland.

01:40:04.383 --> 01:40:07.133
In modern day, New Finland, Canada.

01:40:07.133 --> 01:40:09.925
Leif and his crew spent the winter in Vinland,

01:40:10.758 --> 01:40:12.175
establishing a small settlement and trading

01:40:12.175 --> 01:40:14.133
with the local indigenous people.

01:40:14.133 --> 01:40:16.466
They also explored the surrounding area,

01:40:16.466 --> 01:40:19.591
which they found rich in natural resources,

01:40:19.591 --> 01:40:21.925
including timber, fish, and game.

01:40:21.925 --> 01:40:25.050
Leif and his crew returned to Greenland in the spring

01:40:25.050 --> 01:40:29.008
where they were greeted as heroes for discovering new lands.

01:40:29.008 --> 01:40:32.425
Little did Leif know that he discovered a new continent

01:40:32.425 --> 01:40:34.091
for his European people.

01:40:38.383 --> 01:40:41.633
Though significantly less is known about the Americas,

01:40:41.633 --> 01:40:44.966
some historians believe that at the time a similar type

01:40:44.966 --> 01:40:47.925
of expansion happened in the American continent,

01:40:47.925 --> 01:40:49.091
like in Europe.

01:40:49.091 --> 01:40:52.591
Sadly, we just don't have the historical records

01:40:52.591 --> 01:40:54.216
from this unique period.

01:40:54.216 --> 01:40:57.508
We know that the Mayans down in South America were building

01:40:57.508 --> 01:41:01.966
the impressive cities of Tikal, Palenque, and Chichen Itza,

01:41:01.966 --> 01:41:04.841
having a population of anywhere between two

01:41:04.841 --> 01:41:06.591
and 10 million.

01:41:06.591 --> 01:41:08.925
We also know that there were various tribes

01:41:08.925 --> 01:41:11.633
across the north, including the Cherokee,

01:41:11.633 --> 01:41:13.841
the Navajo, and the Inuits.

01:41:13.841 --> 01:41:16.633
The Inuits are most likely to have interacted

01:41:16.633 --> 01:41:17.758
with Leif's fleet.

01:41:19.258 --> 01:41:20.508
While back in Europe,

01:41:20.508 --> 01:41:24.841
in the holy city of Jerusalem laid the very famous church,

01:41:24.841 --> 01:41:27.175
the Church of the Holy Sepulchre.

01:41:27.175 --> 01:41:28.800
According to Christian belief,

01:41:28.800 --> 01:41:32.216
this church was built on the day Jesus was crucified

01:41:32.216 --> 01:41:33.508
and resurrected.

01:41:33.508 --> 01:41:36.133
However, in 1009 AD

01:41:36.133 --> 01:41:39.091
Arab Caliph Al-Hakim ordered the destruction

01:41:39.091 --> 01:41:41.008
of this sacred holy site.

01:41:41.008 --> 01:41:43.466
All of the sacred sites were destroyed,

01:41:43.466 --> 01:41:46.133
leaving them completely annihilated.

01:41:46.133 --> 01:41:49.550
When the news reached Europe, Christians were horrified.

01:41:49.550 --> 01:41:54.008
Pope Sergius IV sent a circular letter to all churches

01:41:54.008 --> 01:41:56.591
calling for a holy fight in the Middle East

01:41:56.591 --> 01:41:59.800
and the expulsion of Muslims from the holy land.

01:42:00.841 --> 01:42:01.925
But yet, the Arabs

01:42:01.925 --> 01:42:04.883
of the Abbasid Caliphate would actually be expelled

01:42:04.883 --> 01:42:07.008
by another before Jerusalem,

01:42:07.008 --> 01:42:10.300
the Seljuk Turks, a central Asian Turkish people

01:42:10.300 --> 01:42:12.466
of the Muslim faith were beginning

01:42:12.466 --> 01:42:13.716
to grow their empire.

01:42:13.716 --> 01:42:15.550
In 1055,

01:42:15.550 --> 01:42:18.591
they took over the Abbasid Caliphate capital city

01:42:18.591 --> 01:42:19.716
of Baghdad.

01:42:19.716 --> 01:42:22.675
The Celtic Turks initially respected the Caliph

01:42:22.675 --> 01:42:25.550
but the Celtics took over the city over time.

01:42:25.550 --> 01:42:29.341
In 1076, they captured Medina followed the next year

01:42:29.341 --> 01:42:33.633
by the capturing of Mecca, the holiest city in Islam.

01:42:39.300 --> 01:42:41.966
Due to this, the Muslim world wasn't ready

01:42:41.966 --> 01:42:45.133
for Pope Urban II at the Council of Claremont

01:42:45.133 --> 01:42:48.425
in 1095 to call upon all Christians

01:42:48.425 --> 01:42:52.466
to take up arms and liberate the holy land from Muslim rule.

01:42:52.466 --> 01:42:55.258
The Pope promised spiritual rewards

01:42:55.258 --> 01:42:58.800
and forgiveness of sins to those who joined the crusade,

01:42:58.800 --> 01:43:00.508
and many knight, nobles

01:43:00.508 --> 01:43:03.841
and peasants were inspired to take up the cause.

01:43:03.841 --> 01:43:07.050
Many European nobles, such as Godfrey of Bouillon,

01:43:07.050 --> 01:43:09.508
Toulouse, Bohemond of Taranto

01:43:09.508 --> 01:43:12.883
and Robert of Flanders, brought their armies from Europe

01:43:12.883 --> 01:43:14.925
on their journey to Jerusalem.

01:43:14.925 --> 01:43:18.550
While the Christians were united, the Muslims were divided

01:43:18.550 --> 01:43:22.550
and unable to put up a strong defense against the Crusaders.

01:43:22.550 --> 01:43:26.883
Hence, the Christians took over the County of Edessa in 1098

01:43:26.883 --> 01:43:31.133
and finally the holy city of Jerusalem in 1099.

01:43:33.050 --> 01:43:35.633
However, the crusade wasn't done.

01:43:35.633 --> 01:43:39.800
In 1144, the Muslim forces led by Turkish ruler,

01:43:39.800 --> 01:43:43.925
Ahmad ad-Din Zengi, launched a siege against Edessa.

01:43:43.925 --> 01:43:45.591
The city was poorly defended,

01:43:45.591 --> 01:43:48.633
and the crusaders could not resist the Muslim forces

01:43:48.633 --> 01:43:49.466
for long.

01:43:49.466 --> 01:43:52.883
After a siege of several weeks, the city was breached

01:43:52.883 --> 01:43:55.633
and the Muslim forces overran the city,

01:43:55.633 --> 01:43:58.466
killing or enslaving much of the population,

01:43:58.466 --> 01:44:00.758
but the Christians weren't happy with that.

01:44:00.758 --> 01:44:05.091
So in 1147, the massive armies of Europe came back

01:44:05.091 --> 01:44:07.175
with attempts to free Edessa.

01:44:07.175 --> 01:44:11.091
The crusaders faced significant logistical challenges,

01:44:11.091 --> 01:44:14.050
including shortages of food and supplies.

01:44:14.050 --> 01:44:16.175
They were also plagued by infighting

01:44:16.175 --> 01:44:19.258
and political rivalries, which called the campaign

01:44:19.258 --> 01:44:22.258
to be in ruin after the disastrous loss

01:44:22.258 --> 01:44:25.341
of the Battle of Inab in 1149,

01:44:25.341 --> 01:44:28.925
which resulted in the capture of King Louis VII

01:44:28.925 --> 01:44:32.050
and the loss of much of the crusader army.

01:44:36.591 --> 01:44:39.091
While the Christians and Muslims were fighting,

01:44:39.091 --> 01:44:41.133
the Hindus in the Khmer Empire

01:44:41.133 --> 01:44:45.133
under King Suryavarman II built a fantastic temple

01:44:45.133 --> 01:44:48.841
for the Hindu God Vishnu called the Angkor Wat.

01:44:48.841 --> 01:44:50.841
Vishnu is an important God

01:44:50.841 --> 01:44:52.883
in Hinduism known as the preserver

01:44:52.883 --> 01:44:54.841
and protector of the universe.

01:44:54.841 --> 01:44:58.341
He has 10 incarnations or avatars

01:44:58.341 --> 01:45:00.883
and is often depicted as having blue skin

01:45:00.883 --> 01:45:02.925
and holding four objects.

01:45:02.925 --> 01:45:04.716
As you approach Angkor Wat,

01:45:04.716 --> 01:45:06.716
you are greeted by a massive moat

01:45:06.716 --> 01:45:10.341
and a grand entrance gate adorned with intricate carvings

01:45:10.341 --> 01:45:12.966
of mythological creatures and deities.

01:45:12.966 --> 01:45:15.966
The main temple rises like a towering mountain

01:45:15.966 --> 01:45:17.508
with intricate carvings

01:45:17.508 --> 01:45:20.966
and reliefs that tell the stories of Hindu mythology

01:45:20.966 --> 01:45:23.300
and the history of the Khmer Empire.

01:45:23.300 --> 01:45:25.050
The temple's galleries are lined

01:45:25.050 --> 01:45:28.800
with stunning bass reliefs depicting scenes of battles,

01:45:28.800 --> 01:45:32.633
ceremonies, and daily life in ancient Cambodia.

01:45:32.633 --> 01:45:35.966
At the heart of the complex is the central sanctuary,

01:45:35.966 --> 01:45:38.508
a massive pyramid-like structure surrounded

01:45:38.508 --> 01:45:40.925
by smaller temples and courtyards.

01:45:40.925 --> 01:45:44.091
The sanctuary is considered the most sacred part

01:45:44.091 --> 01:45:47.633
of the temple, adorned with intricately carved statues

01:45:47.633 --> 01:45:50.633
and images of Hindu gods and goddesses.

01:45:50.633 --> 01:45:53.716
It was an incredible feat of human ingenuity.

01:45:55.591 --> 01:45:59.300
But yet in 1187, the Muslim commander from Egypt,

01:45:59.300 --> 01:46:03.383
Saladin became fed up with the Christian rule of Jerusalem,

01:46:03.383 --> 01:46:07.258
so he declared a Holy War across the Muslim world,

01:46:07.258 --> 01:46:10.925
in order to re-conquer Jerusalem from the Christians.

01:46:10.925 --> 01:46:13.508
The battle occurred on a scorching hot day

01:46:13.508 --> 01:46:15.841
in the hills near the Sea of Galilee.

01:46:15.841 --> 01:46:19.050
Saladin's forces numbered around 20,000.

01:46:19.050 --> 01:46:21.300
The Crusaders had a much smaller force

01:46:21.300 --> 01:46:24.091
of around 12,000 knights, soldiers

01:46:24.091 --> 01:46:28.175
and civilians under the aptly named king, King Guy.

01:46:28.175 --> 01:46:31.341
The battle began with skirmishes between the two sides,

01:46:31.341 --> 01:46:35.133
but soon escalated into a full scale engagement.

01:46:35.133 --> 01:46:38.008
Saladin's forces could use their superior cavalry

01:46:38.008 --> 01:46:39.841
to encircle the crusaders

01:46:39.841 --> 01:46:42.508
who could not break through the Muslim lines.

01:46:42.508 --> 01:46:46.425
The heat and thirst soon took a toll on the crusaders

01:46:46.425 --> 01:46:48.508
who were weakened and disoriented.

01:46:48.508 --> 01:46:51.591
The Muslim forces took advantage of the situation.

01:46:51.591 --> 01:46:54.050
They launched a fierce attack, breaking

01:46:54.050 --> 01:46:57.175
through the crusader lines and capturing many nights.

01:46:57.175 --> 01:46:59.966
King Guy and a small group of knights were able

01:46:59.966 --> 01:47:01.591
to escape the battlefield.

01:47:01.591 --> 01:47:05.425
Still, the majority of the crusader army was destroyed.

01:47:05.425 --> 01:47:07.883
The loss of the battle was a severe blow

01:47:07.883 --> 01:47:10.300
to the Christian forces in the region,

01:47:10.300 --> 01:47:14.508
and it paved the way for Saladin's conquest of Jerusalem,

01:47:15.591 --> 01:47:18.175
but the Christians weren't going to allow that.

01:47:18.175 --> 01:47:20.008
So guess what happened?

01:47:20.008 --> 01:47:21.800
Another crusade.

01:47:21.800 --> 01:47:25.591
This time, the three most powerful monarchs at the time,

01:47:25.591 --> 01:47:28.675
Emperor Frederick I of the Holy Roman Empire,

01:47:28.675 --> 01:47:30.675
King Richard I of England,

01:47:30.675 --> 01:47:34.591
and King Philip II of France sent their best armies

01:47:34.591 --> 01:47:37.383
to reconquer the holy city of Jerusalem.

01:47:37.383 --> 01:47:40.300
However, all the force in the world

01:47:40.300 --> 01:47:43.966
couldn't retake Jerusalem, from the grips of Saladin.

01:47:43.966 --> 01:47:47.050
Leaving the third crusade to be a failure.

01:47:52.466 --> 01:47:55.591
Genghis was born to a mother kidnapped by his father

01:47:55.591 --> 01:47:57.175
and forced into marriage.

01:47:57.175 --> 01:47:59.883
Legend holds that he came into this world clutching

01:47:59.883 --> 01:48:02.216
a blood clot in his right hand.

01:48:02.216 --> 01:48:05.341
Before he turned 10, his father was poisoned to death

01:48:05.341 --> 01:48:07.050
by an enemy clan.

01:48:07.050 --> 01:48:10.216
Genghis' clan then deserted him, his mother,

01:48:10.216 --> 01:48:13.508
and his six siblings to avoid having to feed them.

01:48:13.508 --> 01:48:15.550
However, he soon began to make friends

01:48:15.550 --> 01:48:18.883
with the other clans throughout the Mongolian mountain side.

01:48:18.883 --> 01:48:22.800
By 1206, he had united all the various tribes,

01:48:22.800 --> 01:48:25.175
uniting 1 million people.

01:48:25.175 --> 01:48:28.050
For the time, Genghis was quite progressive.

01:48:28.050 --> 01:48:30.550
He made it illegal to sell and kidnap women,

01:48:30.550 --> 01:48:33.591
banished the idea of enslavement of any Mongol

01:48:33.591 --> 01:48:36.300
and even allowed freedom of religion.

01:48:36.300 --> 01:48:37.716
When it came to war though,

01:48:37.716 --> 01:48:40.716
Genghis was as barbaric as the next one,

01:48:40.716 --> 01:48:45.091
his first campaign was against the Xi Xia Kingdom in 1209,

01:48:45.091 --> 01:48:49.008
his army of mostly cavalry men on horses quickly outnumbered

01:48:49.008 --> 01:48:51.050
and destroyed the kingdom.

01:48:51.050 --> 01:48:53.966
His next target was the Jin dynasty in China.

01:48:53.966 --> 01:48:56.216
From 1211 to 1214,

01:48:56.216 --> 01:48:59.550
the outnumbered Mongols ravaged the countryside,

01:48:59.550 --> 01:49:01.008
causing food shortages,

01:49:01.008 --> 01:49:04.425
resulting in the Jin Army killing tens of thousands

01:49:05.300 --> 01:49:08.008
of their own peasants just so their elites could live.

01:49:08.008 --> 01:49:11.133
In 1214, the Mongols besieged the capital

01:49:11.133 --> 01:49:15.841
of Dadu, now Beijing and burnt it to the ground.

01:49:15.841 --> 01:49:17.633
In the early 13th century,

01:49:17.633 --> 01:49:21.216
King John was facing increasing pressure from his barons

01:49:21.216 --> 01:49:22.675
who were demanding greater rights

01:49:22.675 --> 01:49:24.341
and protections under the law.

01:49:24.341 --> 01:49:27.050
In response to their demands, John agreed to meet

01:49:27.050 --> 01:49:29.425
with the barons and negotiate a settlement.

01:49:29.425 --> 01:49:33.091
The result of these negotiations was the Magna Carta,

01:49:33.091 --> 01:49:35.591
a document that set out a series of rights

01:49:35.591 --> 01:49:38.675
and freedoms that the king could not violate.

01:49:38.675 --> 01:49:41.425
Among these rights were the right to a fair trial,

01:49:41.425 --> 01:49:43.550
the right to due process of law,

01:49:43.550 --> 01:49:45.050
and the right to be protected

01:49:45.050 --> 01:49:47.758
from arbitrary arrest and imprisonment.

01:49:47.758 --> 01:49:50.466
The Magna Carta also established the principle

01:49:50.466 --> 01:49:53.550
of habeas corpus, which required the government

01:49:53.550 --> 01:49:55.508
to produce a prisoner in court

01:49:55.508 --> 01:49:58.716
and provide a lawful reason for their detention.

01:49:58.716 --> 01:50:01.341
This principle has been a cornerstone

01:50:01.341 --> 01:50:04.383
of modern legal systems around the world.

01:50:05.841 --> 01:50:09.800
Then in 1217, there was another crusade.

01:50:09.800 --> 01:50:13.091
This time led by King Andrew II of Hungary

01:50:13.091 --> 01:50:15.591
and Duke Leopold VI of Austria,

01:50:15.591 --> 01:50:19.341
with the same goal in mind, to take over Jerusalem.

01:50:19.341 --> 01:50:22.383
The crusaders successfully captured the city of Damietta

01:50:22.383 --> 01:50:26.841
in 1219, but they could not advance further into Egypt.

01:50:26.841 --> 01:50:29.675
After a series of setbacks, including capture

01:50:29.675 --> 01:50:32.050
and imprisonment of many crusaders,

01:50:32.050 --> 01:50:34.133
the Christian forces were forced

01:50:34.133 --> 01:50:36.675
to abandon their campaign in Egypt.

01:50:36.675 --> 01:50:39.091
The crusaders eventually agreed to a treaty

01:50:39.091 --> 01:50:40.508
with the Muslim forces,

01:50:40.508 --> 01:50:42.966
allowing them to leave Egypt unharmed,

01:50:42.966 --> 01:50:45.633
but without achieving their ultimate goal.

01:50:47.216 --> 01:50:49.383
Genghis Khan wasn't done though.

01:50:49.383 --> 01:50:53.675
In 1219 went to war against the Khwarazmian Empire.

01:50:53.675 --> 01:50:55.675
In present day, Turkmenistan,

01:50:55.675 --> 01:50:58.841
Uzbekistan, Afghanistan, and Iran.

01:50:58.841 --> 01:51:02.383
During his raids, the Mongol horde swept through one city

01:51:02.383 --> 01:51:05.383
after another, taking over the likes of Bukhara,

01:51:05.383 --> 01:51:07.591
Samarkand and Urgench.

01:51:07.591 --> 01:51:09.508
Skilled workers, such as carpenters

01:51:09.508 --> 01:51:12.508
and jewelers were usually saved while aristocrats

01:51:12.508 --> 01:51:14.841
and resisting soldiers were killed.

01:51:14.841 --> 01:51:18.883
Unskilled workers meanwhile were often used as human shields

01:51:18.883 --> 01:51:20.383
during the next assault.

01:51:20.383 --> 01:51:23.883
No one knows with any certainty how many people died

01:51:23.883 --> 01:51:26.550
during Genghis Khan's wars, in part

01:51:26.550 --> 01:51:29.841
because the Mongols propagated their vicious image

01:51:29.841 --> 01:51:31.675
as a way of spreading terror.

01:51:31.675 --> 01:51:35.841
At Genghis Khan's death, he controlled a massive territory

01:51:35.841 --> 01:51:39.216
from the sea of Japan to the Caspian Sea.

01:51:39.216 --> 01:51:43.216
However, even more impressively, around 8%

01:51:43.216 --> 01:51:47.966
of the men in South Asia descend from Genghis Khan today.

01:51:49.675 --> 01:51:52.341
In 1228, Emperor Frederick II

01:51:52.341 --> 01:51:55.758
of the Holy Roman Empire tried to conquer the Holy land,

01:51:55.758 --> 01:51:59.216
but failed, ending the sixth crusade.

01:51:59.216 --> 01:52:01.800
Of course, the Holy Roman Empire couldn't be

01:52:01.800 --> 01:52:03.300
the only one crusading.

01:52:03.300 --> 01:52:06.966
King Louis IX of France in 1248 decided

01:52:06.966 --> 01:52:10.466
to start the seventh crusade to retake Jerusalem,

01:52:10.466 --> 01:52:12.800
but he was taken prisoner by the Muslims

01:52:12.800 --> 01:52:16.175
and forced to pay a hefty ransom as he retreated.

01:52:16.175 --> 01:52:18.925
However, that didn't deter King Louis IX,

01:52:18.925 --> 01:52:22.133
because in 1270, he was at it again,

01:52:22.133 --> 01:52:26.175
trying to free Jerusalem from the grips of Muslim rule.

01:52:26.175 --> 01:52:29.091
But this time, he died of dysentery.

01:52:29.091 --> 01:52:31.050
Once King Louis IX died,

01:52:31.050 --> 01:52:33.425
his troops retreated creating the eighth

01:52:33.425 --> 01:52:35.550
and final time there was a crusade.

01:52:36.633 --> 01:52:39.300
In England though in 1295,

01:52:39.300 --> 01:52:42.008
England was making a diplomatic headway.

01:52:42.008 --> 01:52:43.675
In a letter summoning Parliament,

01:52:43.675 --> 01:52:47.091
King Edward I wrote "since the most righteous law

01:52:47.091 --> 01:52:48.675
of the emperors ordains that

01:52:48.675 --> 01:52:51.591
what touches all should be approved by all.

01:52:51.591 --> 01:52:54.175
So it appears that common danger should be met

01:52:54.175 --> 01:52:56.883
by remedies agreed upon and common.

01:52:56.883 --> 01:52:58.216
As King Edward,

01:52:58.216 --> 01:53:01.550
I would then request a 10th of the incomes of nobles

01:53:01.550 --> 01:53:04.050
and an 11th of the income of knights,"

01:53:04.050 --> 01:53:07.258
creating one of the first parliaments we would see

01:53:07.258 --> 01:53:08.550
in the new age.

01:53:10.550 --> 01:53:14.175
While down in Africa, a leader of extravagant wealth,

01:53:14.175 --> 01:53:16.591
Mansa Musa, was gaining power.

01:53:16.591 --> 01:53:20.633
On his famous Hajj, a religious Muslim pilgrimage to Mecca

01:53:20.633 --> 01:53:23.966
that every Muslim should make at least once in his life.

01:53:23.966 --> 01:53:26.550
Mansa Musa with his caravan of camels

01:53:26.550 --> 01:53:29.883
and an army of scholars gave vast amounts of gold

01:53:29.883 --> 01:53:33.633
to any poor person he saw, hence crashing all

01:53:33.633 --> 01:53:36.008
of the economies in northern Africa

01:53:36.008 --> 01:53:38.175
due to the inflation of gold.

01:53:38.175 --> 01:53:40.258
When Mansa Musa returned to Mali,

01:53:40.258 --> 01:53:41.675
he made it his life purpose

01:53:41.675 --> 01:53:45.091
to make Timbuktu the Muslim capital of knowledge.

01:53:45.091 --> 01:53:47.425
So Mansa Musa invested heavily

01:53:47.425 --> 01:53:49.883
in building the University of SanKore.

01:53:49.883 --> 01:53:53.008
Various Islamic faith scholars quickly made their way

01:53:53.008 --> 01:53:56.550
to SanKore to study Islamic theology, law,

01:53:56.550 --> 01:54:00.508
and literature with over 1 million manuscripts.

01:54:00.508 --> 01:54:04.466
Mansa Musa was also a very religious man with a policy

01:54:04.466 --> 01:54:07.591
that he commissioned a new mosque every Friday.

01:54:07.591 --> 01:54:09.091
However, sadly though,

01:54:09.091 --> 01:54:12.716
only the Djingareyber Mosque in Timbuktu stood the test

01:54:12.716 --> 01:54:13.550
of time.

01:54:18.466 --> 01:54:19.841
In the Americas though

01:54:19.841 --> 01:54:23.008
another built on riches was being created.

01:54:23.008 --> 01:54:24.925
As Aztec legend has it,

01:54:24.925 --> 01:54:28.341
the God Huitzilopochtli directed them to build

01:54:28.341 --> 01:54:31.050
where they saw an eagle perched on a cactus,

01:54:31.050 --> 01:54:32.258
eating a snake.

01:54:32.258 --> 01:54:35.216
When they saw this exact scene on an island located

01:54:35.216 --> 01:54:38.425
in what was once Lake Texcoco, they interpreted it

01:54:38.425 --> 01:54:40.300
as a sign from their God

01:54:40.300 --> 01:54:43.341
and founded Tenochtitlan on that island.

01:54:43.341 --> 01:54:45.716
As time passed, Tenochtitlan started

01:54:45.716 --> 01:54:48.841
to build impressive temples such as The Great Temple.

01:54:48.841 --> 01:54:52.716
The Great Temple comprised of two main structures dedicated

01:54:52.716 --> 01:54:56.008
to the gods Huitzilopochtli and Tlaloc.

01:54:56.008 --> 01:54:58.508
The city itself was most fascinating.

01:54:58.508 --> 01:55:01.425
It was designed with a complex system of canals

01:55:01.425 --> 01:55:03.966
and causeways to help control flooding

01:55:03.966 --> 01:55:06.800
and facilitate transport across the city.

01:55:06.800 --> 01:55:09.300
While they started to farm on floating gardens,

01:55:09.300 --> 01:55:11.841
known as chinampas on the shallow waters

01:55:11.841 --> 01:55:14.216
of Lake Texcoco, which were used

01:55:14.216 --> 01:55:18.175
to grow crops such as maize, beans, and squash.

01:55:20.008 --> 01:55:23.091
As Mali and the Aztecs were building their cities,

01:55:23.091 --> 01:55:26.758
England and France were in war for 100 years,

01:55:26.758 --> 01:55:29.341
the origins of the conflict lay with the status

01:55:29.341 --> 01:55:30.925
of the duchy of Guyenne.

01:55:30.925 --> 01:55:33.258
In basic capitalistic terms,

01:55:33.258 --> 01:55:35.508
this was owned by the British crown.

01:55:35.508 --> 01:55:38.425
However, the land itself was in France.

01:55:38.425 --> 01:55:41.341
The second reason was that the last direct descendant

01:55:41.341 --> 01:55:46.300
of Charlemagne, King Charles IV died in 1328.

01:55:46.300 --> 01:55:48.716
So the next closest relative was Edward III

01:55:49.550 --> 01:55:50.633
the King of England.

01:55:50.633 --> 01:55:55.633
So King Edward III claimed the rule of France in 1337,

01:55:55.925 --> 01:55:58.466
which was not liked by the French people.

01:55:59.508 --> 01:56:03.425
As the petty erratic Hundred Years War raged on,

01:56:03.425 --> 01:56:04.716
the people of the world had

01:56:04.716 --> 01:56:07.466
to face a pandemic like no other,

01:56:07.466 --> 01:56:09.175
the bubonic plague.

01:56:09.175 --> 01:56:12.341
As the Italian poet Giovanni Boccaccio wrote.

01:56:12.341 --> 01:56:14.216
"At the beginning of the malady,

01:56:14.216 --> 01:56:16.591
certain swellings either on the groin

01:56:16.591 --> 01:56:19.591
or under the armpits, waxed to the bigness

01:56:19.591 --> 01:56:23.841
of a common apple, others to the size of an egg, some more

01:56:23.841 --> 01:56:28.800
and some less, and these the vulgar named plague boils."

01:56:28.800 --> 01:56:31.091
Historians believe this pandemic was spread

01:56:31.091 --> 01:56:33.925
by rats traveling through ships across Europe

01:56:33.925 --> 01:56:36.300
and merchants throughout the Silk Road.

01:56:36.300 --> 01:56:39.216
No matter how this plague was produced, around 75

01:56:39.216 --> 01:56:42.591
to 200 million people died,

01:56:42.591 --> 01:56:44.550
with the death of so many people,

01:56:44.550 --> 01:56:46.716
especially the poor, landowners

01:56:46.716 --> 01:56:50.050
and nobles were required to allow farmers to keep more

01:56:50.050 --> 01:56:54.008
of the product they farmed, leading to more workers' rights.

01:56:55.883 --> 01:56:58.258
In China, though a group of rebels known

01:56:58.258 --> 01:57:00.133
as The Red Turbans revolted

01:57:00.133 --> 01:57:02.591
against the Mongol rulers of China.

01:57:02.591 --> 01:57:06.008
The Red Turbans were led by a man named Zhu Yuanzhang,

01:57:06.008 --> 01:57:08.425
born into a poor peasant family.

01:57:08.425 --> 01:57:12.091
Zhu built a strong following among the rebel forces

01:57:12.091 --> 01:57:14.258
and eventually emerged as their leader.

01:57:14.258 --> 01:57:18.383
In 1368, Zhu declared himself emperor

01:57:18.383 --> 01:57:20.675
and established the Ming Dynasty,

01:57:20.675 --> 01:57:24.508
marking the beginning of a new era in Chinese history.

01:57:30.383 --> 01:57:35.383
In 1428, at the age of 16, Joan left her home in the village

01:57:35.383 --> 01:57:38.925
of Domremy, and traveled to the court of Charles VII

01:57:38.925 --> 01:57:40.341
where she asked for permission

01:57:40.341 --> 01:57:43.341
to lead the French army against the English.

01:57:43.341 --> 01:57:47.466
At first, her request was met with skepticism and disbelief.

01:57:47.466 --> 01:57:51.175
Still, Joan persisted and eventually won the support

01:57:51.175 --> 01:57:52.883
of the French Commanders.

01:57:52.883 --> 01:57:56.633
Joan's first major military victory came in the Siege

01:57:56.633 --> 01:58:01.341
of Orleans in 1429, she led the French troops in a series

01:58:01.341 --> 01:58:04.216
of daring attacks on the English forces,

01:58:04.216 --> 01:58:07.216
and she broke the siege and liberated the city.

01:58:07.216 --> 01:58:09.675
This victory boosted French morale

01:58:09.675 --> 01:58:13.133
and helped to turn the tide of the war in their favor.

01:58:13.133 --> 01:58:15.883
Over the next several months, Joan led the French army

01:58:15.883 --> 01:58:17.966
to victories against the English,

01:58:17.966 --> 01:58:22.050
including the Battle of Patay in June 1429.

01:58:22.050 --> 01:58:25.050
However, her success also made her enemies

01:58:25.050 --> 01:58:27.091
in the English and French court.

01:58:27.091 --> 01:58:30.383
In 1430, she was captured by the English

01:58:30.383 --> 01:58:33.508
and put on trial for heresy and witchcraft.

01:58:33.508 --> 01:58:36.508
Joan was subjected to a grueling trial.

01:58:36.508 --> 01:58:39.091
She was accused of various crimes,

01:58:39.091 --> 01:58:41.341
including dressing in men's clothing,

01:58:41.341 --> 01:58:44.841
practicing sorcery, and hearing voices.

01:58:44.841 --> 01:58:46.633
Despite the odds against her,

01:58:46.633 --> 01:58:49.675
Joan remained steadfast in her faith

01:58:49.675 --> 01:58:53.008
and her belief that she was carrying out God's will.

01:58:53.008 --> 01:58:55.216
In the end, Joan was found guilty

01:58:55.216 --> 01:58:58.383
and sentenced to death by burning at stake.

01:58:58.383 --> 01:59:03.383
She was executed on May 30th, 1431 at 19.

01:59:03.591 --> 01:59:06.883
Then 20 years later, in the Battle of Castilian,

01:59:06.883 --> 01:59:09.925
Charles II of France led a French army,

01:59:09.925 --> 01:59:12.216
which defeated the English army,

01:59:12.216 --> 01:59:16.591
effectively ending English territorial claims in France.

01:59:18.508 --> 01:59:21.175
While back in the great city of Constantinople,

01:59:21.175 --> 01:59:23.716
the Byzantine Empire was declining,

01:59:23.716 --> 01:59:25.716
weakened by years of war,

01:59:25.716 --> 01:59:29.175
political instability and economic turmoil.

01:59:29.175 --> 01:59:31.341
In contrast, the Ottoman Empire

01:59:31.341 --> 01:59:34.675
led by Sultan Mehmed II was on the rise,

01:59:34.675 --> 01:59:38.133
and Sultan saw an opportunity to expand his empire

01:59:38.133 --> 01:59:42.591
and gained control of the strategic city of Constantinople.

01:59:42.591 --> 01:59:46.050
By 1453, Mehmed II led an army

01:59:46.050 --> 01:59:51.050
of 80,000 soldiers, including elite janissary troops

01:59:51.175 --> 01:59:55.675
and a powerful artillery force to besiege Constantinople.

01:59:55.675 --> 01:59:57.383
The Byzantine defenders led

01:59:57.383 --> 02:00:00.383
by Emperor Constantine XI were

02:00:00.383 --> 02:00:02.925
vastly outnumbered and outgunned.

02:00:02.925 --> 02:00:05.800
They faced a seemingly impossible task

02:00:05.800 --> 02:00:07.800
to hold off the Ottoman assault.

02:00:07.800 --> 02:00:10.300
The Ottomans bombarded the city with artillery

02:00:10.300 --> 02:00:14.216
for nearly two months, causing extensive damage to the walls

02:00:14.216 --> 02:00:15.841
and fortifications.

02:00:15.841 --> 02:00:18.591
The Byzantine defenders meanwhile struggled

02:00:18.591 --> 02:00:22.383
to maintain morale and keep their troops fed and supplied.

02:00:22.383 --> 02:00:26.508
Then on the fateful day, May 29th, 1453,

02:00:26.508 --> 02:00:29.675
the Ottomans launched a massive assault on the city,

02:00:29.675 --> 02:00:32.633
climbing up covered by siege towers,

02:00:32.633 --> 02:00:34.466
they were able to breach the walls

02:00:34.466 --> 02:00:36.550
and gain access to the city.

02:00:36.550 --> 02:00:38.966
Despite putting up a valiant defense,

02:00:38.966 --> 02:00:41.841
the Byzantine defenders were overwhelmed,

02:00:41.841 --> 02:00:44.300
and the Ottomans were able to storm the city

02:00:44.300 --> 02:00:48.675
and capture the capitol causing the great Byzantine empire

02:00:48.675 --> 02:00:53.675
to fall, in 1453, all paths no longer led to Rome

02:00:54.425 --> 02:00:58.800
and all traces back to the empire of Caesar were erased.

02:00:58.800 --> 02:01:00.383
It was replaced by the beginning

02:01:00.383 --> 02:01:03.925
of utter Ottoman domination in the region,

02:01:03.925 --> 02:01:07.133
ushering in a new era of Turkish power

02:01:07.133 --> 02:01:09.466
and influence in the Mediterranean.

02:01:11.466 --> 02:01:13.883
While the Byzantines might have been falling,

02:01:13.883 --> 02:01:17.425
the Russians were finally gaining their independence.

02:01:17.425 --> 02:01:21.175
At the time, the Mongol Empire was ruling over Russia,

02:01:21.175 --> 02:01:23.966
demanding that various Russian towns pay tribute

02:01:23.966 --> 02:01:26.633
or face the wrath of the Mongols.

02:01:26.633 --> 02:01:30.383
However, in 1472, Ivan the Great refused

02:01:30.383 --> 02:01:31.841
to pay such tribute.

02:01:31.841 --> 02:01:33.300
Over the next several years,

02:01:33.300 --> 02:01:35.675
he built up his military strength

02:01:35.675 --> 02:01:38.550
and was able to drive out the Mongol garrisons

02:01:38.550 --> 02:01:41.508
from various cities and towns throughout Russia.

02:01:41.508 --> 02:01:45.591
In 1480, the Mongols demanded that Ivan pay tribute

02:01:45.591 --> 02:01:47.550
or face military action,

02:01:47.550 --> 02:01:51.133
but after a tense standoff, they finally retreated.

02:01:51.133 --> 02:01:54.383
Ivan's victory was the beginning of a free Russia

02:01:54.383 --> 02:01:57.508
and the a decline of the Mongolian empire.

02:01:59.341 --> 02:02:04.341
Then in 1492, as Christopher Columbus sailed the ocean blue,

02:02:04.341 --> 02:02:07.508
the Europeans discovered the new world.

02:02:07.508 --> 02:02:10.091
Set initially on finding a path to India,

02:02:10.091 --> 02:02:13.091
instead, he landed on an island in The Bahamas,

02:02:13.091 --> 02:02:15.966
which he aptly named San Salvador.

02:02:15.966 --> 02:02:18.050
When he and his crew set up camp,

02:02:18.050 --> 02:02:20.841
he met the Lucayans, skilled fishermen

02:02:20.841 --> 02:02:23.800
and farmers who welcomed him and his crew

02:02:23.800 --> 02:02:26.550
and provided them with food and supplies.

02:02:32.508 --> 02:02:36.508
While back in Europe, a golden age of culture was upon us.

02:02:36.508 --> 02:02:40.716
In 1503, Leonardo da Vinci painted the Mona Lisa.

02:02:40.716 --> 02:02:43.883
Da Vinci's biographer, Walter Isaacson says,

02:02:43.883 --> 02:02:47.675
"the Mona Lisa to me is the greatest emotional painting

02:02:47.675 --> 02:02:48.675
ever done.

02:02:48.675 --> 02:02:50.883
The way the smile flickers makes it a work

02:02:50.883 --> 02:02:52.258
of art and science,

02:02:52.258 --> 02:02:56.341
because Leonardo understood optics, the muscles of the lips

02:02:56.341 --> 02:02:58.258
and how light strikes the eye,

02:02:58.258 --> 02:03:00.841
all of it goes into making the Mona Lisa smile

02:03:00.841 --> 02:03:03.300
so mysterious and elusive."

02:03:03.300 --> 02:03:07.050
In 1504, Michelangelo sculpted David,

02:03:07.050 --> 02:03:08.675
Michelangelo would say,

02:03:08.675 --> 02:03:12.591
"in every block of marble I see a statue as plain

02:03:12.591 --> 02:03:16.758
as though it stood before me, shaped in perfect in attitude

02:03:16.758 --> 02:03:20.300
and action, I have only to (indistinct) away the rough walls

02:03:20.300 --> 02:03:23.216
that imprisoned the lovely apparition to reveal it

02:03:23.216 --> 02:03:25.800
to the other eyes as mine see it.

02:03:25.800 --> 02:03:27.591
While in 1506,

02:03:27.591 --> 02:03:30.716
Michelangelo was painting the magnificent painting

02:03:30.716 --> 02:03:32.591
of the Sistine Chapel.

02:03:36.758 --> 02:03:40.591
While in the political world, Niccolo Machiavelli is one

02:03:40.591 --> 02:03:43.466
of, if not the most influential pieces

02:03:43.466 --> 02:03:45.425
of literature we have today.

02:03:45.425 --> 02:03:48.175
"The Prince" is a political manifesto

02:03:48.175 --> 02:03:51.258
that comments on the past civilizations we've heard about

02:03:51.258 --> 02:03:52.425
in this video.

02:03:52.425 --> 02:03:53.675
Machiavelli writes,

02:03:53.675 --> 02:03:56.341
"it is much safer to be feared than loved

02:03:56.341 --> 02:04:00.758
because love is preserved by the link of obligation,

02:04:00.758 --> 02:04:02.341
which owing to the beastness

02:04:02.341 --> 02:04:06.591
of men is broken at every opportunity for their advantage.

02:04:06.591 --> 02:04:09.758
But fear preserves you by a dread of punishment,

02:04:09.758 --> 02:04:11.550
which never fails."

02:04:11.550 --> 02:04:13.425
Think about the ordinary farmer.

02:04:13.425 --> 02:04:15.716
Think about the man who spends generations

02:04:15.716 --> 02:04:19.383
of their life farming, giving heavy taxes to a noble lord

02:04:19.383 --> 02:04:21.758
for doing nothing except protecting them.

02:04:21.758 --> 02:04:23.425
Why won't the farmers rebel?

02:04:23.425 --> 02:04:25.008
It's because they're afraid

02:04:25.008 --> 02:04:27.383
of what would happen without their leaders.

02:04:27.383 --> 02:04:29.550
Without the elites, the Huns

02:04:29.550 --> 02:04:31.633
or the Mongols can come to your farm

02:04:31.633 --> 02:04:34.383
and destroy you on their own, so you live in fear

02:04:34.383 --> 02:04:36.300
as to what might happen to you,

02:04:36.300 --> 02:04:38.925
leaving you to give your wheat to said leader.

02:04:44.216 --> 02:04:46.508
Martin Luther, though didn't just report

02:04:46.508 --> 02:04:48.425
on the basics of human nature.

02:04:48.425 --> 02:04:50.216
Martin wanted to make a difference

02:04:50.216 --> 02:04:52.300
and was sick of the Catholic church.

02:04:52.300 --> 02:04:55.675
At the time, the Catholic Church was selling indulgences,

02:04:55.675 --> 02:04:56.883
which were certificates

02:04:56.883 --> 02:04:59.300
that people could purchase to reduce the amount

02:04:59.300 --> 02:05:03.050
of time they would spend in purgatory after they died.

02:05:03.050 --> 02:05:05.425
Luther believed this practice was corrupt

02:05:05.425 --> 02:05:07.591
and went against the Bible's teachings,

02:05:07.591 --> 02:05:10.091
which emphasized the importance of repentance

02:05:10.091 --> 02:05:12.591
and faith over material wealth.

02:05:12.591 --> 02:05:16.466
In protest, he wrote a series of 95 thesis

02:05:16.466 --> 02:05:19.716
or arguments challenging the church's authority

02:05:19.716 --> 02:05:21.425
and calling for reform.

02:05:21.425 --> 02:05:24.300
On October 31st, 1517,

02:05:24.300 --> 02:05:27.508
Luther nailed his 95 thesis to the door

02:05:27.508 --> 02:05:30.966
of the Castle Church in Wittenberg, which was a common way

02:05:30.966 --> 02:05:34.300
of announcing a public debate or discussion.

02:05:34.300 --> 02:05:37.925
Luther's 95 thesis sparked a debate within the church

02:05:37.925 --> 02:05:41.008
and among European scholars and theologies.

02:05:41.008 --> 02:05:43.966
Some people agreed with his criticisms of the church,

02:05:43.966 --> 02:05:45.758
while others saw him as a heretic

02:05:45.758 --> 02:05:48.008
and a threat to the established order.

02:05:48.008 --> 02:05:51.425
The beginning of Protestantism was upon us.

02:05:55.800 --> 02:05:59.300
In 1519, though the Spanish conquistadors

02:05:59.300 --> 02:06:02.300
under the leadership of Hernan Cortez arrived

02:06:02.300 --> 02:06:03.925
on the Aztec shores.

02:06:03.925 --> 02:06:07.341
They were greeted by the Aztecs who gave gifts of gold

02:06:07.341 --> 02:06:10.425
and silver of incredible wealth to the Spanish

02:06:10.425 --> 02:06:13.258
as they believed that the Spaniards were emissaries

02:06:13.258 --> 02:06:15.008
of the God Quetzalcoatl.

02:06:15.008 --> 02:06:18.966
However, Cortez soon revealed his true intentions

02:06:18.966 --> 02:06:23.716
to conquer the Aztec empire and claim its wealth for Spain.

02:06:23.716 --> 02:06:25.800
Over several years, Cortez

02:06:25.800 --> 02:06:28.258
and his forces engaged in a series of battles

02:06:28.258 --> 02:06:32.716
with the Aztecs, marked by intense violence and brutality.

02:06:32.716 --> 02:06:33.925
The Spanish were aided

02:06:33.925 --> 02:06:37.550
by their superior military technology, including guns

02:06:37.550 --> 02:06:41.175
and cannons, and by the support of indigenous allies

02:06:41.175 --> 02:06:43.425
who were the enemies of the Aztecs.

02:06:43.425 --> 02:06:45.633
Despite being vastly outnumbered,

02:06:45.633 --> 02:06:48.383
Cortez and his men made significant gains

02:06:48.383 --> 02:06:49.925
against the Aztecs,

02:06:49.925 --> 02:06:51.508
eventually laying siege

02:06:51.508 --> 02:06:54.341
to their capital city of Tenochtitlan,

02:06:54.341 --> 02:06:56.758
after months of fighting, the city fell

02:06:56.758 --> 02:06:59.300
to the Spanish in 1521,

02:06:59.300 --> 02:07:02.966
and the Aztec Empire was effectively destroyed.

02:07:02.966 --> 02:07:05.758
Then following the strategy of Cortez,

02:07:05.758 --> 02:07:08.550
Francisco Pizarro led an expedition

02:07:08.550 --> 02:07:12.800
that conquered the Incan empire in present day Peru.

02:07:12.800 --> 02:07:15.091
Though the violence was authoritarian,

02:07:15.091 --> 02:07:18.175
the biohazards were even more demanding.

02:07:18.175 --> 02:07:21.425
The Europeans due to having survived illnesses such

02:07:21.425 --> 02:07:24.800
as the bubonic plague and smallpox developed immunity

02:07:24.800 --> 02:07:27.841
to many of these diseases that they've one way

02:07:27.841 --> 02:07:30.591
or another spread to the native people,

02:07:30.591 --> 02:07:33.341
essentially over time, killing them off.

02:07:38.341 --> 02:07:41.091
Under Suleiman the Magnificent's leadership,

02:07:41.091 --> 02:07:44.008
the Ottoman Empire became one of the most powerful

02:07:44.008 --> 02:07:46.675
and influential empires in world history.

02:07:46.675 --> 02:07:50.508
Suleiman was a brilliant strategist and military leader,

02:07:50.508 --> 02:07:53.550
and his reign was marked by significant conquests

02:07:53.550 --> 02:07:55.466
and political achievements.

02:07:55.466 --> 02:07:59.466
Like many other leaders, he set out to conquer the world.

02:07:59.466 --> 02:08:00.675
By the end of his reign,

02:08:00.675 --> 02:08:04.633
Suleiman the Magnificent presided over a vast empire

02:08:04.633 --> 02:08:07.591
that stretched from southeastern Europe to the deserts

02:08:07.591 --> 02:08:10.675
of Arabia and from the shores of the Mediterranean

02:08:10.675 --> 02:08:12.675
to the plains of Persia.

02:08:12.675 --> 02:08:15.425
His conquests included the capture of Belgrade

02:08:15.425 --> 02:08:16.925
and Budapest in Europe,

02:08:16.925 --> 02:08:19.425
Jerusalem, and Mecca in the Middle East,

02:08:19.425 --> 02:08:21.966
and Tabriz and Baghdad in Persia.

02:08:21.966 --> 02:08:25.550
The Ottomans also became the dominant naval power

02:08:25.550 --> 02:08:29.258
in the Mediterranean with control over North African cities,

02:08:29.258 --> 02:08:31.258
such as Algiers and Tunisia,

02:08:31.258 --> 02:08:34.675
creating the dominant Ottoman civilization.

02:08:40.050 --> 02:08:43.925
But yet all things fall when one is in love.

02:08:43.925 --> 02:08:46.841
And the murder happy King Henry had fallen

02:08:46.841 --> 02:08:48.425
in love with Anne Boleyn

02:08:48.425 --> 02:08:50.508
and was desperate to marry her.

02:08:50.508 --> 02:08:53.300
However, Catherine of Aragon was still alive

02:08:53.300 --> 02:08:56.883
and the Catholic church did not recognize divorce.

02:08:56.883 --> 02:09:00.133
Henry's solution was to break away from the Catholic church

02:09:00.133 --> 02:09:02.550
and established the Church of England

02:09:02.550 --> 02:09:04.466
with himself as the head.

02:09:04.466 --> 02:09:09.383
In 1534, Henry passed the Act of Supremacy, which declared

02:09:09.383 --> 02:09:12.758
that the king, not the Pope, was the supreme head

02:09:12.758 --> 02:09:15.716
of the Church of England, leaving the Catholic church

02:09:15.716 --> 02:09:20.091
to be angry and excommunicate Henry VII leaving a schism

02:09:20.091 --> 02:09:21.716
between the Church of England

02:09:21.716 --> 02:09:24.508
and the Catholic church, even today.

02:09:29.008 --> 02:09:32.008
Ivan the Terrible is now the ruler of Russia.

02:09:32.008 --> 02:09:33.841
In the early years of his reign,

02:09:33.841 --> 02:09:36.300
Ivan enjoyed significant success,

02:09:36.300 --> 02:09:39.591
launching military campaigns against neighboring kingdoms

02:09:39.591 --> 02:09:41.758
and expanding Russia's borders.

02:09:41.758 --> 02:09:43.675
He also oversaw the construction

02:09:43.675 --> 02:09:46.091
of magnificent public works,

02:09:46.091 --> 02:09:49.258
including St. Basil's Cathedral in Moscow.

02:09:49.258 --> 02:09:52.050
However, as Ivan grew older,

02:09:52.050 --> 02:09:55.216
he became increasingly paranoid and erratic.

02:09:55.216 --> 02:09:57.675
He launched a series of brutal purges

02:09:57.675 --> 02:10:01.175
and executions targeting anyone he perceived

02:10:01.175 --> 02:10:02.800
as threatening his power.

02:10:02.800 --> 02:10:06.508
He also had a volatile temper, lashing out at advisors

02:10:06.508 --> 02:10:09.550
and nobles who dared to question his decisions.

02:10:09.550 --> 02:10:11.133
In 1560,

02:10:11.133 --> 02:10:14.216
Ivan suffered a devastating personal loss

02:10:14.216 --> 02:10:17.008
when his beloved wife Anastasia died.

02:10:17.008 --> 02:10:18.383
This event seems

02:10:18.383 --> 02:10:22.133
to have triggered a significant psychological breakdown,

02:10:22.133 --> 02:10:25.883
and Ivan became increasingly unstable and violent.

02:10:25.883 --> 02:10:26.966
He launched a series

02:10:26.966 --> 02:10:29.841
of bloody campaigns against his own people,

02:10:29.841 --> 02:10:32.508
including the notorious oprichnina,

02:10:32.508 --> 02:10:35.216
a campaign of terror and repression

02:10:35.216 --> 02:10:37.591
that killed thousands of Russians

02:10:37.591 --> 02:10:39.300
and destroyed countless homes

02:10:39.300 --> 02:10:43.508
and families, truly deserving of the name terrible.

02:10:47.883 --> 02:10:51.258
While Russia was going through that, England was on the rise

02:10:51.258 --> 02:10:53.550
with the start of the English renaissance.

02:10:53.550 --> 02:10:56.466
Under the leadership of Queen Elizabeth I,

02:10:56.466 --> 02:10:59.633
Elizabethan playwrights dominated the scene,

02:10:59.633 --> 02:11:02.633
creating written words that were poetic in language

02:11:02.633 --> 02:11:03.966
and poignant in meaning.

02:11:03.966 --> 02:11:05.758
They've even written plays about people

02:11:05.758 --> 02:11:07.258
we've already talked about.

02:11:07.258 --> 02:11:10.841
William Shakespeare wrote many plays including histories.

02:11:10.841 --> 02:11:13.633
Julius Caesar, which was about the assassination

02:11:13.633 --> 02:11:15.175
of Julius Caesar,

02:11:15.175 --> 02:11:18.383
King John, which was about the A Hundred Years War,

02:11:18.383 --> 02:11:20.383
and Henry VII was a play

02:11:20.383 --> 02:11:23.300
about showing human needs to gain power.

02:11:23.300 --> 02:11:24.550
Other notable playwrights

02:11:24.550 --> 02:11:26.966
who filled the scene were Christopher Marlowe,

02:11:26.966 --> 02:11:29.133
Ben Johnson and John Webster.

02:11:33.883 --> 02:11:37.050
While on the other side of the world, the English colony

02:11:37.050 --> 02:11:39.591
of Jamestown was forming in Virginia,

02:11:39.591 --> 02:11:43.050
under the Virginia Trading Company, slightly up north,

02:11:43.050 --> 02:11:46.675
Samuel de Champlain was establishing the French colony

02:11:46.675 --> 02:11:48.591
of Quebec in Canada.

02:11:53.341 --> 02:11:56.966
While back in the old world, they were having a new era

02:11:56.966 --> 02:12:00.008
of fighting, The 30 Years War.

02:12:00.008 --> 02:12:03.800
This time, it was between the Protestants and the Catholics.

02:12:03.800 --> 02:12:08.008
It began in 1618 when the Holy Roman Emperor attempted

02:12:08.008 --> 02:12:09.633
to impose Catholicism

02:12:09.633 --> 02:12:12.591
on the Protestant population of Bohemia.

02:12:12.591 --> 02:12:14.258
The Bohemians rebelled,

02:12:14.258 --> 02:12:17.425
and soon the conflict spread throughout the region.

02:12:17.425 --> 02:12:20.341
Over the next 30 years, armies marched

02:12:20.341 --> 02:12:22.425
and counter marched across Europe,

02:12:22.425 --> 02:12:26.091
leaving a trail of destruction and devastation.

02:12:26.091 --> 02:12:29.425
The war was characterized by brutal sieges,

02:12:29.425 --> 02:12:33.175
bloody battles, and atrocities committed by both sides.

02:12:33.175 --> 02:12:36.716
At its height, the war involved most of the major powers

02:12:36.716 --> 02:12:39.216
of Europe, including France, Spain,

02:12:39.216 --> 02:12:41.841
Sweden, and the Holy Roman Empire.

02:12:41.841 --> 02:12:44.341
It was fought along religious, political,

02:12:44.341 --> 02:12:47.341
and economic lines with each side vying

02:12:47.341 --> 02:12:49.258
for dominance and control.

02:12:49.258 --> 02:12:53.300
The war finally ended in 1648 with the signing

02:12:53.300 --> 02:12:55.258
of the Peace of Westphalia.

02:12:55.258 --> 02:12:58.508
The treaty recognized the Dutch Republic's independence,

02:12:58.508 --> 02:13:00.841
established the individual state sovereignty

02:13:00.841 --> 02:13:02.800
within the Holy Roman empire

02:13:02.800 --> 02:13:06.633
and ended the religious conflicts that fueled the war.

02:13:11.758 --> 02:13:15.300
While in China, the Ming Court was plagued by corruption,

02:13:15.300 --> 02:13:18.008
factionalism, and economic decline.

02:13:18.008 --> 02:13:21.508
The emperor at the time, Chongzhen, faced mounting pressure

02:13:21.508 --> 02:13:24.300
from his advisors to strengthen the military

02:13:24.300 --> 02:13:26.550
and defend against the Manchu threat.

02:13:26.550 --> 02:13:29.258
However, his efforts were hindered by infighting

02:13:29.258 --> 02:13:32.175
among officials and a lack of resources.

02:13:32.175 --> 02:13:35.216
In 1644, the Manchu army led

02:13:35.216 --> 02:13:39.300
by Prince Dorgon launched a massive invasion of China.

02:13:39.300 --> 02:13:42.008
The Ming Army weakened by years of neglect

02:13:42.008 --> 02:13:44.841
and corruption, was no match for the highly disciplined

02:13:44.841 --> 02:13:47.216
and skilled Manchu forces.

02:13:47.216 --> 02:13:49.758
The Manchus quickly conquered Beijing

02:13:49.758 --> 02:13:53.466
and installed their puppet emperor, ending the Ming Dynasty,

02:13:53.466 --> 02:13:56.758
continuing the cycle of dynasties in China.

02:14:02.758 --> 02:14:06.383
While in Spain, King Charles II died without having

02:14:06.383 --> 02:14:09.883
any heirs, creating a real political crisis

02:14:09.883 --> 02:14:11.633
of who should be the leader.

02:14:11.633 --> 02:14:15.925
King Louis XIV of France supported his grandson, Philip,

02:14:15.925 --> 02:14:19.050
as the rightful heir to the Spanish throne, hoping

02:14:19.050 --> 02:14:22.966
to secure French influence over Spain and its territories.

02:14:22.966 --> 02:14:26.425
On the other hand, Emperor Leopold I of Austria,

02:14:26.425 --> 02:14:29.758
supported the candidacy of Archduke Charles,

02:14:29.758 --> 02:14:32.758
a member of the Habsburg dynasty, who was seen

02:14:32.758 --> 02:14:36.466
as a potential ally against French expansionism.

02:14:36.466 --> 02:14:39.716
The conflict soon escalated into a major war

02:14:39.716 --> 02:14:42.258
with many European powers taking sides,

02:14:42.258 --> 02:14:43.925
and forming alliances.

02:14:43.925 --> 02:14:46.716
The principle belligerents were France and Spain

02:14:46.716 --> 02:14:48.758
against a coalition of Austria,

02:14:48.758 --> 02:14:51.008
Great Britain, the Dutch Republic,

02:14:51.008 --> 02:14:54.175
Portugal, and several other minor powers.

02:14:54.175 --> 02:14:58.550
The war ended with the Treaty of Utrecht in 1713,

02:14:58.550 --> 02:15:01.466
which recognized Philip as King of Spain.

02:15:01.466 --> 02:15:05.300
Bud required him to renounce any claims to the French throne

02:15:05.300 --> 02:15:09.300
and cede some territories to Great Britain and Austria.

02:15:09.300 --> 02:15:12.091
The Treaty of Rastatt signed the following year

02:15:12.091 --> 02:15:14.133
officially ended the war.

02:15:18.675 --> 02:15:21.925
In 1707, the Acts of the Union were passed

02:15:21.925 --> 02:15:24.550
by the parliaments of England and Scotland,

02:15:24.550 --> 02:15:28.133
which united the two kingdoms into a single political entity

02:15:28.133 --> 02:15:31.800
known as Great Britain, hence creating the legal foothold,

02:15:31.800 --> 02:15:33.300
that is Great Britain.

02:15:33.300 --> 02:15:36.050
However, Scotland took a disliking to this.

02:15:36.050 --> 02:15:37.133
There were protests

02:15:37.133 --> 02:15:40.050
and uprisings in the years following the union,

02:15:40.050 --> 02:15:42.841
including the Jacobite Risings of 1715

02:15:44.050 --> 02:15:48.633
and 1745, which aimed to restore the Scottish monarchy

02:15:48.633 --> 02:15:50.216
and independence.

02:15:56.341 --> 02:16:00.841
Then on July 4th, 1776, a group

02:16:00.841 --> 02:16:04.341
of American patriots stood in a room in Philadelphia signing

02:16:04.341 --> 02:16:07.883
a document that would say the words "we hold these truths

02:16:07.883 --> 02:16:11.341
to be self-evident, that all men are created equal,

02:16:11.341 --> 02:16:13.341
that they are endowed by their creator

02:16:13.341 --> 02:16:17.300
with certain unalienable rights, that among these are life,

02:16:17.300 --> 02:16:20.008
liberty, and the pursuit of happiness."

02:16:20.008 --> 02:16:22.925
War in the Americas was on.

02:16:27.383 --> 02:16:30.425
But back in Europe, the tone was quite different.

02:16:30.425 --> 02:16:32.383
Adam Smith published the famous book,

02:16:32.383 --> 02:16:34.133
"The Wealth of Nations,"

02:16:34.133 --> 02:16:37.550
the foundations of laissez-faire economics,

02:16:37.550 --> 02:16:40.258
which essentially says the market would balance itself

02:16:40.258 --> 02:16:41.758
out over time.

02:16:41.758 --> 02:16:45.383
In Austria, Mozart was performing his Magnum opus,

02:16:45.383 --> 02:16:47.300
the Haffner Serenade.

02:16:47.300 --> 02:16:50.091
Mozart's Haffner Serenade is a charming

02:16:50.091 --> 02:16:52.966
and elegant work featuring courtly dance music

02:16:52.966 --> 02:16:55.091
and light lyrical melodies.

02:16:55.091 --> 02:16:57.716
Its graceful melodies, subtle harmonies,

02:16:57.716 --> 02:17:00.841
and elegant instrumental writing characterize it.

02:17:05.675 --> 02:17:07.341
As the war continued,

02:17:07.341 --> 02:17:09.508
King George III sent his armies

02:17:09.508 --> 02:17:11.591
of the masses over to America.

02:17:11.591 --> 02:17:14.508
Though the colonists had little military training,

02:17:14.508 --> 02:17:15.883
their knowledge of the terrain

02:17:15.883 --> 02:17:19.341
and guerrilla tactics made them nearly invisible.

02:17:19.341 --> 02:17:22.300
At the same time, the red army coats were easy

02:17:22.300 --> 02:17:24.216
to see for the Americans.

02:17:24.216 --> 02:17:27.383
In the summer of 1781, George Washington

02:17:27.383 --> 02:17:30.841
and French General Rochambeau marched their forces south

02:17:30.841 --> 02:17:33.008
to Virginia, where they laid siege

02:17:33.008 --> 02:17:36.175
to Cornwallis and his army at Yorktown.

02:17:36.175 --> 02:17:37.508
The British were trapped

02:17:37.508 --> 02:17:40.758
and could not escape by land or sea.

02:17:40.758 --> 02:17:43.300
The siege dragged on for weeks.

02:17:43.300 --> 02:17:46.341
The American and French forces bombarded the British

02:17:46.341 --> 02:17:47.675
with artillery.

02:17:47.675 --> 02:17:50.216
They dug trenches to inch their way closer

02:17:50.216 --> 02:17:51.466
to the British defensive.

02:17:51.466 --> 02:17:53.841
The French Navy defeated the British Navy

02:17:53.841 --> 02:17:57.175
in a crucial naval battle off the coast of Virginia,

02:17:57.175 --> 02:18:00.883
cutting off Cornwallis's only escape route by sea.

02:18:00.883 --> 02:18:03.508
On October 14th, 1781,

02:18:03.508 --> 02:18:06.883
the American and French forces launched a massive assault

02:18:06.883 --> 02:18:08.675
on the British defenses.

02:18:08.675 --> 02:18:12.383
The British fought valiantly but were vastly outnumbered

02:18:12.383 --> 02:18:15.591
and outgunned, and they soon began to falter.

02:18:15.591 --> 02:18:18.758
On October 19th, Cornwallis surrendered his army

02:18:18.758 --> 02:18:22.008
to Washington effectively ending the war.

02:18:22.008 --> 02:18:25.925
The victory at Yorktown was a decisive moment in the war,

02:18:25.925 --> 02:18:29.425
and it marked the end of British rule in America,

02:18:29.425 --> 02:18:32.008
and the beginning of a new experiment.

02:18:36.383 --> 02:18:38.633
With America finally being free

02:18:38.633 --> 02:18:41.800
from the totally tyrannical grips of Britain,

02:18:41.800 --> 02:18:45.008
they had one issue, how were they going to lead?

02:18:45.008 --> 02:18:45.841
Were they going

02:18:45.841 --> 02:18:48.716
to make General George Washington their monarch?

02:18:48.716 --> 02:18:51.675
Therefore, democracy was chosen.

02:18:51.675 --> 02:18:55.425
However, Plato made a good point many years ago

02:18:55.425 --> 02:18:57.508
that the common man was incapable

02:18:57.508 --> 02:18:59.758
and not wise enough to pick a better leader,

02:18:59.758 --> 02:19:01.675
to lead them to success.

02:19:01.675 --> 02:19:05.550
So the American founded constitutional convention came up

02:19:05.550 --> 02:19:08.466
with this idea of the electoral college,

02:19:08.466 --> 02:19:11.341
where the common man would vote for a particular person

02:19:11.341 --> 02:19:14.341
who would then have a say in who could be president.

02:19:14.341 --> 02:19:17.133
So instead of the president being directly voted on

02:19:17.133 --> 02:19:19.675
by the people, they would vote on elites

02:19:19.675 --> 02:19:22.133
who would then vote for the president directly.

02:19:27.508 --> 02:19:28.883
The French then noticed

02:19:28.883 --> 02:19:31.341
how well the American Revolution went.

02:19:31.341 --> 02:19:35.008
At the time the French were ruled by King Louis the 16th,

02:19:35.008 --> 02:19:37.758
and his wife, Queen Marie Antoinette.

02:19:37.758 --> 02:19:40.508
As Queen Marie Antoinette told the peasants,

02:19:40.508 --> 02:19:42.216
let them eat cake.

02:19:42.216 --> 02:19:44.508
The people of France got together.

02:19:44.508 --> 02:19:46.216
They decided they wanted more say

02:19:46.216 --> 02:19:48.133
in how the country was run,

02:19:48.133 --> 02:19:51.091
and they formed a group called the National Assembly

02:19:51.091 --> 02:19:54.591
and started making new laws to give them more rights.

02:19:54.591 --> 02:19:56.133
One of the most famous events

02:19:56.133 --> 02:19:59.550
of the French Revolution was the storming of the Bastille.

02:19:59.550 --> 02:20:03.133
This was a prison that represented the king's power,

02:20:03.133 --> 02:20:04.591
and the people wanted to show

02:20:04.591 --> 02:20:06.675
that they were not afraid of him.

02:20:06.675 --> 02:20:09.591
They broke into the prison and freed the prisoners,

02:20:09.591 --> 02:20:12.758
which started a revolution throughout France.

02:20:12.758 --> 02:20:15.758
Many influential people lost their heads

02:20:15.758 --> 02:20:19.675
during the revolution, including King Louis XVI

02:20:19.675 --> 02:20:22.508
and his wife Queen Marie Antoinette.

02:20:22.508 --> 02:20:25.258
The people were tired of being ruled by a king

02:20:25.258 --> 02:20:27.425
and queen who didn't care about them,

02:20:27.425 --> 02:20:29.383
and they wanted to create a new system

02:20:29.383 --> 02:20:31.675
where everyone would have a say,

02:20:31.675 --> 02:20:35.966
and the people of France voted in Maximilian Robespierre.

02:20:35.966 --> 02:20:39.925
In 1789 Robespierre was elected as a delegate

02:20:39.925 --> 02:20:42.591
to the Estates General, which was convened

02:20:42.591 --> 02:20:45.633
to address France's financial crisis.

02:20:45.633 --> 02:20:46.800
He quickly emerged

02:20:46.800 --> 02:20:50.425
as a leading voice in the National Assembly, advocating

02:20:50.425 --> 02:20:52.216
for the ordinary people's rights

02:20:52.216 --> 02:20:54.800
and opposing the aristocracy's power.

02:20:54.800 --> 02:20:57.050
As the revolution continued though,

02:20:57.050 --> 02:21:00.883
Robespierre became increasingly radical in his views,

02:21:00.883 --> 02:21:05.133
advocating for the execution of King Louis XVI

02:21:05.133 --> 02:21:07.508
and the establishment of a republic.

02:21:07.508 --> 02:21:09.841
He was elected to the powerful Committee

02:21:09.841 --> 02:21:12.841
of Public Safety in 1793,

02:21:12.841 --> 02:21:14.883
tasked with protecting the revolution

02:21:14.883 --> 02:21:17.091
and rooting out enemies of the state.

02:21:17.091 --> 02:21:19.091
Under Robespierre's leadership,

02:21:19.091 --> 02:21:22.466
the committee launched a period of intense repression known

02:21:22.466 --> 02:21:24.466
as the reign of terror.

02:21:24.466 --> 02:21:27.300
Thousands of people were arrested, tried

02:21:27.300 --> 02:21:30.675
and executed for crimes against the revolution.

02:21:30.675 --> 02:21:33.633
Robespierre became known as a ruthless,

02:21:33.633 --> 02:21:35.800
and uncompromising figure.

02:21:35.800 --> 02:21:38.633
However, Robespierre's power began to wane

02:21:38.633 --> 02:21:40.800
as the people grew tired of the violence

02:21:40.800 --> 02:21:43.258
and the instability of the revolution.

02:21:43.258 --> 02:21:45.966
In 1794, he was arrested

02:21:45.966 --> 02:21:49.383
and imprisoned along with his closest allies.

02:21:49.383 --> 02:21:53.591
On July 28th, 1794, Robespierre was taken

02:21:53.591 --> 02:21:56.591
to the guillotine and executed.

02:21:56.591 --> 02:22:00.675
The execution marked the end of the reign of terror

02:22:00.675 --> 02:22:03.591
and democracy for now in France.

02:22:03.591 --> 02:22:06.216
Instead, they moved to a directory.

02:22:06.216 --> 02:22:08.008
A directory is a government led

02:22:08.008 --> 02:22:12.050
by a five member executive council, known as the directory,

02:22:12.050 --> 02:22:14.883
which was chosen by the Council of Elders.

02:22:14.883 --> 02:22:18.341
This legislative body was also part of the new government.

02:22:18.341 --> 02:22:21.841
The directory was meant to serve as a moderating force,

02:22:21.841 --> 02:22:24.425
balancing the interests of the various factions

02:22:24.425 --> 02:22:26.800
that had emerged during the revolution.

02:22:31.425 --> 02:22:35.633
However, the directory concept wasn't successful as well,

02:22:35.633 --> 02:22:38.216
so general Napoleon Bonaparte decided

02:22:38.216 --> 02:22:40.008
to overthrow the government

02:22:40.008 --> 02:22:42.883
and begin his conquests to take over the world.

02:22:43.883 --> 02:22:47.133
So off Napoleon went to conquer much of Europe.

02:22:47.133 --> 02:22:48.550
In 1805,

02:22:48.550 --> 02:22:52.258
Napoleon defeated a combined Austro Russian army

02:22:52.258 --> 02:22:56.175
at the Battle of Austerlitz solidifying his position as one

02:22:56.175 --> 02:22:58.758
of Europe's most powerful leaders.

02:22:58.758 --> 02:23:02.008
He then conquered much of the continent, including Spain,

02:23:02.008 --> 02:23:04.383
Portugal, and the Netherlands.

02:23:04.383 --> 02:23:09.008
In 1812, Napoleon invaded Russia with a massive army.

02:23:09.008 --> 02:23:12.383
Still, the campaign proved disastrous

02:23:12.383 --> 02:23:17.008
and his forces were decimated by the harsh Russian winter.

02:23:17.008 --> 02:23:20.675
The defeat marked the beginning of Napoleon's downfall.

02:23:20.675 --> 02:23:24.925
In 1814, the European powers allied against Napoleon

02:23:24.925 --> 02:23:28.675
and invaded France, forcing him to abdicate his throne

02:23:28.675 --> 02:23:31.508
and go into exile on the Island of Elba.

02:23:31.508 --> 02:23:34.841
However, he returned to France in 1815

02:23:34.841 --> 02:23:37.591
in what became known as the hundred days

02:23:37.591 --> 02:23:39.550
and briefly regained power

02:23:39.550 --> 02:23:42.883
before being defeated by the British and Prussian armies,

02:23:42.883 --> 02:23:44.508
at the Battle of Waterlo.

02:23:49.383 --> 02:23:50.966
While back in the Americas,

02:23:50.966 --> 02:23:54.216
Simon Bolivar was on his military campaigns

02:23:54.216 --> 02:23:56.591
to free Latin American countries,

02:23:56.591 --> 02:23:59.425
from the grasp of the Spanish colonial rule.

02:23:59.425 --> 02:24:04.425
Bolivar began his military campaigns in Venezuela in 1810,

02:24:04.675 --> 02:24:06.591
where he led a successful uprising

02:24:06.591 --> 02:24:09.258
against the Spanish colonial authorities.

02:24:09.258 --> 02:24:11.966
He then moved on to Columbia where he won a series

02:24:11.966 --> 02:24:14.591
of important victories against the Spanish,

02:24:14.591 --> 02:24:18.300
including the Battle of Boyaca in 1819,

02:24:18.300 --> 02:24:21.300
which secured the independence of Columbia.

02:24:21.300 --> 02:24:24.091
Bolivar then turned his attention to Ecuador

02:24:24.091 --> 02:24:27.758
and Peru, where he won a series of decisive battles

02:24:27.758 --> 02:24:30.800
that helped secure both country's independence.

02:24:30.800 --> 02:24:34.383
He captured the city of Lima in 1824,

02:24:34.383 --> 02:24:37.591
effectively ending Spanish control of Peru.

02:24:37.591 --> 02:24:41.216
Bolivar's final military campaign was in Bolivia

02:24:41.216 --> 02:24:43.133
where he led the fight for independence

02:24:43.133 --> 02:24:45.925
against the Spanish in 1825,

02:24:45.925 --> 02:24:48.633
Bolivia was named in honor of Bolivar

02:24:48.633 --> 02:24:51.841
who played a critical role in its liberation.

02:24:56.675 --> 02:24:59.633
In 1848, 2 men had an idea

02:24:59.633 --> 02:25:02.050
that would spark debate worldwide.

02:25:02.050 --> 02:25:05.258
Karl Marx and Friedrich Engels wrote the book called

02:25:05.258 --> 02:25:09.091
"The Communist Manifesto," which is a book about the idea

02:25:09.091 --> 02:25:12.633
of communism, where instead of a capitalistic system

02:25:12.633 --> 02:25:15.841
where the nobles or bourgeois own everything,

02:25:15.841 --> 02:25:17.758
and the workers and proletariats work

02:25:17.758 --> 02:25:19.300
for slave wages,

02:25:19.300 --> 02:25:22.675
instead, what if the proletariats own the means

02:25:22.675 --> 02:25:25.300
of production and all work together?

02:25:25.300 --> 02:25:27.341
As Marx and Engles would write,

02:25:27.341 --> 02:25:32.050
let the ruling classes tremble at a communistic revolution,

02:25:32.050 --> 02:25:34.050
"the proletarians would have nothing

02:25:34.050 --> 02:25:38.216
to lose but their chains and they have, and they'd to win."

02:25:38.216 --> 02:25:39.966
They would also write "the need

02:25:39.966 --> 02:25:42.008
for a constantly expanding market

02:25:42.008 --> 02:25:44.466
for its products chases the bourgeoisie

02:25:44.466 --> 02:25:46.758
over the whole surface of the globe.

02:25:46.758 --> 02:25:50.175
It must nestle everywhere, settle everywhere,

02:25:50.175 --> 02:25:53.008
establish connections everywhere."

02:25:58.258 --> 02:25:59.425
Right after the writing

02:25:59.425 --> 02:26:02.966
of "The Communist Manifesto" began a period in Europe known

02:26:02.966 --> 02:26:05.550
as the Scramble for Africa.

02:26:05.550 --> 02:26:09.591
It all began in the 1870s when European countries began

02:26:09.591 --> 02:26:12.550
to explore the interior of Africa, looking

02:26:12.550 --> 02:26:16.341
for new territories to claim and resources to exploit.

02:26:16.341 --> 02:26:19.466
At first, the European powers were cautious,

02:26:19.466 --> 02:26:22.800
sending explorers and missionaries into Africa

02:26:22.800 --> 02:26:24.550
to establish trade networks

02:26:24.550 --> 02:26:26.925
and alliances with local leaders.

02:26:26.925 --> 02:26:29.258
However, as competition increased,

02:26:29.258 --> 02:26:32.966
the European powers became more aggressive in their tactics.

02:26:32.966 --> 02:26:36.091
They used military force to establish colonies

02:26:36.091 --> 02:26:38.341
and protectorates, and they engaged

02:26:38.341 --> 02:26:41.758
in diplomatic maneuvering and propaganda campaigns

02:26:41.758 --> 02:26:44.633
to gain the support of local populations.

02:26:44.633 --> 02:26:48.425
One of the most ruthless tactics the European powers used

02:26:48.425 --> 02:26:52.133
was dividing Africa into artificial borders

02:26:52.133 --> 02:26:56.008
and creating new ethnic and linguistic divisions.

02:26:56.008 --> 02:26:57.425
This created tensions

02:26:57.425 --> 02:27:00.508
and conflicts between different African groups,

02:27:00.508 --> 02:27:03.550
which the Europeans used to their advantage,

02:27:03.550 --> 02:27:07.591
creating a European stronghold over the continent of Africa

02:27:07.591 --> 02:27:09.466
to increase their profits.

02:27:09.466 --> 02:27:11.841
The scramble for Africa came to an end

02:27:11.841 --> 02:27:14.091
as a result of several factors,

02:27:14.091 --> 02:27:16.758
including changing international politics,

02:27:16.758 --> 02:27:20.591
economic realities, and rising African nationalism.

02:27:20.591 --> 02:27:23.341
One of the key factors that contributed to the end

02:27:23.341 --> 02:27:26.841
of the scramble for Africa was the changing balance

02:27:26.841 --> 02:27:28.466
of power in Europe.

02:27:28.466 --> 02:27:30.425
By the early 20th century,

02:27:30.425 --> 02:27:33.925
European powers were increasingly focused on competition

02:27:33.925 --> 02:27:37.591
with each other, particularly in Europe itself,

02:27:37.591 --> 02:27:38.966
and were less interested

02:27:38.966 --> 02:27:41.841
in acquiring new colonies in Africa.

02:27:41.841 --> 02:27:44.341
This was due in part to the growing tensions

02:27:44.341 --> 02:27:47.841
between European powers that would eventually lead

02:27:47.841 --> 02:27:51.966
to the outbreak of World War I in 1914.

02:27:53.550 --> 02:27:57.716
Because on June 28th, 1914, a shot was heard

02:27:57.716 --> 02:28:00.508
around the world with the assassination

02:28:00.508 --> 02:28:03.133
of Arch Duke Franz Ferdinand.

02:28:03.133 --> 02:28:05.800
Franz Ferdinand was the heir to the throne

02:28:05.800 --> 02:28:08.716
of Austria-Hungary, and his assassination

02:28:08.716 --> 02:28:10.591
by a Serbian nationalist

02:28:10.591 --> 02:28:15.050
named Gavrilo Princip sparked a diplomatic crisis

02:28:15.050 --> 02:28:18.800
that quickly escalated into a global conflict.

02:28:18.800 --> 02:28:21.133
In the aftermath of the assassination,

02:28:21.133 --> 02:28:23.966
Austria-Hungary declared war on Serbia,

02:28:23.966 --> 02:28:26.841
triggering a complex web of alliances

02:28:26.841 --> 02:28:30.425
and treaties that drew other countries into the conflict.

02:28:30.425 --> 02:28:34.633
Germany, an ally of Austria-Hungary declared war on Russia

02:28:34.633 --> 02:28:37.800
and France, while Great Britain, which had a treaty

02:28:37.800 --> 02:28:40.341
with Belgium declared war on Germany.

02:28:40.341 --> 02:28:44.966
Within weeks, most of Europe was embroiled in a brutal

02:28:44.966 --> 02:28:46.925
and devastating conflict.

02:28:46.925 --> 02:28:48.883
In November, 1918,

02:28:48.883 --> 02:28:53.466
after four years of brutal fighting, the allied powers

02:28:53.466 --> 02:28:56.675
and the central powers agreed to an armistice,

02:28:56.675 --> 02:28:58.883
effectively bringing an end to the war

02:28:58.883 --> 02:29:01.341
and the demise of the Ottoman Empire.

02:29:01.341 --> 02:29:04.591
On November 11th, the armistice went into effect

02:29:04.591 --> 02:29:07.133
and the guns fell silent across Europe.

02:29:12.591 --> 02:29:15.966
World War II, the peace was short lived

02:29:15.966 --> 02:29:19.800
because a man named Adolf Hitler invaded Poland.

02:29:19.800 --> 02:29:23.758
Like Alexander the Great, Julius Caesar, Trajan,

02:29:23.758 --> 02:29:27.175
Attila the Hun, Genghis Khan, Napoleon Bonaparte,

02:29:27.175 --> 02:29:28.675
and Suleiman the Great.

02:29:28.675 --> 02:29:31.508
Adolf Hitler wanted to establish an empire

02:29:31.508 --> 02:29:34.050
for his nation and his people.

02:29:34.050 --> 02:29:37.883
Adolf had dreams of building an empire larger than anything

02:29:37.883 --> 02:29:39.675
that was ever created.

02:29:39.675 --> 02:29:43.341
He wanted to make the Roman Empire look like nothing.

02:29:43.341 --> 02:29:45.508
However, for the sake of the world,

02:29:45.508 --> 02:29:49.591
and especially those Hitler viewed as undesirable vermin,

02:29:49.591 --> 02:29:51.925
in April, 1945,

02:29:51.925 --> 02:29:55.800
Soviet forces began a massive assault on Berlin.

02:29:55.800 --> 02:29:59.966
After weeks of intense fighting, the city fell on May 2nd,

02:29:59.966 --> 02:30:02.133
and German forces surrendered.

02:30:02.133 --> 02:30:05.675
Meanwhile, allied forces were closing in from the West,

02:30:05.675 --> 02:30:10.091
and on May 7th, Germany signed an unconditional surrender,

02:30:10.091 --> 02:30:12.841
officially ending the war in Europe.

02:30:12.841 --> 02:30:16.091
A few months later, after the bombings of Nagasaki

02:30:16.091 --> 02:30:19.175
and Hiroshima, Japan surrendered as well.

02:30:19.175 --> 02:30:21.300
Leaving the war to be over.

02:30:28.675 --> 02:30:31.466
From World War II on, the world has faced

02:30:31.466 --> 02:30:33.675
a technological revolution

02:30:33.675 --> 02:30:36.091
with Alan Turing's invention of the computer

02:30:36.091 --> 02:30:39.758
during the war, the world became global.

02:30:39.758 --> 02:30:41.633
For 50 years, America

02:30:41.633 --> 02:30:44.633
and the Soviet Union were at war despite the fact

02:30:44.633 --> 02:30:47.758
that they were on two totally different continents.

02:30:47.758 --> 02:30:52.758
In 1969, Neil Armstrong landed on the moon saying.

02:30:52.758 --> 02:30:54.716
- [Neil] It's one small step for a man,

02:30:56.300 --> 02:30:58.550
one giant leap for mankind.

02:30:59.508 --> 02:31:00.508
- [Narrator] As the years

02:31:00.508 --> 02:31:03.300
on the world has become increasingly smaller,

02:31:03.300 --> 02:31:05.758
computers have become more affordable.

02:31:05.758 --> 02:31:08.966
Cell phones change the way we communicated with one another.

02:31:08.966 --> 02:31:10.341
Let's go back to the story

02:31:10.341 --> 02:31:14.341
of a man named Gilgamesh on his quest for immortality.

02:31:14.341 --> 02:31:16.841
At the end of the poem, Gilgamesh realizes

02:31:16.841 --> 02:31:20.133
"life, which you look for, you will never find.

02:31:20.133 --> 02:31:24.258
For when gods created man, they let death be his share

02:31:24.258 --> 02:31:27.508
and life withheld in their own hands."

02:31:27.508 --> 02:31:31.550
The history of human civilizations is an incomplete book,

02:31:31.550 --> 02:31:33.800
constantly being updated.

02:31:33.800 --> 02:31:35.841
Some things will never change.

02:31:35.841 --> 02:31:38.925
However, humans will always die.

02:31:38.925 --> 02:31:42.716
Empires will always rise and fall.

02:31:42.716 --> 02:31:46.091
The masses will always clamor towards safety.

02:31:50.300 --> 02:31:53.050
(dramatic music)

